{ :id => 1, :name => "vulcanica", :genus => { :id => 26, :name => "Fuchsia", :family => { :id => 18, :name => "onagraceae", :old_id => "120" }, :old_id => "121" }, :scientific => "Fuchsia vulcanica", :author => "André", :tropicos => "23200095", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 3 m de alto, con tallos color rosado rojizo. Hojas elípticas, hasta 10 cm de largo; márgenes ligeramente crenados, los pecíolos color rosado rojizo. Inflorescencia tiene con pocas flores. Flores colgantes, hasta 8 cm de largo, color rosado rojizo, tubulares con 4 sépalos triangulares y 4 pétalos ovados. Frutos carnosos, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, color verde con morado. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en los remanentes boscosos en las partes bajas del páramo.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 3 m tall, with reddish pink stems. Leaves elliptic, up to 10 cm long; margins slightly crenate, the petioles reddish pink. Inflorescence few-flowered. Flowers pendent, up to 8 cm long, reddish pink, tubular with 4 triangular sepals and 4 spathulate petals. Fruits fleshy, up to 1.5 cm long, green with purple. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the forests patches in the lower parts of the páramo.", :old_id => "122", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }] }
{ :id => 2, :name => "pedunculata", :genus => { :id => 3, :name => "Azorella", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" }, :old_id => "20" }, :scientific => "Azorella pedunculata", :author => "(Spreng.) Mathias & Constance", :tropicos => "1703586", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Plantas dispuestas en almohadillas muy compactas y grandes hasta de 2 m de diámetro. Hojas amontonadas al final de las ramas, hasta 1 cm de largo, muy duras y brillantes, tienen el ápice profundamente partido en 3 a 5 lóbulos espinosos. Inflorescencia pequeña, mide menos de 1 cm y tiene hasta 20 flores. Flores diminutas, hasta 3 mm de largo, color verde amarillento. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Colombia a Ecuador. En el Cajas es una especie muy común en varios ambientes.", :description_en => "Cushion-forming plants that form compact mounds up to 2 m in diameter. Leaves clustered at the tip of the branches, up to 1 cm long, very hard and glossy; apex is deeply divided into 3 to 5 spiny lobes. Inflorescence small, less than 1 cm long and with up to 20 flowers. Flowers minute, up to 3 mm long, yellowish green. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia to Ecuador. In Cajas it is a common species in various environments.", :old_id => "21", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 3, :name => "intermedia", :genus => { :id => 9, :name => "Calamagrostis", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" }, :old_id => "55" }, :scientific => "Calamagrostis intermedia", :author => "(J. Presl) Steud.", :tropicos => "25512876", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas en macollas densas, hasta 80 cm de diámetro. Hojas lineares y hasta 80 cm de largo; márgenes doblados y dan una apariencia cilíndrica a las hojas. Inflorescencias en llamativas, hasta 90 cm de largo, racimos compuestos con numerosas espiguillas amarillentas. Flores reducidas, hasta 10 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Argentina. En el Cajas es la planta dominante en el páramo de pajonal. Sobrevive a las quemas.", :description_en => "Large tussock grasses, up to 80 cm long in diameter. Leaves linear, up to 80 cm long; margins curled inwards along the leaf giving it a cylindrical shape. Inflorescences showy racemes, up to 90 cm long, with numerous yellowish spikelets. Flowers reduced, up to 10 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Argentina. In Cajas it is the dominant plant in the grass páramo. It survives fires.", :old_id => "56", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 4, :name => "americana", :genus => { :id => 21, :name => "Ephedra", :family => { :id => 14, :name => "ephedraceae", :old_id => "101" }, :old_id => "102" }, :scientific => "Ephedra americana", :author => "Willd", :tropicos => "14300006", :color1 => nil, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 50 cm de alto, bastante ramificados, color verde oliva. Hojas reducidas a escamas dispuestas en anillos espaciados a lo largo del tallo, hasta de 3 mm de largo, color rojo-rosado. Las estructuras reproductivas se llaman estróbilos y es un conjunto de hojas modificadas (brácteas) gruesas, hasta de 8 mm de largo, color verde con rojo-rosado, amarillo o anaranjado, los masculinos producen polen, los femeninos llevan óvulos. Las semillas envueltas por las brácteas engrosadas y carnosas, color rojo rosado. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador a Argentina. En el Cajas se encuentra en áreas rocosas.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 50 cm tall, profusely branched, olive-green. Leaves scale-like and arranged in rings spaced along the stem, up to 3 mm long, pinkish-red. The reproductive structures, called strobili, a group of modified, leathery leaves (bracts), up to 8 mm long, green suffused with pinkish-red, yellow or orange, the masculine bear pollen, the feminine bear ovules. The seeds covered with the fleshy, pinkish, swollen bracts. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Argentina. In Cajas it is found in rocky areas.", :old_id => "103", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 5, :name => "hypocarpium", :genus => { :id => 27, :name => "Galium", :family => { :id => 1, :name => "rubiaceae", :old_id => "6" }, :old_id => "124" }, :scientific => "Galium hypocarpium", :author => "(L.) Endl. ex Griseb.", :tropicos => "27909757", :color1 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas rastreras, cubiertas con pelos blancos. Hojas opuestas, hasta 1 cm, elípticas, junto con 2 estípulas muy parecidas se disponen en grupos de 4 en cada nudo. Inflorescencia con 2 flores. Flores poco llamativas, hasta de 4 mm de diámetro, con 4 pétalos color verdoso. Frutos globosos, hasta 7 mm de diámetro, carnosos, color anaranjado brillante. \\n", :distribution_es => " México hasta Paraguay. En el Cajas se encuentra dentro de los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Trailing herbs, covered with white hairs. Leaves opposite, up to 1 cm long, elliptic; together with 2 similar stipules in groups of 4 at each node. Inflorescence has 2 flowers. Flowers inconspicuous, up to 4 mm in diameter, with 4 greenish petals. Fruits globose, up to 7 mm in diameter, fleshy, bright orange. \\n", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Paraguay. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "125", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 6, :name => "filiforme", :genus => { :id => 1, :name => "Arcytophyllum", :family => { :id => 1, :name => "rubiaceae", :old_id => "6" }, :old_id => "7" }, :scientific => "Arcytophyllum filiforme", :author => "(Ruiz & Pav.) Standl.", :tropicos => "27904079", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas con apariencia de musgo, formando alfombras; tallos rastreros, algo leñosos. Hojas opuestas, lanceoladas, hasta de 0.4 cm de largo. Flores solitarias, hasta de 5 mm de largo, blancas o teñidas con lila o rosado, tienen un tubo corto con 4 lóbulos triangulares. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador a Bolivia. Especie común en los páramos. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal. Llama la atención su aspecto como musgo.", :description_en => "Moss-like herbs that form mats; stems trailing, somewhat woody. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 0.4 cm long. Flowers solitary, up to 5 mm long, white or tinged with lilac or pink; they have a short tube with 4 triangular lobes. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia. In Cajas it is a common species found in the grass páramo. Its moss-like habit is noticeable.", :old_id => "8", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 7, :name => "elata", :genus => { :id => 2, :name => "Arracacia", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" }, :old_id => "17" }, :scientific => "Arracacia elata", :author => "Wolff", :tropicos => "1700589", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas grandes, más de 1 m de alto, bastante ramificadas; tallos teñidos de café-rojizo. Hojas alternas, hasta 30 cm de largo, divididas en hojuelas hasta 6 cm de largo, más pálidas en la cara inferior; márgenes marcadamente aserrado-espinosos y profundamente partidos. Inflorescencia en forma de sombrilla hacia arriba, hasta de 10 cm de diámetro, tiene muchas flores. Flores pequeñas, hasta 4 mm de largo, color verde-amarillento. Frutos secos y hasta 8 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas se encuentran cerca o dentro de los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Large herbs, over 1 m tall, profusely branching; stems tinged with reddish-brown. Leaves alternate and compound, up to 30 cm long; its leaflets up to 6 cm long, paler below; margins coarsely serrate-spiny and deeply divided. Inflorescence like an upside down umbrella, up to 10 cm in diameter, many-flowered. Flowers small, up to 4 mm long, yellowish-green. Fruits dry and to 8 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is found in or around the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "18", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 8, :name => "australis", :genus => { :id => 60, :name => "Plantago", :family => { :id => 31, :name => "plantaginaceae", :old_id => "228" }, :old_id => "267" }, :scientific => "Plantago australis", :author => "Lam.", :tropicos => "25200077", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 40 cm de alto. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, hasta 40 cm de largo, lanceoladas, color verde con tintes morados, ambas superficies con pelos cortos. Inflorescencia alta, hasta de 40 cm, tiene numerosas flores. Flores poco vistosas, se disponen a lo largo del eje elevado, hasta 5 mm de largo y son verdosas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. En el Cajas crece en el páramo de pajonal y en áreas abiertas húmedas.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 40 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 40 cm long, lanceolate, green tinged with purple, both surfaces with short hairs. Inflorescence up to 40 cm long, with numerous flowers. Flowers inconspicuous and arranged on the elevated axis, up to 5 mm long and greenish. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. In Cajas it grows in the grass páramo and in open humid areas.", :old_id => "268", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 9, :name => "crassus", :genus => { :id => 36, :name => "Phlegmariurus", :family => { :id => 22, :name => "lycopodiaceae", :old_id => "166" }, :old_id => "167" }, :scientific => "Phlegmariurus crassus", :author => "(Willd.) Rothm", :tropicos => "100364214", :color1 => nil, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas hasta de 25 cm de alto, solitarias o en pequeños grupos; tallos con forma cilín­drica y a veces bifurcados en la punta. Hojas dispuestas en espiral, con forma de escamas alargadas, hasta 1 cm de largo, sobrepuestas, color verde a rojo-anaranjado o rojo-rosado. Hojas superiores llevan las estructuras reproductivas (esporan­gios) en la base; esporangios de 2 mm de largo, de forma arriñonada y color verde a amarillo. n", :distribution_es => " Guatemala a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Plants up to 25 cm tall, solitary or in small groups; stems cylindrical and some­times furcate at apex. Leaves spirally arranged, scale-shaped, up to 1 cm long, overlapping, green to orange-red or pink-red. The upper leaves bear the reproductive struc­tures (sporangia) at their base; sporangia 2 mm long and kidney-shaped, green to yellow. n", :distribution_en => " Guatemala to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the cushion páramo.", :old_id => "168", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 10, :name => "novo-granadensis", :genus => { :id => 39, :name => "Isoëtes", :family => { :id => 24, :name => "isoëtaceae", :old_id => "178" }, :old_id => "179" }, :scientific => "Isoëtes novo-granadensis", :author => "H. P. Fuchs", :tropicos => "26619689", :color1 => nil, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Plantas terrestres o acuáticas, hasta de 10 cm de diámetro; tallos generalmente carno­sos, cortos y en general enterrados. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta semi­enterrada, lineares, hasta de 5 cm de largo, algo triangulares en corte transversal y con cámaras de aire, gruesas, puntiagudas. Las estructuras reproductivas (esporangios) de 5 mm de largo, sean masculinas o femeninas se encuentran hundidas en la base de las hojas, recubiertas colora membrana; las esporas color que va de blanco a gris. n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentran en áreas muy húmedas o totalmente sumergidas en el agua", :description_en => "Terrestrial or aquatic plants, up to 10 cm in diameter; stems generally fleshy, and generally buried. Leaves arranged in a half-buried rosette, linear, up to 5 cm long, triangular in a transversal cut and containing air chambers, leathery, acute. The reproduc­tive structures (sporangia) 5 mm long, masculine or feminine, found at the base of the leaves and covered by a membrane; spores white to gray. n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in moist areas or totally submerged in water", :old_id => "180", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 11, :name => "goudotii", :genus => { :id => 40, :name => "Jamesonia", :family => { :id => 25, :name => "pteridaceae", :old_id => "182" }, :old_id => "183" }, :scientific => "Jamesonia goudotii", :author => "(Hieron.) C. Chr.", :tropicos => "26606391", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos terrestres, hasta de 35 cm de alto, cubiertos de pelos color café rojizo. Hojas hasta 30 cm de largo, rectas y tiesas, el ápice es enrollado, compuestas de numerosos pares de hojuelas generalmente con forma de orejuelas, hasta de 5 mm de largo, sobrepuestas, gruesas; márgenes enrollados hacia abajo. Las estructuras reproductivas (soros) se encuentran en la cara inferior de las hojas; las esporas color café oscuro. n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el bosque de Polylepis. Las especies de este género son casi exclusivas de los páramos andinos.", :description_en => "Terrestrial ferns, up to 35 cm tall, covered with reddish brown hairs. Leaves up to 30 cm long, erect and stiff with a coiled apex, and with numerous pairs of ear-shaped, leathery, overlapping leaflets to 5 mm long, with margins curled downwards. The reproductive structures (sori) on the lower side of the leaflets; spores dark brown. n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests. The species of this genus almost exclusive to the Andean páramos.", :old_id => "184", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 12, :name => "pygmaea", :genus => { :id => 76, :name => "Werneria", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "343" }, :scientific => "Werneria pygmaea", :author => "Gillies ex Hook. & Arn.", :tropicos => "2723559", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas hasta 5 cm de diámetro. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta basal, hasta 3 cm de largo, alargadas y muy estrechas. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas solitarias a nivel del suelo, ca. 2.5 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 14) irregulares y presentan una lengüeta hasta de 15 mm de largo, color blanco, las internas (± 25) cortas, tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. Frutos con una corona de pelos ca. 10 mm de largo y son color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela hasta Argentina. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de almohadillas y en áreas muy húmedas en los alrededores de las lagunas. Se diferencia de la especie anterior por su porte general más pequeño y menor número de flores.", :description_en => "Low herbs, up to 5 cm in diameter. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 3 cm long, elongate and narrow. Inflorescences of solitary heads at ground level up to 2.5 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 14 irregular and strap-shaped, 15 mm long, white, the internal (± 25) short, tubular, with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruits with a crown of white hairs, up to 10 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Argentina. In Cajas it is found in the cushion páramo and around the lakes. It differs from the previous species by its overall smaller size.", :old_id => "348", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 13, :name => "quitense", :genus => { :id => 47, :name => "Myriophyllum", :family => { :id => 29, :name => "haloragaceae", :old_id => "211" }, :old_id => "212" }, :scientific => "Myriophyllum quitense", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "15000089", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas acuáticas sumergidas y flotantes, se las ve en grupos densos; tallos de longitud variable, a veces semi-leñosos. Hojas dispuestas en verticilos y se ven 4 ó 5 al mismo nivel, hasta 1.5 cm de largo; las hojas sumergidas tienen muchas divisiones muy delgadas como hilos; las hojas emergentes son enteras, color verde-amarillo con tintes rojizos, con los márgenes aserrados. Flores diminutas, hasta 3 mm de largo y son verdosas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Tierra del Fuego. En el Cajas es común en las lagunas.", :description_en => "Aquatic herbs, submerged and floating, forming dense groups; stems variable in length and sometimes woody. Leaves in groups of 4 or 5. to 1.5 cm long; submerged leaves have many slender divisions like thread; emerging leaves entire, yellow-green tinged with red and the margins serrate. Flowers minute, up to 3 mm long and greenish. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Tierra del Fuego. In Cajas it is common in the lakes.", :old_id => "213", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 14, :name => "caespitosa", :genus => { :id => 4, :name => "Baccharis", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "24" }, :scientific => "Baccharis caespitosa", :author => "(Lam.) Pers.", :tropicos => "2722892", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas, rastreras, forman alfombras o crecen entre otras plantas, los tallos presentan tonos rosados. Hojas espatuladas, hasta 0.5 cm de largo, amontonadas, carnosas y color verde oscuro y brillantes, con las puntas cafés. Inflorescencias en capítulos solitarios hasta de 1 cm de diámetro, ubicados en las puntas de los tallos. Flores numerosas, tubulares y color blanco-crema. El fruto tiene una corona de pelos de 8 mm y color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de almohadillas y ocasionalmente en el pajonal, en general entremezclada con otras plantas.", :description_en => "Low, crawling herbs, forming mats or growing among other plants, the stem suffused with pink. Leaves spathulate, up to 0.5 cm long, clustered, fleshy, dark green and glossy, with a brown apex. Inflorescences a solitary head up to 1 cm in diameter, terminal on the stems. Flowers numerous, tubular, cream-white. Fruits with a crown of white hairs, 8 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the cushion and occasionally in the grass páramo, in general interspersed with other plants.", :old_id => "25", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 15, :name => "lutea", :genus => { :id => 6, :name => "Berberis", :family => { :id => 5, :name => "berberidaceae", :old_id => "38" }, :old_id => "39" }, :scientific => "Berberis lutea", :author => "Ruiz & Pav.", :tropicos => "3500102", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 3 m de alto, con madera amarilla. Hojas alternas pero se encuentran amon­tonadas, hasta 2 cm de largo, brillantes en la cara superior y más claras en la inferior, la punta es espinosa; márgenes enteros o espinosos. Flores solitarias, colgantes, y hasta de 10 mm de diámetro, color amarillo brillante, teñidas de rosado por fuera. Frutos subglobosos, carnosos, hasta 8 mm de largo, verdes, luego rojizos y finalmente color negro-morado. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 3 m tall, with yellow wood. Leaves alternate but clustered, up to 2 cm long, glossy above, paler below, with a spiny tip; margins entire or spiny. Flowers solitary, pendent, up to 10 mm in diameter, bright yellow, tinged with pink. Fruits subglobose, fleshy, up to 8 mm long, green turning reddish and finally purple-black. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "40", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 16, :name => "crassifolia", :genus => { :id => 46, :name => "Monnina", :family => { :id => 28, :name => "polygalaceae", :old_id => "207" }, :old_id => "208" }, :scientific => "Monnina crassifolia", :author => "(Bonpl.) Kunth", :tropicos => "25900130", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 1.5 m de alto. Hojas alternas, lanceoladas, hasta 6 cm de largo, gruesas. Inflorescencia tiene numerosas flores, hasta 6 cm de largo. Flores hasta unos 6 mm de largo, tienen la forma de mariposa, color azul o azul-morado, uno de los pétalos llamado “quilla” tiene la punta amarilla. Frutos carnosos, con forma de elipse o de fréjol, hasta 8 mm de largo, color vino morado y verde en la base cuando inmaduros, color negro-morado cuando maduros. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas es muy común en varios ambientes.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1.5 m tall. Leaves alternate, lanceolate, up to 6 cm long, leathery. Inflorescence has numerous flowers, up to 6 cm long. Flowers up to 6 mm long, butterfly-shaped, blue or purple-blue; one of the petals, the 'keel', has a yellow tip. Fruits fleshy, ellipsoid or kidney-shaped, up to 8 mm long, wine purple and green at base when young, turning purple black. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is common in various environments.", :old_id => "209", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 17, :name => "sedifolia", :genus => { :id => 28, :name => "Gentiana", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "129" }, :scientific => "Gentiana sedifolia", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "13800257", :color1 => { :id => 9, :name => "blue", :old_id => "127" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, hasta 4 cm de alto. Hojas opuestas, hasta 0.7 cm de largo, lanceoladas y estrechas. Flores solitarias, erguidas, hasta de 10 mm de diámetro, con forma de embudo, color azul pálido o violeta, con puntos morados hacia el centro y con la garganta amarilla, raras veces color blanco o amarillo pálido. La flor se cierra durante la noche o si se oculta el sol. \\n", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica a Bolivia. En el Cajas es común en todos los ambientes, crecen entre las almohadillas junto a otras plantas o bajo las macollas de paja.", :description_en => "Small herbs, up to 4 cm tall. Leaves opposite, up to 0.7 cm long, lanceolate and narrow. Flowers solitary and erect, up to 10 mm in diameter, funnel-shaped, pale blue or violet, with purple dots in the center and with a yellow throat, rarely white or pale yellow. The flower closes at night or on cold and cloudy days. \\n", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Bolivia. In Cajas it is common in all environments, growing within cushion plants or in the tussock grass.", :old_id => "130", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 18, :name => "aciculare", :genus => { :id => 37, :name => "Hypericum", :family => { :id => 23, :name => "hypericaceae", :old_id => "170" }, :old_id => "171" }, :scientific => "Hypericum aciculare", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "7800273", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 50 cm de alto, muy ramificados. Hojas opuestas, hasta de 15 mm de largo, con forma de aguja y se las ve amontonadas. Flores solitarias, en la punta de las ramas, hasta 40 mm de diámetro, con 5 pétalos color amarillo intenso; estambres son numerosos, también color amarillo. Frutos cápsulas ovadas, secas, color café. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Ecuador al N Perú. En el Cajas se lo encuentra dentro de los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 50 cm tall, profusely branched. Leaves opposite, up to 15 mm long, needle-like and clustered. Flowers solitary, at the top of the branches, up to 40 mm in diameter, with 5 bright yellow petals, the stamens numerous, yellow. Fruits ovate, dry, brown capsules. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Ecuador to N Peru. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "172", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 19, :name => "acaulis", :genus => { :id => 10, :name => "Calandrinia", :family => { :id => 8, :name => "portulacaceae", :old_id => "59" }, :old_id => "60" }, :scientific => "Calandrinia acaulis", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "26200245", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas, pegadas al suelo, de 8 cm de diámetro. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, lineares, que hasta de 5 cm de largo, con la base color rojo-rosado. Flores individuales, hasta 8 mm de largo, tubulares, y se encuentran varias por planta, a menudo escondidas entre las hojas, color rosado o violeta pálido, a veces casi blancas. Frutos envueltos en el cáliz color rojo con textura como papel. \\n", :distribution_es => " México a Chile. En el Cajas se encuentra en áreas rocosas o pedregosas.", :description_en => "Low herbs at ground level, 8 cm in diameter. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, linear, up to 5 cm long, with a pinkish-red base. Flowers single, up to 8 mm long, tubular, and various per plant, often hidden among the leaves, pink or pale violet, sometimes almost white. Fruits enclosed in the red papery calyx. \\n", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Chile. In Cajas it is found in rocky or sandy areas.", :old_id => "61", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 20, :name => "arbutifolia", :genus => { :id => 55, :name => "Pentacalia", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "248" }, :scientific => "Pentacalia arbutifolia", :author => "(Kunth) Cuatrec.", :tropicos => "2733350", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 2 m de alto. Hojas alternas, de menos de 1 cm de largo, gruesas, brillantes en la superficie superior, los márgenes con dientes pequeños. Inflorescencia en cabezuelas pequeñas, cada una hasta de 1.5 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 10) presentan una lengüeta angosta hasta de 8 mm de largo, color amarillo pálido o crema, las internas (± 20) tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo pálido o amarillo verdoso. Frutos con una corona de pelos sedosos, 8 mm de largo, color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador. En el Cajas es común en remanentes de bosques y en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 2 m tall. Leaves alternate, less than 1 cm long, thick, glossy above; margins have small teeth. Inflorescence has small heads, each up to 1.5 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 10) strap-shaped, narrow, up to 8 mm long, pale yellow or cream, the internal (± 20) tubular and with 5 teeth, pale yellow or greenish yellow. Fruits with a crown of white silky hairs, up to 8 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador. In Cajas it is common in the patches of forest in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "249", :provincias => [{ :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 21, :name => "peruvianum", :genus => { :id => 31, :name => "Geum", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "148" }, :scientific => "Geum peruvianum", :author => "Focke", :tropicos => "27800530", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 80 cm de alto, cubiertas de pelos. Hojas alternas, las de la base divididas, tienen la forma de lira, hasta 15 cm de largo, las hojas superiores hasta 4 cm y generalmente tienen 3 lóbulos. Inflorescencia hasta de 8 cm de largo, con 1 a 7 flores. Flores hasta 10 mm de diámetro, con 5 pétalos abiertos, color amarillo brillante; pistilos son numerosos. Fruto globoso, de 15 mm de diámetro, y está formado por un conjunto de pequeños frutos secos, cada uno de 4 mm y con un gancho alargado. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas crece en áreas arbustivas.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 80 cm tall, covered with hairs. Leaves alternate, the basal divided, lyre-shaped, up to 15 cm long, the upper ones generally 3-lobed and up to 4 cm long. Inflorescence up to 8 cm long has 1 to 7 flowers. Flowers up to 10 mm in diameter, with 5 open, bright yellow petals, with numerous pistils. Fruit globose, 15 mm in diameter, and it is an aggregate of small dry fruits each 4 mm long and with a long hook. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is found in shrubby areas.", :old_id => "149", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 22, :name => "serpyllifolia", :genus => { :id => 33, :name => "Halenia", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "156" }, :scientific => "Halenia serpyllifolia", :author => "J. S. Pringle", :tropicos => "13803175", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas menos de 10 cm de alto. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base y otras opuestas a lo largo color corto tallo, hasta 1 cm de largo, lanceoladas. Flores solitarias o a veces de 2 a 4 reunidas, hasta 10 mm de largo, color verde-amarillo claro, con prolongaciones en forma de espuelas hasta 6 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Especie endémica del Cajas, se la ve en páramos de almohadillas. De las tres especies que se encuentran en el Cajas, esta es la más pequeña; todas tienen las flores de forma y color similares, pero las otras son plantas más grandes.", :description_en => "Small herbs less than 10 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette with others opposite along a short stem, lanceolate, up to 1 cm long. Flowers solitary or sometimes 2 to 4. up to 10 mm long, light green-yellow, with spur-like extensions up to 6 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Cajas, in the cushion páramo. Of the three species found in Cajas, this is the smallest; all have the flowers with similar shape and color, but the others arelarger plants.", :old_id => "157", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 23, :name => "chionophila", :genus => { :id => 45, :name => "Miconia", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "202" }, :scientific => "Miconia chionophila", :author => "Naud.", :tropicos => "20301006", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Arbustos pequeños con los tallos tendidos y rastreros, con pelos glandulares en las ramitas y hojas. Hojas opuestas, ovadas, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, con pelos esparcidos en los bordes, con 3 venas sobresalientes. Flores por lo general dispuestas por debajo de las ramas, solitarias, hasta de 1.5 cm de diámetro, con forma de copa (hipanto) y con 4 pétalos y 4 estambres color blanco; estigma es grande. Frutos carnosos y verdes. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Bolivia. En la Cajas es común en los bosques de Polylepis y ocasionalmente escondida entre pajonales.", :description_en => "Small shrubs, with trailing stems; twigs and leaves covered with glandular hairs. Leaves opposite, ovate, up to 1.5 cm long, with scattered hairs on the margins, and with 3 raised veins. Flowers solitary and generally beneath the branches, up to 1.5 cm diameter, cup-shaped (hypanthium), with 4 white petals and 4 stamens; stigma is large. Fruits fleshy and green. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia. In Cajas it is common in the Polylepis forests and occasionally hidden among the tussock grasses.", :old_id => "203", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 24, :name => "salicifolia", :genus => { :id => 45, :name => "Miconia", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "202" }, :scientific => "Miconia salicifolia", :author => "(Bonpl. ex Naudin) Naudin", :tropicos => "20302462", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de 1 a 4 m, con forma columnar, densamente ramificados; tallos, la cara inferior de las hojas y las flores cubiertos de pelos color amarillento a café-rojizo. Hojas opuestas, hasta de 5 cm de largo, lanceoladas y estrechas, los márgenes enrollados hacia abajo. Inflorescencia de 1 a 2 cm de largo, con pocas flores. Flores hasta de 5 mm de largo, con forma de copa, rosadas con los pétalos color blanco-crema; estambres rosados. Frutos redondeados y carnosos, hasta de 6 mm de largo, color verde azulado y luego morado. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el subpáramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Shrubs 1 to 4 m tall, with an overall columnar shape, densely branched, the stem, lower surface of leaves, and flowers covered with yellowish to reddish-brown hairs. Leaves opposite, up to 5 cm long, lanceolate and narrow, the margins curl downwards. Inflorescence 1 to 2 cm long, few-flowered. Flowers up to 5 mm long, cup-shaped, pink; petals cream-white; stamens pink. Fruits round and fleshy, up to 6 mm long, bluish-green turning purple. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. In Cajas it is found in the grass subpáramo.", :old_id => "205", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 25, :name => "prostrata", :genus => { :id => 58, :name => "Pernettya", :family => { :id => 13, :name => "ericaceae", :old_id => "91" }, :old_id => "260" }, :scientific => "Pernettya prostrata", :author => "(Cav.) DC.", :tropicos => "50066293", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos bajos, hasta de 30 cm de alto. Hojas alternas, lanceoladas, hasta de 1.5 cm de largo, gruesas, con el margen aserrado. Flores solitarias, hasta de 5 mm de largo, con forma de jarroncito con 5 dientes, blancas a veces teñidas de rosado. Frutos redondeados y carnosos, hasta de 10 mm de largo, color negro-azul oscuro. \\n", :distribution_es => " C México hasta NO Argentina. En el Cajas se encuentra hasta de los bosques de Polylepis y en el pajonal.", :description_en => "Low shrubs up to 30 cm tall. Leaves alternate, lanceolate, up to 1.5 cm long, leathery, with serrate margins. Flowers solitary, up to 5 mm long, vase-shaped with 5 teeth, white sometimes tinged with pale pink. Fruits round and fleshy, up to 10 mm long, blackish-blue. \\n", :distribution_en => " C Mexico to NW Argentina. In Cajas it is found around the Polylepis forests and in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "261", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }] }
{ :id => 26, :name => "pimpinellifolia", :genus => { :id => 19, :name => "Dorobaea", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "95" }, :scientific => "Dorobaea pimpinellifolia", :author => "(Kunth) B. Nord.", :tropicos => "2733220", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 25 cm de alto. Hojas muy divididas y se disponen en una roseta en la base, hasta 5 cm de largo. Inflorescencia elevada y está formada por cabezuelas vistosas hasta de 7 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 20) irre­gu­lares, presentan una lengüeta que hasta de 30 mm de largo, color amarillo brillante, las internas (más de 50) tubulares, con 5 dientes, color amarillo oscuro a ana­ran­jado. Frutos con una corona de pelos sedosos hasta 10 mm de largo y son color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas es común en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 25 cm tall. Leaves much divided, up to 5 cm long, and arranged in a basal rosette. The elevated inflorescence is of showy heads, up to 7 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 20) irregular, strap-shaped, up to 30 mm long, bright yellow, the internal (more than 50) tubular, with 5 teeth, dark yellow to orange. Fruits with a crown of white silky hairs up to 10 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is common in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "96", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 27, :name => "flagelliformis", :genus => { :id => 66, :name => "Ranunculus", :family => { :id => 38, :name => "ranunculaceae", :old_id => "293" }, :old_id => "294" }, :scientific => "Ranunculus flagelliformis", :author => "Sm.", :tropicos => "27100571", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas acuáticas o semi-acuáticas hasta 25 cm de largo. Hojas flotantes en la superficie del agua, elípticas a ovadas, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, sobre pecíolos largos y delgados. Flores emergentes, hasta 7 mm de diámetro, tienen 5 pétalos color amarillo limón; pistilos son numerosos y color amarillo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica, Venezuela a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en charcas o lagunas poco profundas.", :description_en => "Aquatic or semi-aquatic herbs up to 25 cm long. Leaves floating on the water surface elliptic to ovate, up to 1.5 cm long, on long and slender petioles. Flowers emergent, up to 7 mm in diameter, with 5 lemon yellow petals; pistils numerous and yellow. \\n", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica, Venezuela to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in pools or shallow lakes.", :old_id => "295", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 19, :name => "galapagos" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 28, :name => "crocifolium", :genus => { :id => 49, :name => "Oritrophium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "225" }, :scientific => "Oritrophium crocifolium", :author => "(Lam.) Cuatrec", :tropicos => "2738138", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 30 cm de alto, con largos pelos sedosos blancos. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta basal, hasta 10 cm de largo, alargadas y muy estrechas, con los márgenes engrosados y doblados hacia abajo. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas solitarias ergui­das, ca. 2 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 80) irregulares y presentan una lengüeta estrecha hasta de 10 mm de largo, color blanco, las internas (± 50) cortas, tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amari­llo pálido. Frutos con una corona de pelos ásperos ca. 8 mm y son color amarillo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador y Perú. En el Cajas es común en todos los ambientes.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 30 cm tall, covered with long, silky, white hairs. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 10 cm long, elongate and narrow, with the thickened margin curled downwards. Inflorescences solitary, erect heads, up to 2 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 80) irregular, strap-shaped, up to 10 mm long, white, the internal (± 50) short, tubular and with 5 teeth, pale yellow. Fruits with a crown of coarse hairs, up to 8 mm long, yellow \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and Peru. In Cajas it is common in all environments.", :old_id => "226", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }] }
{ :id => 29, :name => "nubigena", :genus => { :id => 76, :name => "Werneria", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "343" }, :scientific => "Werneria nubigena", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "2711495", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas hasta 15 cm de diámetro. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta basal, hasta 10 cm de largo, alargadas y estrechas. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas solitarias a ras del suelo, ca. 7 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 25) irregu­lares y presentan una lengüeta hasta de 25 mm de largo, color blanco, las internas (más de 100) cortas, tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. Frutos con una corona de pelos blancos. \\n", :distribution_es => " S México, Guatemala, Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas es común en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Low herbs, up to 15 cm in diameter. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 10 cm long, elongate and narrow. Inflorescences solitary heads at ground level, up to 7 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 25) irregular and strap-shaped, up to 25 mm long, white, the internal (more than 100) short, tubular and with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruits with a crown of white hairs. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Mexico, Guatemala, Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is common in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "344", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 30, :name => "rigida", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana rigida", :author => "Ruiz & Pav.", :tropicos => "33500386", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas sin tallo, con olor fuerte y desagradable, ca. 10 cm de diámetro; crecen a nivel del suelo, a veces forman almohadillas. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta basal, lanceoladas, hasta 10 cm de largo, estrechas, gruesas y punzantes. Flores pequeñas, hasta de 5 mm de largo, tubulares con 5 lóbulos cortos, color blanco, se las puede ver varias en el centro de la roseta de las hojas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Stemless herbs, with a strong unpleasant smell, up to 10 cm in diameter; they grow at ground level, sometimes forming cushions. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, lanceolate, up to 10 cm long, narrow, leathery, and prickly. Flowers small, various in the center of the rosette, up to 5 mm long, white, tubular, with 5 short lobes. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "334", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 31, :name => "ericoides", :genus => { :id => 17, :name => "Diplostephium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "86" }, :scientific => "Diplostephium ericoides", :author => "(Lam.) Cabrera", :tropicos => "2733144", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 1 m de alto, bastante ramificados, las ramas con pelos lanosos color blanco grisáceo. Hojas alternas, lineares, hasta 0.5 cm de largo, gruesas, el margen doblado hacia abajo, la cara inferior cubierta por una densa capa de pelos lanosos color blanco grisáceo. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas ca. 1.5 cm de diámetro, ubicadas al final de las ramas. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 15) irregulares y presentan una lengüeta hasta de 8 mm de largo, color blanco, las internas (± 20) tubulares y con 5 dientes, color ama­rillo a anaranjado. Frutos con una corona de pelos de 10 mm de largo, blancos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del país. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1 m tall, profusely branched, with grayish-white, wooly hairs. Leaves alternate, linear, up to 0.5 cm long, leathery, below densely covered with grayish-white wooly hairs; margin curled downwards. Inflorescences heads, up to 1.5 cm in diameter, at the end of the branches. Flowers of two types: the external (± 15) irregular and strap-shaped, up to 8 mm long, white, the internal (± 20) tubular, with 5 teeth, yellow to orange. Fruits with a crown of white hairs, up to 10 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "87", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 32, :name => "secunda", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana secunda", :author => "Eriksen", :tropicos => "33500758", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 30 cm de alto, con olor fuerte y desagradable. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, espatuladas, hasta 10 cm de largo, gruesas, tienen tintes morados; márgenes enteros o presentan un fleco fino. Inflorescencia hasta de 15 cm de largo, está compuesta de subunidades más o menos péndulas, el eje principal está densamente cubierto de pelos blancos; las brácteas son color morado. Flores hasta 4 mm de largo, tubulares con 5 lóbulos cortos, color blanco o púrpura. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Cajas. Se la encuentra únicamente en áreas pedregosas en los sitios más altos como el área de Tres Cruces.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 30 cm tall, with a strong unpleasant smell. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, spathulate, to 10 cm long, thick, tinged with purple; margins entire or fringed. Inflorescence up to 15 cm is composed of pendent subunits, white hairs densely cover the principal axis, and the bracts purple. Flowers 4 mm long, tubular with 5 short lobes, white or purple. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Cajas. It is only found in rocky areas at highest elevations, like at the Tres Cruces area.", :old_id => "336", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 33, :name => "thuyoides", :genus => { :id => 42, :name => "Loricaria", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "191" }, :scientific => "Loricaria thuyoides", :author => "(Lam.) Sch. Bip", :tropicos => "2727069", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 1.5 m de alto, muy ramificados; las ramas con apariencia de ser planas. Hojas alternas, pequeñas y duras, hasta de 0.5 cm de largo, dobladas y tienen la forma de escamas sobrepuestas en dos hileras, las inferiores color café rojizo y las superiores brillantes, color verde oscuro con las puntas rojizas, con abundantes pelos sedosos y blancos en la parte interior. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas pequeñas hasta de 0.5 cm de diámetro. Flores tubulares y color amarillo pálido o crema. Frutos con una corona de pelos hasta de 5 mm de largo, color blanco-pajizo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en grupos entre los pajonales en las partes más altas del páramo.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1.5 m tall, profusely branched; branches appearing flattened. Leaves alternate, small, hard, up to 0.5 cm long, folded and scale-like, overlapping in two rows, the inferior reddish-brown and the superior glossy, dark green with a reddish apex, with dense silky white hairs. Inflorescences small heads, up to 0.5 cm in diameter. Flowers tubular, pale yellow or cream. Fruits with a crown of yellowish-white hairs, up to 5 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in groups in the highest parts of the grass páramo.", :old_id => "192", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 34, :name => "coriaceus", :genus => { :id => 68, :name => "Rubus", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "303" }, :scientific => "Rubus coriaceus", :author => "Poir.", :tropicos => "27800796", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Subarbustos rastreros muy espinosos; tallos y las venas (de la cara inferior) rojizos. Hojas alternas, hasta 7 cm de largo, ovadas, gruesas; márgenes aserrados. Flores solitarias, hasta de 30 mm de diámetro, color rosado fuerte; estambres y pistilos son numerosos. Fruto globoso, hasta de 15 mm de diámetro, está formado por un conjunto de muchos frutos pequeños de 3 mm cada uno, carnosos y color rojo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo arbustivo.", :description_en => "Trailing, prickly subshrubs; stems and veins (below) reddish. Leaves alternate, up to 7 cm long, ovate, leathery; margins serrate. Flowers solitary, up to 30 mm in diameter, dark pink, with numerous stamens and pistils. The fruit is globose, up to 15 mm in diameter; it is an aggregate of many small fruits each 3 mm long, fleshy and red. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is found in the shrubby páramo.", :old_id => "304", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 35, :name => "palustre", :genus => { :id => 71, :name => "Sisyrinchium", :family => { :id => 41, :name => "iridaceae", :old_id => "313" }, :old_id => "314" }, :scientific => "Sisyrinchium palustre", :author => "Diels", :tropicos => "16600587", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 25 cm de alto. Hojas todas basales, generalmente sobrepuestas en la base, hasta 15 cm de largo, alargadas y muy estrechas. Inflorescencias terminales, con 1 a pocas flores. Flores hasta de 8 mm de largo, tienen forma de copa, con 6 tépalos color amarillo brillante con rayas cafés por fuera. Fruto una cápsula globosa, seca, color negro brillante, que eventualmente se abre. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador y Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal y de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 25 cm tall. Leaves all basal, generally overlapping at base, up to 15 cm long, elongate and narrow. Inflorescences terminal, with 1 to few flowers. Flowers up to 8 mm long, cup-shaped, have 6 bright yellow tepals with brown stripes on the outer surface. Fruit a globose, dry, glossy black capsule, which eventually opens. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and Peru. In Cajas it is found in the grass and cushion páramos.", :old_id => "315", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }] }
{ :id => 36, :name => "dombeyi", :genus => { :id => 64, :name => "Potentilla", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "286" }, :scientific => "Potentilla dombeyi", :author => "Nestl.", :tropicos => "27800748", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas extendidas en el suelo, con las ramas rojizas y densamente cubiertas de pelos blancos sedosos o glandulares. Hojas alternas, compuestas, sus 3 hojuelas hasta 2 cm de largo; márgenes aserrados. Flores solitarias, hasta de 10 mm de diámetro, con 5 pétalos con forma acorazonada, color amarillo brillante a pálido; pistilos son numerosos. El fruto rodeado por el cáliz agrandado y como un conjunto de pequeños frutos secos, cada uno de hasta de 1 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador y Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra debajo de las macollas de pastos.", :description_en => "Sprawling herbs with reddish branches and densely covered with white, silky or glandular hairs. Leaves alternate and compound; its 3 leaflets up to 2 cm long; margins serrate. Flowers solitary, up to 10 mm in diameter, with 5 heart-shaped, bright to pale yellow petals, with numerous pistils. The fruit surrounded by the enlarged calyx is an aggregate of small dry fruits, each around 1 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and Peru. In Cajas it is found under bunch grasses.", :old_id => "287", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 37, :name => "rosmarinifolia", :genus => { :id => 11, :name => "Calceolaria", :family => { :id => 9, :name => "calceolariaceae", :old_id => "63" }, :old_id => "64" }, :scientific => "Calceolaria rosmarinifolia", :author => "Lam.", :tropicos => "29200665", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Subarbustos hasta de 1 m de alto, cubiertos de pelos amarillentos y pegajosos. Hojas opuestas, lanceoladas, hasta 12 cm de largo, color verde brillante en la superficie superior y verde amarillento y densamente lanosa en la inferior, el margen enrollado hacia abajo. Inflorescencia hasta de 10 cm, con varias flores. Flores irregulares, con forma globosa, hasta de 15 mm de largo, color amarillo brillante. \\n", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Subshrubs up to 1 m tall, covered with sticky, yellowish hairs. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 12 cm long, glossy green above, and yellowish green and densely wooly below; margins curled downwards. Inflorescences up to 10 cm long, with numerous flowers. The flowers have an irregular globose shape, up to 15 mm long, bright yellow. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "65", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 38, :name => "sessiliflora", :genus => { :id => 38, :name => "Hypochaeris", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "174" }, :scientific => "Hypochaeris sessiliflora", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "2702714", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas hasta 5 cm de alto. Hojas dispuestas en rosetas basales, hasta de 2.5 cm de largo, alargadas y estrechas. Inflorescencia en cabezuelas solitarias hasta 3 cm de diámetro. Flores numerosas, todas irregulares, tienen una lengüeta llamativa color amarillo con 5 pequeños dientes en la punta. Frutos con una corona de pelos plumosos, de 15 mm de largo, color blanco o rojizo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en todos los ambientes. Compare con la especie anterior la cual tiene flores de dos tipos.", :description_en => "Low herbs up to 5 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 2.5 cm long, elongate and narrow. Inflorescence of solitary heads, up to 3 cm in diameter. Flowers numerous; all irregular, yellow, strap-shaped and with 5 small teeth at the apex. Fruits with a crown of white or reddish plumose hairs up to 15 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in all environments. Compare with the previous species that has two types of flowers.", :old_id => "175", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 39, :name => "floribundum", :genus => { :id => 73, :name => "Vaccinium", :family => { :id => 13, :name => "ericaceae", :old_id => "91" }, :old_id => "320" }, :scientific => "Vaccinium floribundum", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "12300488", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos enanos, hasta 30 cm de alto. Hojas alternas, hasta 2 cm de largo, duras, lanceoladas, con el margen aserrado. Inflorescencia en racimos de 6 a 10 flores, hasta 1.5 cm de largo. Flores hasta de 8 mm de largo, la corola es cilíndrica con 4 ó 5 dientes, color blanco o rosado a rojizo. Los frutos son redondeados, hasta 8 mm de diámetro, carnosos, color negro-azul, a veces con una cubierta cerosa. \\n", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica a Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo arbustivo.", :description_en => "Dwarf shrubs, up to 30 cm tall. Leaves alternate, up to 2 cm long, stiff, lanceolate; margins serrate. Inflorescence a raceme of 6 to 10 flowers, up to 1.5 cm long. Flowers up to 8 mm long; corolla is cylindrical with 4 or 5 teeth, white or pink to reddish. Fruits round, up to 8 mm in diameter, fleshy, blue-black, sometimes with a waxy cover. \\n", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Peru. In Cajas it is found in the shrubby páramo.", :old_id => "321", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 40, :name => "phaeotricha", :genus => { :id => 51, :name => "Oxalis", :family => { :id => 32, :name => "oxalidaceae", :old_id => "233" }, :old_id => "234" }, :scientific => "Oxalis phaeotricha", :author => "Diels", :tropicos => "23700365", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas ascendentes hasta de 50 cm de alto, cubiertas de pelos largos, blancos y sedosos; tallos suculentos y presentan tintes color rojo. Hojas alternas, compuestas de 3 hojuelas hasta de 1 cm de largo, de forma acorazonada, sensibles al tacto y se viran hacia abajo. Inflorescencia con de 1 a 3 flores hasta 25 mm de diámetro, con 5 pétalos color amarillo intenso con las venas rojas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Ascending herbs up to 50 cm tall, covered with white, silky, long hairs; stems fleshy and tinged with red. Leaves alternate and compound; its 3 heart-shaped leaflets up to 1 cm long, sensitive to the touch and turn downwards. Inflorescence has 1 to 3 flowers up to 25 mm in diameter, with 5 deep yellow petals with red veins. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "235", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 41, :name => "vacciniodes", :genus => { :id => 55, :name => "Pentacalia", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "248" }, :scientific => "Pentacalia vacciniodes", :author => "(Kunth) Cuatrec.", :tropicos => "2733432", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 2 m de alto, bastante ramificados. Hojas alternas, hasta 4 cm de largo, gruesas, color verde-azulado, el ápice es puntiagudo, color rosado. Inflorescencia hasta 8 cabezuelas en las puntas de las ramas, cada una de 1.5 cm de diámetro. Flores (± 30) tubulares y con 5 dientes, hasta de 8 mm de largo, color amarillo. Frutos con una corona de pelos sedosos hasta 5 mm y son color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 2 m tall, profusely branched. Leaves alternate, up to 4 cm long, thick, bluish-green; apex is pointed and pink. Inflorescences terminal and have up to 8 heads, each 1.5 cm in diameter. The flowers (± 30) tubular, up to 8 mm long, with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruits with a crown of white silky hairs, up to 5 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "251", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 42, :name => "chionogeton", :genus => { :id => 70, :name => "Senecio", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "310" }, :scientific => "Senecio chionogeton", :author => "Wedd.", :tropicos => "2743430", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 50 cm de alto. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base y otras más pequeñas a lo largo del tallo, espatuladas, hasta 6 cm de largo; márgenes crenados. Inflorescencia en cabezuelas vistosas colgantes en el extremo del tallo, hay hasta de 15 por planta, hasta 2.5 cm de diámetro, color amarillo limón. Flores hasta 15 mm de largo, color amarillo limón, tubulares y con 5 dientes cortos. Frutos con una corona de pelos sedosos, de 12 mm de largo, color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 50 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette and some smaller ones along the stem, spathulate, up to 6 cm long; margins crenate. Inflorescence of showy, pendent heads at the end of the stems, around 15 per plant, up to 2.5 cm in diameter, lemon yellow. Flowers up to 15 mm long, lemon yellow, tubular with 5 short teeth. Fruits with a crown of white, silky hairs, up to 12 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "311", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 43, :name => "pumila", :genus => { :id => 76, :name => "Werneria", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "343" }, :scientific => "Werneria pumila", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "2709070", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas hasta de 5 cm de alto, que crecen solas o en grupos pequeños. Hojas forman una roseta que crece al ras del suelo, hasta 4 cm de largo, alargadas y estrechas. Inflorescencia una cabezuela ca. 2.5 cm de diámetro, las brácteas color café rojizo. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 20) irregulares, presentan una lengüeta llamativa hasta de 15 mm de largo, color amarillo, las internas (numerosas) tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. Frutos con una corona de pelos blancos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en las partes más altas del páramo. Compare con la siguiente especie la cual tiene flores color solo tipo.", :description_en => "Low herbs up to 5 cm tall, solitary or in small groups. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, at ground level, up to 4 cm long, elongate and narrow. Inflorescence a head, 2.5 cm in diameter, with reddish brown bracts. Flowers of two types: the external (± 20) irregular, strap-shaped, up to 15 mm long, yellow, the internal (numerous) tubular, with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruits with a crown of white hairs. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the highest areas of the páramo. Compare with the next species that has only one type of flowers.", :old_id => "346", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 44, :name => "lehmannii", :genus => { :id => 67, :name => "Ribes", :family => { :id => 39, :name => "grossulariaceae", :old_id => "299" }, :old_id => "300" }, :scientific => "Ribes lehmannii", :author => "Janc.", :tropicos => "29100299", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 1 m de alto, cubiertos de pelos. Hojas alternas, hasta 2.5 cm de largo; márgenes crenado-lobulados. Inflorescencia en forma de racimos colgantes. Flores hasta 10 mm de largo, tienen la base en forma de copa, tubulares y con 5 lóbulos triangulares, color rojo-rosado salmón con el interior amarillo. Frutos carnosos, color rojo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra entre pajonales, en bosques de Polylepis y con menos frecuencia en áreas rocosas.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1 m tall, covered with hairs. Leaves alternate, up to 2.5 cm long; margins crenate-lobed. Inflorescence a pendent raceme. Flowers up to 10 mm long, cup-shaped at base, tubular and with 5 triangular lobes, pink salmon to red and yellow within. Fruits fleshy and red. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo, in the Polylepis forests and less frequently in rocky areas.", :old_id => "301", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 45, :name => "graveolens", :genus => { :id => 56, :name => "Peperomia", :family => { :id => 34, :name => "piperaceae", :old_id => "253" }, :old_id => "254" }, :scientific => "Peperomia graveolens", :author => "Rauh & Barthlott", :tropicos => "25004174", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas epífitas o terrestres, suculentas, hasta 25 cm de alto; tallos tienen tintes café-rojizos. Hojas dispuestas en verticilos, ovadas, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, carnosas, a veces con el margen teñido de rojo. Inflorescencia con forma de espigas hasta 6 cm de largo, se encuentra en la parte terminal del tallo, carnosas, color verde claro cuando jóvenes y rosado cuando maduras. Flores diminutas. Frutos hasta 1 mm de largo, color negro. \\n", :distribution_es => " México a Bolivia y en las Antillas. En el Cajas se encuentra en los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Epiphytic or terrestrial herbs, fleshy, up to 25 cm tall; stems suffused with brown-red. Leaves arranged in groups, ovate, up to 1.5 cm long, fleshy, sometimes with a red margin. Inflorescence a fleshy spike, up to 6 cm long, terminal on the stem, light green when young, turning pinkish. Flowers minute. Fruits 1 mm long, black. \\n", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Bolivia and in the West Indies. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "255", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }] }
{ :id => 46, :name => "jamesonii", :genus => { :id => 12, :name => "Cardamine", :family => { :id => 10, :name => "brassicaceae", :old_id => "67" }, :old_id => "68" }, :scientific => "Cardamine jamesonii", :author => "Hook.", :tropicos => "4101583", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas delicadas hasta 40 cm de alto. Hojas alternas; las de la base divididas en 3 segmentos más o menos redondeados hasta 1.5 cm de largo, las del tallo divididas hasta en 9 segmentos alargados hasta 1 cm de largo, la superficie inferior color morado. Inflorescencia en la parte terminal del tallo, está dispuesta en racimos de pocas flores. Flores hasta 10 mm de largo, tienen 4 pétalos algo sobrepuestos, color rosado a púrpura. Frutos lineares, al abrirse las valvas se enrollan en espiral. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra dentro de los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Delicate herbs, to 40 cm tall. Leaves alternate; those at base divided into 3 more or less round segments, up to 1.5 cm long, and those on the stem divided into 9 elongate segments up to 1 cm long, purple below. Inflorescence terminal on the stem, a few-flowered raceme. Flowers up to 10 mm long, with 4 overlapping petals, pink to purple. Fruits linear, opening by valves curling into spirals. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "69", :provincias => [{ :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 47, :name => "jussieui", :genus => { :id => 15, :name => "Chuquiraga", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "79" }, :scientific => "Chuquiraga jussieui", :author => "J. F. Gmelin", :tropicos => "2728050", :color1 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 1.5 m de alto. Hojas alternas, hasta 1.2 cm de largo, duras y punzantes. Inflorescencia tiene cabezuelas vistosas hasta de 5 cm de largo, muy compactas, con brácteas punzantes color anaranjado. Flores (20–45) del­ga­das, color amarillo o anaranjado, de 20 mm de largo. El fruto con una corona blanca. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Colombia al S de Perú. En el Cajas crece en el páramo arbustivo. Flores visitadas por colibríes Oreotrochilus chimborazo.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1.5 m tall. Leaves alternate, up to 1.2 cm long, stiff, with a spiny tip. Inflorescence of showy, compact heads, up to 5 cm long; spine-tipped bracts orange. Flowers (20–45) slender, yellow or orange, 20 mm long. The fruit has a white crown. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia to S of Peru. In Cajas it is found in the shrubby páramo. Flowers visited by Oreotrochilus chimborazo hummingbirds.", :old_id => "80", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 48, :name => "roseum", :genus => { :id => 77, :name => "Xenophyllum", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "350" }, :scientific => "Xenophyllum roseum", :author => "(Hieron.) V. A. Funk", :tropicos => "50101826", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas forman almohadillas pequeñas en lugares húmedos. Hojas dispuestas en rosetas, muy estrechas y hasta 1 cm de largo. Inflorescencia en forma de cabezuela al nivel del suelo, ca. 2 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 13) irregulares y presentan una lengüeta vistosa de 10 mm de largo, color rosado fuerte, las internas (± 35) tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo oscuro. Frutos con una corona de pelos sedosos, de 8 mm de largo, color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del S Ecuador y prácticamente restringida al Cajas en el páramo de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Low herbs, forming small cushions in moist places. Leaves arranged in rosettes narrow, up to 1 cm long. Inflorescence a head at ground level, up to 2 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 13) irregular, showy, strap-shaped, 10 mm long, dark pink, the internal (± 35) tubular with 5 teeth, dark yellow. Fruits with a crown of silky white hairs, up to 8 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to S Ecuador and practically restricted to Cajas in the cushion páramo.", :old_id => "353", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 18, :name => "los ríos" }] }
{ :id => 49, :name => "pedicularioides", :genus => { :id => 5, :name => "Bartsia", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "31" }, :scientific => "Bartsia pedicularioides", :author => "(Kunth) Benth.", :tropicos => "29200512", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 30 cm de alto, recubiertas de pelos blancos; tallos rojizos. Hojas opuestas, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, con tintes color rosado; márgenes crenados, enrollados hacia abajo y a veces teñidos de morado. Flores tubulares y hasta 8 mm de largo, color rosado con blanco o violeta. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas es una especie común que se encuentra en varios ambientes.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 30 cm tall, covered with white hairs; stems reddish. Leaves opposite, up to 1.5 cm long, tinged with pink; crenate margins curled downwards and sometimes tinged with purple. Flowers tubular, up to 8 mm long, pink with white or violet. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is a common species found in various environments.", :old_id => "34", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 50, :name => "incurva", :genus => { :id => 54, :name => "Pedicularis", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "245" }, :scientific => "Pedicularis incurva", :author => "Benth.", :tropicos => "29206498", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierba hasta de 30 cm de alto. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base y a veces algunas alternas a lo largo del tallo, hasta 9 cm de largo, divididas hasta el nervio principal en segmentos crenados, color morado. Inflorescencia hasta de 20 cm de largo, tiene numerosas flores. Flores tubulares, recurvadas y hasta 2 cm de largo, color rosado fuerte, con uno de los pétalos formando un pico color más oscuro. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y S Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal y ocasionalmente en el de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 30 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, sometimes with a few alternate along the stem, up to 9 cm long, deeply divided towards the principal vein into crenate segments, purple. Inflorescence up to 20 cm long, with numerous flowers. Flowers tubular, curved, up to 2 cm long, dark pink, with one of the petals forming a darker beak. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and S Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo and occasionally in the cushion páramo.", :old_id => "246", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }] }
{ :id => 51, :name => "empetrifolium", :genus => { :id => 18, :name => "Disterigma", :family => { :id => 13, :name => "ericaceae", :old_id => "91" }, :old_id => "92" }, :scientific => "Disterigma empetrifolium", :author => "(Kunth) Drude", :tropicos => "12300816", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos enanos o plantas rastreras, bastante ramificadas, en general forman pequeñas almohadillas. Hojas alternas, hasta de 1 cm de largo, sobrepuestas, y son duras. Flores solitarias, hasta 10 mm de largo, tienen la forma de jarroncito con 4 dientes pequeños, carnosas, color rosado brillante o pálido a rojo. Fruto globoso, carnoso, 8– 12 mm de largo, color blanco-verdoso, translúcido. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. En el Cajas crece en el páramo de almohadillas y en el bosque de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Dwarf shrubs or trailing plants, profusely branched, forming small cushions. Leaves alternate, up to 1 cm long, overlapping, stiff. Flowers solitary, up to 10 mm long, vase-shaped with 4 small teeth, fleshy, bright or pale pink to reddish. Fruit globose, fleshy, up to 12 mm long, greenish-white, translucent. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. In Cajas it grows in the cushion páramo and in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "93", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 52, :name => "elliptica", :genus => { :id => 72, :name => "Stachys", :family => { :id => 12, :name => "lamiaceae", :old_id => "82" }, :old_id => "317" }, :scientific => "Stachys elliptica", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "17601420", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 8 cm de alto, se encuentran tendidas o erguidas, cubiertas con pelos blancos. Hojas opuestas, ovadas, hasta 1 cm de largo; márgenes crenados. Inflorescencias en grupos de 6 flores en la punta de los tallos. Flores hasta 1 cm de largo, irregulares, tubulares y con dos labios, color blanco con grandes manchas color rosado-lila o rosado oscuro. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra cerca o dentro de los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 8 cm long, sprawling or erect covered with white hairs. Leaves opposite, ovate, up to 1 cm long; margins crenate. Inflorescences groups of up to 6 flowers at the tips of the stems. Flowers up to 1 cm long, irregular, tubular and with two lips, white with large pinkish-lilac or dark pink spots. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found around or in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "318", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 53, :name => "multipartitum", :genus => { :id => 30, :name => "Geranium", :family => { :id => 20, :name => "geraniaceae", :old_id => "143" }, :old_id => "144" }, :scientific => "Geranium multipartitum", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "13900186", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas, hasta 5 cm de alto, formando alfombras pequeñas. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, hasta de 1.5 cm de largo, muy divididas en finos lóbulos; pecíolos largos y rojizos, con pelos blancos. Flores solitarias en el centro de la roseta, hasta 2 cm de diámetro, tienen 5 pétalos color lila muy pálido con los nervios morados. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal y en los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Low herbs, up to 5 cm tall, forming small mats. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 1.5 cm long, divided in fine lobes; petioles long and reddish, with white hairs. Flowers solitary and central in the rosette, up to 2 cm in diameter, with 5 very pale lilac petals with purple veins. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo and in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "145", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 54, :name => "nubigenum", :genus => { :id => 16, :name => "Clinopodium", :family => { :id => 12, :name => "lamiaceae", :old_id => "82" }, :old_id => "83" }, :scientific => "Clinopodium nubigenum", :author => "(Kunth) Kuntze", :tropicos => "17605046", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Arbustos rastreros, tendidos, forman alfombras, muy aromáticos; tallos color café rojizo. Hojas opuestas, ovadas, hasta 0.4 cm de largo, amontonadas en los tallos y tienen pelos esparcidos. Flores solitarias en las axilas de las hojas, irregulares, tubulares, hasta de 7 mm de largo, color lila muy claro con tintes oscuros. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Trailing shrubs, sprawling, forming mats, very aromatic, the stems reddish brown. Leaves opposite, ovate, up to 0.4 cm long, clustered along the stems, with scattered hairs. Flowers solitary in the axils of the leaves, irregular, tubular, up to 7 mm long, pale lilac with darker spots. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "84", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 55, :name => "cerastioides", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella cerastioides", :author => "(Kunth) Fabris", :tropicos => "13800126", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas hasta 5 cm de alto, a veces forman almohadillas pequeñas. Hojas, opuestas y amontonadas a lo largo del corto tallo, lanceoladas, hasta 8 mm de largo. Flores solitarias, erguidas, hasta 25 mm de largo, color lila o rara vez rosado, con las venas más oscuras. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Small herbs up to 5 cm tall, sometimes forming small cushions. Leaves opposite and clustered along the short stem, lanceolate, up to 8 mm long. Flowers solitary, erect, up to 25 mm long, lilac or rarely pink, with darker veins. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the cushion páramo.", :old_id => "133", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 56, :name => "rapunculoides", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella rapunculoides", :author => "(Willd. ex Schult.) J. S. Pringle", :tropicos => "/13800128", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 20 cm de alto, forman grupos pequeños. Hojas lanceoladas, opuestas, hasta 1 cm de largo, con tintes morados. Inflorescencia con forma de racimos, hasta 10 cm de largo, tiene 3 a 10 flores, el eje es color rojo-morado. Flores hasta 20 mm de largo, acampanadas y colgantes, color violeta pálido a oscuro o azulado, con las venas más oscuras. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Colombia-Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 20 cm tall, in small groups. Leaves lanceolate, opposite, up to 1 cm long, tinged with purple. Inflorescence a raceme, up to 10 cm long, with 3 to 10 flowers, the axis purple-red. Flowers up to 20 mm long, bell-shaped and pendent, pale to dark violet or bluish, with darker veins. 0\\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the cushion páramo.", :old_id => "141", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 57, :name => "vernicosum", :genus => { :id => 1, :name => "Arcytophyllum", :family => { :id => 1, :name => "rubiaceae", :old_id => "6" }, :old_id => "7" }, :scientific => "Arcytophyllum vernicosum", :author => "(Ruiz & Pav.) Standl.", :tropicos => "27909983", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 1 m de alto, densamente rami­ficados. Hojas opuestas, lanceo­ladas, hasta de 0.6 cm de largo, brillantes en la cara superior; márgenes engrosados en la cara inferior. Las inflorescencias tienen 1 a 3 flo­res. Flores hasta 8 mm de largo, blancas teñidas de lila, morado o rosado, tienen un tubo corto con 4 lóbulos trian­gulares, recubiertos de diminutos pelos blancos. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Ecuador al N Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1 m tall, densely branched. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 0.6 cm long, glossy above; margins thickened below. Inflorescences have 1 to 3 flowers. Flowers 8 mm long, white tinged with lilac, purple or pink; they have a short tube and 4 triangular lobes covered with minute white hairs. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Ecuador to N Peru. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "11", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }] }
{ :id => 58, :name => "pungens", :genus => { :id => 57, :name => "Perezia", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "257" }, :scientific => "Perezia pungens", :author => "(Humb. & Bonpl.) Less.", :tropicos => "2707362", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 25 cm de alto, con pelos glandulares en varias partes. Hojas de dos tipos: las basales dispuestas en una roseta, hasta 15 cm y tienen los márgenes menudamente espinosos, las del tallo hasta 4 cm de largo y tienen pelos glandulares. Inflorescencia en forma de cabezuela hasta de 3 cm de largo. Flores irregulares, presentan una lengüeta vistosa color azul-violeta o blanco-violeta, hasta 25 mm de largo \\n", :distribution_es => " S Colombia al N Argentina. En el Cajas esta especie se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal y en sitios rocosos.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 25 cm tall, covered with glandular hairs on various parts. Leaves of two types: the basal ones in a rosette, up to 15 cm long with finely spiny margins, and the ones on the stem, up to 4 cm long, with glandular hairs. Inflorescence a head, up to 3 cm long. Flowers irregular, strap-shaped, and showy, violet-blue or violet-white, up to 25 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia to N Argentina. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo and rocky areas.", :old_id => "258", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 59, :name => "cernua", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana cernua", :author => "Eriksen", :tropicos => "33500749", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Subarbustos hasta de 60 cm de alto, con olor desagradable, cubiertos de pelos diminutos, los tallos con tintes morados. Hojas opuestas, ovadas, hasta de 3 cm de largo, gruesas. Inflorescencias hasta 10 cm de largo, colgantes y dirigidas para un solo lado. Flores hasta 10 mm de largo, tubulares con 5 lóbulos cortos, color blanco o rosado con tintes lilas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Cajas. Crece dentro de los bosques de Polylepis que están hasta de las lagunas.", :description_en => "Subshrubs up to 60 cm tall, with an unpleasant smell, covered with minute hairs; stems tinged with purple. Leaves opposite, ovate, up to 3 cm long, leathery. Inflorescences up to 10 cm long, nodding to one side. Flowers up to 10 mm long, tubular with 5 short lobes, white or pink tinged with lilac. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Cajas. It is found in the Polylepis forests around the lakes.", :old_id => "325", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 60, :name => "glaucescens", :genus => { :id => 7, :name => "Bomarea", :family => { :id => 6, :name => "alstroemeriaceae", :old_id => "42" }, :old_id => "43" }, :scientific => "Bomarea glaucescens", :author => "(Kunth) Baker", :tropicos => "1200216", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas erguidas, hasta 50 cm de alto. Hojas alternas, hasta 3 cm de largo, lineares, duras, con los márgenes enrollados hacia abajo, con pelos color blanco en la superficie inferior, las venas diferenciadas son paralelas. Inflorescencia tiene hasta 6 flores colgantes en la punta del tallo. Flores tubulares con 3 sépalos color rosado intenso por fuera y amarillo por dentro; 3 pétalos amarillos tienen una raya rosada por fuera y con manchas moradas por dentro. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Erect herbs, to 50 cm tall. Leaves alternate, up to 3 cm long, linear, stiff, the margins curl downwards, with white hairs below, the veins noticeable and parallel. Inflorescence has up to 6 pendent flowers on the tip of the stem. Flowers tubular; 3 sepals deep pink outside and yellow inside and the 3 petals yellow with a pink line outside and with purple spots inside. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "44", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 61, :name => "microphyllus", :genus => { :id => 43, :name => "Lupinus", :family => { :id => 26, :name => "fabaceae", :old_id => "194" }, :old_id => "195" }, :scientific => "Lupinus microphyllus", :author => "Desr.", :tropicos => "13037051", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos tendidos, cubiertos de pelos largos color plateado. Hojas alternas, compuestas de 8 hojuelas dispuestas en forma palmeada, lineares, hasta 0.8 cm de largo. Inflorescencia en racimos con hasta 8 flores. Flores irregulares, hasta 10 mm de largo; pétalos tienen varias formas irregulares, color morado intenso con blanco. Fruto una legumbre comprimida, hasta de 15 mm de largo, que se abre por suturas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Sprawling shrubs, covered with long silvery hairs. Leaves alternate and compound; its 8 leaflets palmate, linear and up to 0.8 cm long. Inflorescence a raceme with up to 8 flowers. Flowers irregular, up to 10 mm long; petals, of various irregular shapes, deep purple with white. Fruit a compressed legume, up to 15 mm long, opening by the sutures. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "196", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 62, :name => "calyptrata", :genus => { :id => 59, :name => "Pinguicula", :family => { :id => 35, :name => "lentibulariaceae", :old_id => "263" }, :old_id => "264" }, :scientific => "Pinguicula calyptrata", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "18300017", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Plantas carnívoras, hasta 10 cm de alto. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, hasta 3.5 cm de largo, color verde pálido con los márgenes color café-rojizo y enrollados hacia arriba; recubiertas de glándulas pegajosas adaptadas para la captura y digestión de pequeños insectos. Flores tienen forma acampanada, hasta 15 mm de largo, color azul-violeta o violeta con blanco, con dos labios, el labio superior dividido en dos lóbulos y el inferior dividido en tres. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas esta especie se encuentra en áreas húmedas, debajo de las macollas de la paja.", :description_en => "Carnivorous plants, up to 10 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 3.5 cm long, pale green and the reddish-brown margins curl upwards, covered with sticky glands adapted to the capture and digestion of small insects. Flowers bell-shaped, up to 15 mm long, violet-blue to violet and white, with two lips, the upper lip divided into two lobes and the inferior into three. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is found in moist areas, under tussock grasses.", :old_id => "265", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 63, :name => "rigida", :genus => { :id => 60, :name => "Plantago", :family => { :id => 31, :name => "plantaginaceae", :old_id => "228" }, :old_id => "267" }, :scientific => "Plantago rigida", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "25200233", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas dispuestas en almohadillas, forman montículos grandes, hasta 1 m o más de diámetro. Hojas en una roseta al final de las ramas, hasta 3 cm de largo, duras y brillantes. Flores tubulares, hasta 15 mm de largo, con 4 dientes, color verdoso. Frutos ca. 2 mm de largo, y elevados sobre estructuras tubulares. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de almohadilla. Se ha observado a las llamas rascarse el hocico en estas almohadillas duras.", :description_en => "Cushion-forming plants that form compact mounds up to 1 m or more in diameter. Leaves arranged in rosettes at the tip of the branches, up to 3 cm long, hard and glossy. Flowers greenish, up to 15 mm long, tubular with 4 teeth. Fruits up to 2 mm long, and raised on tubular structures. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the cushion páramo. Lamas have been observed scratching their heads against these hard cushions.", :old_id => "270", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 64, :name => "fissifolia", :genus => { :id => 13, :name => "Castilleja", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "72" }, :scientific => "Castilleja fissifolia", :author => "N. Holmgren", :tropicos => "29202221", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 30 cm de alto, el follaje está a menudo teñido de morado. Hojas alternas, hasta 2 cm de largo, divididas en segmentos. Inflorescencia en forma de racimos hasta de 10 cm de largo, tiene hojas con apariencia de pétalos (brácteas) color rojo brillante que sostienen a cada flor. Flores tubulares, algo recurvadas, hasta 20 mm de largo, color verde claro, con pelos diminutos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del S Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en varios ambientes. Las partes rojas más vistosas de la planta son las brácteas y no las flores.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 30 cm long; foliage is often tinged with purple. Leaves alternate, up to 2 cm long, divided in segments. Inflorescences racemes up to 10 cm long; they have bright red petal-like leaves (bracts) subtending each flower. Flowers tubular, slightly curved, up to 20 mm long, light green, with minute hairs. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to S Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in various environments. The showiest red parts of the plant bracts and not flowers.", :old_id => "73", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 65, :name => "clava-herculis", :genus => { :id => 65, :name => "Puya", :family => { :id => 37, :name => "bromeliaceae", :old_id => "289" }, :old_id => "290" }, :scientific => "Puya clava-herculis", :author => "Mez & Sodiro", :tropicos => "4302804", :color1 => { :id => 9, :name => "blue", :old_id => "127" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas gigantes hasta 1 m de diámetro. Hojas numerosas y dispuestas en una roseta en la base, alargadas, gruesas, con tintes color café rojizo, con grandes espinos negros en los bordes. Inflorescencia alta, erguida, de más de 1 m, densamente cubierta de pelos lanosos blancos. Flores hasta 2 cm de largo, color azul verdoso claro. Frutos cápsulas globosas, secas y que eventualmente se abren. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en pajonales. Colibríes visitan sus flores y el oso de anteojos se alimenta de los cogollos.", :description_en => "Giant herbs up to 1 m in diameter. The numerous leaves arranged in a basal rosette, elongate, leathery, tinged with reddish brown, the margins with large black spines. Inflorescence tall, erect, over 1 m, densely covered with white wooly hairs. Flowers up to 2 cm long, light greenish-blue. Fruits globose dry capsules, which eventually open. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo. Hummingbirds visit the flowers; spectacled bear eats the base of the inflorescence and leaves.", :old_id => "291", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 66, :name => "laticrenata", :genus => { :id => 5, :name => "Bartsia", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "31" }, :scientific => "Bartsia laticrenata", :author => "Benth.", :tropicos => "29200505", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 50 cm de alto, con una base leñosa, cubiertas de pelos glandulares, pegajosos. Hojas opuestas, lanceoladas, hasta 2 cm de largo, con el margen crenado y enrollado hacia abajo, a menudo color rojizo morado, sobre todo en la parte superior. Flores en la parte superior de los tallos, hasta 10 mm de largo, el cáliz es color morado y la corola tubular es color amarillo-verdoso. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 50 cm long, with a woody base, covered with glandular sticky hairs. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 2 cm long; margins crenate and curled downwards, often tinged with reddish purple especially in the upper parts. Flowers in the upper portions of the stems, up to 10 mm long; calyx is purple and the tubular corolla is greenish-yellow. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "32", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 67, :name => "californicus", :genus => { :id => 69, :name => "Schoenoplectus", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" }, :old_id => "307" }, :scientific => "Schoenoplectus californicus", :author => "Boeck", :tropicos => "9904887", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas semi-acuáticas hasta 4 m de alto; tallos rígidos, esponjosos por dentro y triangulares transversalmente. Hojas muy delgadas en la base de los tallos. Inflorescencias en la punta de los tallos y son cabezuelas de espigas que hasta 5 cm de largo; las flores son poco llamativas, color café. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra principalmente en la laguna Totoras.", :description_en => "Semi-aquatic herbs up to 4 m tall; stems stiff, spongy within and triangular transversally. Leaves very thin and at the base of the stems. Inflorescences at the tip of the stems, heads formed by spikes, up to 5 cm long; flowers inconspicuous, brown. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia. In Cajas it is principally found in lake Totoras.", :old_id => "308", :provincias => [], :forma_vida2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" } }
{ :id => 68, :name => "bogotense", :genus => { :id => 23, :name => "Equisetum", :family => { :id => 16, :name => "equisetaceae", :old_id => "109" }, :old_id => "110" }, :scientific => "Equisetum bogotense", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "26605510", :color1 => nil, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas hasta de 30 cm de alto; tallos bastante delgados, generalmente huecos en el centro. Hojas diminutas, reducidas a escamas color café, dispuestas en anillos espaciados a lo largo del tallo. Las estructuras reproductivas (esporangios) se encuentran en un tipo de espigas pequeñas (estróbilos) que en las puntas de las ramas, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, color café os­curo; las esporas verdes. n", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra a los lados de la carretera.", :description_en => "Plants up to 30 cm tall; stems slender and generally hollow. Leaves minute, reduced to brown scales, arranged in rings spaced along the stem. The reproductive structures (sporangia) found in small spike-like structures (strobili) at the apex of the branches; to 1.5 cm long, dark brown with green spores. n", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found along roads.", :old_id => "111", :provincias => [{ :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 19, :name => "galapagos" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 69, :name => "obtusifolia", :genus => { :id => 34, :name => "Hesperomeles", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "159" }, :scientific => "Hesperomeles obtusifolia", :author => "(Pers.) Lindl", :tropicos => "27801590", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 2 m de alto, con las puntas de las ramas generalmente terminando en una espina. Hojas alter­nas, lanceola­das, hasta de 3 cm de largo, rígidas; margen aserrado. Inflorescencias en hasta de 4 cm de largo, con 1 a varias flores. Flores de 10 mm de largo; pétalos blan­cos con tintes rosados a rojos. Fruto redondeado, carnoso, de 10 mm de largo, color rojo a negro. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra hasta de los bosques de Polylepis y en el pajonal.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 2 m tall; branches often terminate in a spine. Leaves alternate, lanceolate, up to 3 cm long, stiff; margin serrate. Inflorescences up to 4 cm tall, with 1 to various flowers. Flowers 10 mm long; petals white tinged with pink or red. Fruits round, fleshy, 10 mm long, and red turning black. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found around the Polylepis forests and in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "160", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 70, :name => "pygmea", :genus => { :id => 75, :name => "Viola", :family => { :id => 43, :name => "violaceae", :old_id => "338" }, :old_id => "339" }, :scientific => "Viola pygmea", :author => "Poir.", :tropicos => "33800244", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 2 cm de alto, forman almohadillas. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, lanceoladas, hasta de 1.5 cm de largo, gruesas; margen es entero. Flores pequeñas, de 10 mm de diámetro, solitarias entre las hojas, color blanco con una mancha morada en el centro; pétalo ventral es más grande, con una espuela, blanca con rayas moradas y el centro amarillo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Cushion-forming herbs, up to 2 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, lanceolate, up to 1.5 cm long, thick; margin is entire. Flowers small, 10 mm in diameter, solitary among the leaves, white with a purple central spot; ventral petal is larger, clawed, and white with purple stripes and yellow center. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "340", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 71, :name => "plantaginea", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana plantaginea", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "33500246", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas grandes, hasta de 1.5 m, con un olor fuerte y desagradable. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta basal, lanceoladas, hasta de 45 cm de largo, gruesas y brillantes en la cara superior. Inflorescencia alta, hasta de 80 cm, con ramificaciones erguidas, con numerosas flores. Flores hasta 5 mm de largo, tubulares con 5 lóbulos cortos, color blanco con tintes morados. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. En el Cajas se la encuentra en grupos dentro de los bosques de Polylepis donde se la ubica fácilmente por su gran tamaño y su olor fuerte", :description_en => "Large herbs, up to 1.5 m tall, with a strong unpleasant smell. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, lanceolate, up to 45 cm long, thick and glossy above. Inflorescence tall, up to 80 cm, with erect branches, with numerous flowers. Flowers 5 mm long, tubular with 5 short lobes, white tinged with purple. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. In Cajas it is found in groups inside the Polylepis forests where it can be easily located due to its size and strong smell.", :old_id => "331", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 72, :name => "vitreola", :genus => { :id => 44, :name => "Lysipomia", :family => { :id => 27, :name => "campanulaceae", :old_id => "198" }, :old_id => "199" }, :scientific => "Lysipomia vitreola", :author => "McVaugh", :tropicos => "5502024", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas que a veces forman almohadillas pequeñas. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta basaal, lanceoladas, hasta de 1.5 cm de largo, gruesas, brillantes y punti­agudas. Flores solitarias, hasta de 15 mm de largo, blancas con puntos morados hacia el centro, tienen dos labios, el un labio tiene 2 lóbulos triangulares y el otro 3; estambres fusionados y forman una columna central. \\n", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Cajas. Se encuentra en los páramos de pajonal y de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Low herbs, sometimes forming small cushions. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, lanceolate, up to 1.5 cm long, leathery, glossy and acute at apex. Flowers solitary, up to 15 mm long, white with purple dots towards the center, with 2 lips; one of the lips has 2 triangular lobes and the other 3; stamens fused and form a central column. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Cajas where it is found in the grass or cushion páramo.", :old_id => "200", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 73, :name => "genistelloides", :genus => { :id => 4, :name => "Baccharis", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "24" }, :scientific => "Baccharis genistelloides", :author => "(Lam.) Pers.", :tropicos => "2722899", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas rígidas hasta 0.5 m de alto, con los tallos marcadamente aplanados, triangulares y con segmentos alados. No tienen hojas. Inflorescencias en capítulos solitarios o en grupos, ubicados a lo largo de los tallos, hasta 0.7 cm de diámetro, las brácteas con tonos rosados. Flores numerosas, tubulares, hasta de 5 mm de largo, blancas. Frutos con una corona de pelos blancos, ca. 6 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en todos los ambientes. Llama la atención sus tallos aplanados con aspecto color cactus.", :description_en => "Stiff herbs up to 0.5 m tall; stems strongly flattened, triangular and with winged segments. Leaves absent. Inflorescences of solitary or clustered heads along the stem, up to 0.7 cm in diameter, the bracts tinged with pink. Flowers numerous, tubular, up to 5 mm long, white. Fruits with a crown of white hairs, up to 6 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in all environments. Noticeable its flat stems with the overall aspect of a cactus.", :old_id => "27", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 74, :name => "tenuicaule", :genus => { :id => 22, :name => "Epidendrum", :family => { :id => 15, :name => "orchidaceae", :old_id => "105" }, :old_id => "106" }, :scientific => "Epidendrum tenuicaule", :author => "F. Lehm. & Kraenzl.", :tropicos => "23509220", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas epífitas o terrestres, a veces crecen sobre rocas, hasta 30 cm de alto; las raíces son color blanco. Hojas alternas, lanceoladas, hasta 3 cm de largo. Inflorescencia en racimos colgantes, hasta de 4 cm de largo, hasta con 20 flores. Flores hasta 10 mm y son color amarillo verdoso, el pétalo central (labelo), que es más grande, tiene 3 lóbulos. Fruto una cápsula globosa, seca, de 2 cm de largo, color verde, con costillas gruesas y miles de semillas diminutas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas es común en varios ambientes.", :description_en => "Epiphytic or terrestrial plants, sometimes growing on rocks, up to 30 cm tall; roots white. Leaves alternate, lanceolate, up to 3 cm long. Inflorescences pendent racemes, up to 4 cm long, with up to 20 flowers. Flowers greenish yellow, up to 10 mm long; central petal (labellum) is larger and has 3 lobes. Fruit a globose dry capsule, 2 cm long, green, ribbed and with thousands of minute seeds. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is common in various environments.", :old_id => "107", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, nil] }
{ :id => 75, :name => "hispidula", :genus => { :id => 41, :name => "Lachemilla", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "186" }, :scientific => "Lachemilla hispidula", :author => "(L. M. Perry) Rothm.", :tropicos => "27806115", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas gruesas hasta 25 cm de alto; tallos rojizos, varios surgen color mismo punto. Hojas reducidas, hasta 0.7 cm de largo, muy estrechas, pueden haber hasta 10 unidas por sus bases y reunidas en anillos a lo largo del tallo, vellosas. Inflorescencia globosa, con varias flores. Flores diminutas, hasta 2.5 mm de largo, color rosado con blanco-verdoso. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Coarse herbs, up to 25 cm tall; stems reddish and emerge from the same point. Leaves reduced, up to 0.7 cm long, narrow, up to 10 fused at their base and clustered in rings along the stem, villous. Inflorescence globose, with various flowers. Flowers minute, up to 2.5 mm long, pink with greenish-white. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the cushion páramo.", :old_id => "187", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 76, :name => "hyssopofila", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella hyssopofila", :author => "(Kunth) Fabris", :tropicos => "13801759", :color1 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 40 cm de alto, con varios tallos. Hojas opuestas, hasta 2 cm de largo, lineares. Inflorescencia en grupos hasta de 5 flores a lo largo de los tallos. Flores hasta 15 mm de largo, tienen forma globosa-elíptica, con los pétalos sobrepuestos y escasamente abiertos, color amarillo pálido con tintes rojos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del S Ecuador. En el Cajas se la encuentra entre las macollas del pajonal. Se diferencia de la especie anterior por ser más alta, con flores más pequeñas y en mayor número.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 40 cm tall, with various stems. Leaves opposite, up to 2 cm long, linear. Inflorescence has groups of up to 5 flowers along the stem. Flowers up to 15 mm long, globose-elliptic with the petals overlapping and barely open, pale yellow tinged with red. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to S Ecuador. In Cajas it is the found among the bunch grass. It differs from the previous species by its taller size, with smaller but numerous flowers.", :old_id => "137", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 77, :name => "chamaedrifolia", :genus => { :id => 50, :name => "Ourisia", :family => { :id => 31, :name => "plantaginaceae", :old_id => "228" }, :old_id => "229" }, :scientific => "Ourisia chamaedrifolia", :author => "Benth.", :tropicos => "29202277", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, reclinadas, hasta 10 cm de alto, generalmente en grupos. Hojas opuestas, hasta 1 cm de largo; márgenes crenados. Flores solitarias, colgantes, con forma de tubo acampanado, hasta 25 mm de largo, color rosado oscuro a rosado-rojizo. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Colombia a Bolivia. En el Cajas se encuentra en áreas rocosas principalmente en las partes más altas del páramo.", :description_en => "Small, reclining herbs, up to 10 cm tall, generally in groups. Leaves opposite, up to 1 cm long; margins crenate. Flowers solitary, pendent, with a bell-tubular shape, up to 25 mm long, dark pink to pinkish-red. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia to Bolivia. In Cajas it is found in rocky areas mainly in the highest parts of the páramo.", :old_id => "230", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 78, :name => "humile", :genus => { :id => 24, :name => "Eryngium", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" }, :old_id => "113" }, :scientific => "Eryngium humile", :author => "Cav.", :tropicos => "1701117", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 20 cm de alto. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, gruesas, brillantes, hasta 15 cm de largo; márgenes espinoso-aserrado, el nervio principal color crema en la cara superior. Inflorescencia hemisférica, hasta de 1.5 cm de diámetro, está conformada por brácteas color blanco o plateado, con la punta espinosa. Flores diminutas, hasta 3 mm de largo, color azul-lila. Frutos de 2 mm de largo, color negro-morado. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. En el Cajas es común en todos los ambientes.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 20 cm tall. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, thick, glossy, up to 15 cm long; margins spiny-serrate, the main vein cream above. Inflorescence globose, up to 1.5 cm in diameter, with white to silvery, spine-tipped bracts. Flowers minute, up to 3 mm long, lilac-blue. Fruits 2 mm long, purple-black. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. In Cajas it is common in various environments.", :old_id => "114", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 79, :name => "orbiculata", :genus => { :id => 41, :name => "Lachemilla", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "186" }, :scientific => "Lachemilla orbiculata", :author => "(Ruiz & Pav.) Rydb.", :tropicos => "27801673", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas rastreras, forman alfombras al nivel del suelo. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, hasta 3.5 cm de largo, tienen forma orbicular-arriñonada, la superficie con vello blanco; márgenes tienen de 9 a 11 lóbulos, dentados; pecíolo es alargado y rojizo. Inflorescencia poco llamativa, mide 3 cm de largo. Flores hasta 4 mm de largo, color verde-amarillento. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. Planta muy común en el Cajas, especialmente en áreas alteradas y de pastoreo.", :description_en => "Trailing herbs, forming mats at ground level. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, up to 3.5 cm long, orbicular-kidney shaped, white-villous; margins dentate, with 9 to 11 lobes; petiole is elongate and reddish. Inflorescence inconspicuous, up to 3 cm long. Flowers up to 4 mm long and yellowish-green. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. It is a common species in Cajas, especially in disturbed and grazing areas.", :old_id => "189", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 80, :name => "villosa", :genus => { :id => 78, :name => "Chusquea", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" }, :old_id => "217" }, :scientific => "Chusquea villosa", :author => "(L.G. Clark) L.G. Clark", :tropicos => "100352741", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Bambúes enanos hasta 1 m de alto, crecen en grupos densos; tallos huecos y presentan tintes morados. Hojas alargadas, hasta 20 cm de largo, duras y recubiertas de pelos blancos, largos y sedosos; márgenes sumamente cortantes. Inflorescencias entre las hojas o son más altas, color café claro; eje es velloso y con numerosas espiguillas cada una con varios flores (flósculos). Flores poco llamativas y duras, hasta 4 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Endémica del S del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en los pajonales en áreas húmedas o en bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Dwarf bamboos up to 1 m tall, growing in dense groups; stems hollow and tinged with purple. Leaves elongate, up to 20 cm long, hard and covered with long silky white hairs; edges quite sharp. Inflorescences among the leaves or taller, light brown; axis is villous and has numerous spikelets each with various flowers (florets). Flowers inconspicuous, stiff, up to 4 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to S Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo and moist areas in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "218", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 81, :name => "floccosum", :genus => { :id => 14, :name => "Cerastium", :family => { :id => 11, :name => "caryophyllaceae", :old_id => "75" }, :old_id => "76" }, :scientific => "Cerastium floccosum", :author => "Benth.", :tropicos => "6300620", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 15 cm de alto, bastante ramificadas, cubiertas de pelos glandu­la­res pegajosos. Hojas opuestas, divididas en 3 en la punta, hasta de 1.5 cm de largo, sobrepuestas. Inflorescencia consiste de 1 o 2 flores al final de los tallos. Flores hasta 15 mm de diámetro; pétalos 5. hendidos en el ápice, color blanco; estambres amarillos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en la zona de Tres Cruces, en el páramo de almohadillas y entre rocas.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 15 cm tall, profusely branched, covered with glandular, sticky hairs. Leaves opposite, divided in 3 at the apex, up to 1.5 cm long, overlapping. Inflorescence of 1 or 2 flowers at the end of the branches. Flowers up to 15 mm in diameter; 5 white petals cleft at apex; stamens yellow. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the Tres Cruces area, in the cushion páramo and among rocks.", :old_id => "77", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 82, :name => "reticulata", :genus => { :id => 62, :name => "Polylepis", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "276" }, :scientific => "Polylepis reticulata", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "27800836", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles hasta 12 m de alto; troncos son retorcidos y tienen la corteza color café-anaranjado, que se desprende en láminas delgadas como papel. Hojas y las flores a menudo cubiertas de pelos. Hojas alternas y crecen amontonadas en las puntas de las ramas, conformadas por 3 hojuelas hasta 2.5 cm de largo, tienen denso vello en la cara inferior, la cara superior lisa. Inflorescencias racimos colgantes poco llamativos, hasta de 8 cm de largo. Flores hasta de 5 mm y son color verdoso. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. En el Cajas forman bosquetes remanentes en el páramo. Posiblemente estos bosques cubrían áreas más extensas en el pasado, pero debido al impacto de las quemas y el pastoreo en la actualidad se encuentran reducidas.", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees up to 12 m tall; trunks twisted and have a flaky orange-brown bark that peels off like paper. Leaves and flowers often covered with hairs. Leaves alternate but clustered at the tips of the branches, compound; its 3 leaflets up to 2.5 cm long, with a dense cover of villous hairs below, smooth above. Inflorescences inconspicuous pendent racemes, to 8 cm long. Flowers about 5 mm long and greenish. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas its forms remnant forests in the páramo. It is possible that these forests covered larger areas in the past, but has been reduced by the impacts of burning and grazing.", :old_id => "277", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 83, :name => "bonplandianum", :genus => { :id => 52, :name => "Paspalum", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" }, :old_id => "237" }, :scientific => "Paspalum bonplandianum", :author => "Flüggé", :tropicos => "25513101", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas en macollas laxas, a veces rastreras, hasta 15 cm de alto, color verde azulado y densamente cubiertas de pelos blancos. Hojas lanceoladas y tienen una vaina en la base; lámina es estrecha y hasta de 8 cm de largo. Las inflorescencias crecen sobre tallos rojizos, racimos compuestos, laxos y contienen hasta 9 espiguillas; las flores son muy reducidas, color verde amarillento. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador y Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Herbs in lax tufts, sometimes trailing, up to 15 cm long, bluish green and densely covered with white hairs. Leaves lanceolate, and have a sheath at the base; blade is narrow, up to 8 cm long. Inflorescences grow on reddish stems, lax compound racemes with up to 9 spikelets; yellowish green flowers much reduced. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and Peru. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "238", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 84, :name => "microphylla", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana microphylla", :author => "Kunth", :tropicos => "33500229", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos bajos, erguidos o algo recostados, hasta 60 cm de alto. Hojas opuestas, ovadas o elípticas, gruesas, hasta de 1 cm de largo. Inflorescencias en las puntas de las ramas, erguidas y hasta 5 cm de largo, con muchas flores. Flores hasta 3 mm de largo, tubulares, con 5 lóbulos cortos, color blanco o rosado, con tintes lilas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. Común en el Cajas en varios ambientes. Es una es­pecie variable que cuando crece a mayor altura presenta las hojas y las flores amon­tonadas, mientras que dentro del bosque son más laxos.", :description_en => "Low shrubs, erect or reclining, up to 60 cm tall. Leaves opposite, ovate or elliptic, leathery, up to 1 cm long. Inflorescences terminal, erect, and up to 5 cm long, many-flowered. Flowers 3 mm long, tubular, with 5 short lobes, white or pink, tinged with lilac. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. In Cajas it is common in various environments. A variable species presenting clustered leaves and flowers at higher elevations and laxer when growing inside the forest.", :old_id => "329", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 85, :name => "henricii", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana henricii", :author => "(Graebn.) Eriksen", :tropicos => "33500711", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas sin tallo, con apariencia de coliflor, hasta 7 cm de diámetro. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta en la base, tienen la forma arriñonada, hasta 3 cm de largo, carnosas, arrugadas, color verde-oliva violeta en la cara superior, moradas en la inferior; márgenes curvados hacia abajo. Inflorescencias con numerosas flores. Flores hasta 5 mm de largo, tubulares con 5 lóbulos cortos, color blanco. \\n", :distribution_es => " S Ecuador y S de Perú. En nuestro país se encuentra sólo en el Cajas donde crece exclusivamente en áreas rocosas por sobre los 4200 m, en el sendero a Cerro Ama­rillo. Puede fácilmente pasar desapercibida porque se confunde con el color de las rocas.", :description_en => "Stemless herbs, shaped like a cauliflower, up to 7 cm in diameter. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette, kidney-shaped, up to 3 cm long, fleshy, wrinkled, olive green to violet above, purple below; margins curled downwards. Inflorescences with numerous flowers. Flowers 5 mm long, white, tubular with 5 short lobes. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Ecuador and S of Peru. In Ecuador only found in Cajas in rocky areas above 4200 m on the trail to Cerro Amarillo. It is easily overlooked as it blends well with the color of the rocks.", :old_id => "327", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 86, :name => "humile", :genus => { :id => 77, :name => "Xenophyllum", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "350" }, :scientific => "Xenophyllum humile", :author => "(Kunth). V.A. Funk", :tropicos => "50101822", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Plantas en almohadillas muy compactas hasta 1 m de diámetro. Hojas dispuestas en espiral, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, muy estrechas y gruesas. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas que crecen a nivel del suelo, hasta de 1 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 12) irregulares y presentan una lengüeta blanca, las internas (± 25) cortas, tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. Frutos con una corona de pelos sedosos, blancos. \\n", :distribution_es => " C Colombia al N Perú. En el Cajas se encuentran en el páramo de almohadillas, en áreas húmedas en los pajonales y raras veces sobre rocas.", :description_en => "Cushion-forming plants, compact, up to 1 m in diameter. Leaves spirally arranged, up to 1.5 cm long, very narrow and leathery. Inflorescence heads grow at ground level, up to 1 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 12) irregular and strap-shaped, white, the internal (± 25) short, and tubular, with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruits with a crown of silky, white hairs. \\n", :distribution_en => " C Colombia to N Peru. In Cajas it is found in the cushion páramo, in moist areas in the grass páramo, and sometimes on rocks.", :old_id => "351", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 87, :name => "peruvianus", :genus => { :id => 66, :name => "Ranunculus", :family => { :id => 38, :name => "ranunculaceae", :old_id => "293" }, :old_id => "294" }, :scientific => "Ranunculus peruvianus", :author => "Pers.", :tropicos => "27101034", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas terrestres, hasta de 10 cm de alto, con pelos sedosos. Hojas de dos tipos: las de la base hasta 1 cm de largo, tienen forma arriñonada con el margen crenado y pecíolos largos y delgados; las otras son alternas en el tallo y profundamente divididas. Flores solitarias y terminales, hasta 15 mm de diámetro, con 5 pétalos espatulados, color amarillo limón; pistilos son numerosos y amarillos. El fruto como un conjunto de pequeños frutos secos ca. 1 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador y Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en áreas húmedas del páramo de almohadillas.", :description_en => "Terrestrial herbs, up to 10 cm tall, with silky hairs. Leaves of two types: the basal up to 1 cm long, kidney-shaped, with crenate margins and have long slender petioles; others deeply divided and alternate along the stem. Flowers solitary and terminal, up to 15 mm in diameter, with 5 lemon yellow spathulate petals and numerous yellow pistils. Fruit an aggregate of small dry fruits each about 1 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and Peru. In Cajas it is found in the moist cushion páramo.", :old_id => "297", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 88, :name => "cuicochensis", :genus => { :id => 32, :name => "Gynoxys", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "151" }, :scientific => "Gynoxys cuicochensis", :author => "Cuatrec.", :tropicos => "2743344", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles pequeños hasta 5 m de alto, tienen una densa capa de pelos color blanco grisáceo. Hojas opuestas, lanceoladas y hasta 10 cm de largo. Inflorescencias en varias cabezuelas, cada una hasta de 1.5 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 8) irregulares, presentan una lengüeta llamativa hasta de 13 mm de largo, color amarillo brillantes, las internas (± 18) tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. Frutos con una corona de pelos ásperos, hasta de 15 mm de largo, blanco-pajizos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en áreas boscosas.", :description_en => "Shrubs or small trees up to 5 m tall, covered with a dense layer of grayish white hairs. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 10 cm long. Inflorescences several heads, each to 1.5 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external (± 8) irregular, strap-shaped, up to 13 mm long, bright yellow; internal (± 18) tubular with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruits with a crown of coarse, yellowish-white hairs, up to 15 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in forested areas.", :old_id => "152", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 89, :name => "miniphylla", :genus => { :id => 32, :name => "Gynoxys", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "151" }, :scientific => "Gynoxys miniphylla", :author => "Cuatrec.", :tropicos => "2733857", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 2 m de alto, con una densa capa de pelos color blanco. Hojas opuestas, hasta de 1.5 cm de largo, ovadas. Inflorescencia compuesta de varias cabezuelas, cada una hasta de 0.5 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas, cuando presentes (± 5), irregulares y tienen una lengüeta corta de 4 mm de largo, color amarillo, las internas (± 15) tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. Frutos con una corona de pelos ásperos hasta 5 mm de largo, color blanco-pajizo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el pajonal", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 2 m tall, covered with a dense layer of grayish white hairs. Leaves opposite, ovate, up to 1.5 cm long. Inflorescence has several heads, each to 0.5 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: the external, when present, (± 5) irregular, strap-shaped, 4 mm long, yellow, the internal (± 15) tubular and with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruits with a crown of coarse yellowish white hairs up to 5 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "154", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }] }
{ :id => 90, :name => "frigidum", :genus => { :id => 35, :name => "Hieracium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "163" }, :scientific => "Hieracium frigidum", :author => "Wedd.", :tropicos => "2737073", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 60 cm de alto, cubiertas de pelos largos color blanco. Hojas de la base son espatuladas, hasta 12 cm de largo. Inflorescencia en cabezuelas al final de los tallos, colgantes, hasta 3 cm de diámetro; las brácteas son color verde oscuro. Flores irregulares y con una lengüeta hasta de 25 mm de largo, con 5 dientes pequeños, color amarillo limón. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. En el Cajas se las encuentra en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 60 cm tall, covered with long white hairs. Basal leaves spathulate, up to 12 cm long. Inflorescence of heads at the end of the stems, pendent, up to 3 cm in diameter; bracts dark green. Flowers irregular and strap-shaped, up to 25 mm long, with 5 small teeth, lemon yellow. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. In Cajas it is the found in the grass páramo.", :old_id => "164", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 91, :name => "hirculus", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella hirculus", :author => "(Griseb.) Fabris", :tropicos => "13801755", :color1 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas, hasta de 10 cm de alto, crecen solitarias o en grupos. Hojas opuestas, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, lineares y amontonadas. Flores, hasta 20 mm de largo, tienen forma de globo, con los pétalos sobrepuestos y escasamente abiertos, color amarillo-anaranjado brillante con el margen expuesto rojo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es una especie endémica del Cajas, común en varios ambientes. Se diferencia de la siguiente especie por tener el porte más bajo y las flores son más grandes pero en menor número, y de colores más brillantes.", :description_en => "Low herbs, up to 10 cm tall, solitary or in groups. Leaves opposite, up to 1.5 cm long, linear and clustered. Flowers up to 20 mm long, with a globose shape, the petals overlapping and barely open, bright orange-yellow with the exposed margin red. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Cajas, common in various environments. It differs from the next species by being smaller with brighter, larger, but fewer flowers.", :old_id => "135", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }] }
{ :id => 92, :name => "coriacardia", :genus => { :id => 61, :name => "Pleurothallis", :family => { :id => 15, :name => "orchidaceae", :old_id => "105" }, :old_id => "272" }, :scientific => "Pleurothallis coriacardia", :author => "Rchb. f.", :tropicos => "23508782", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas terrestres, hasta 20 cm de alto, crecen sobre rocas, se las ve en grupos densos. Hojas hasta 10 cm de largo, solitarias, colgantes en el ápice color tallo largo y delgado, tienen forma acorazonada alargada, color verde brillante en la superficie superior, gruesas, con una vena principal marcada. Inflorescencia en la base de la hoja, tiene pocas flores. Flores hasta 10 mm de largo, de forma irregular; sépalos y pétalos modificados en mayor o menor grado, color rosado rojizo con franjas amarillo verdosas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Ecuador. En el Cajas crece en áreas rocosas.", :description_en => "Terrestrial herbs, up to 20 cm tall, found in large groups, growing on rocks. Leaves pendent at the top of a long slender stem, solitary, up to 10 cm long, elongated heart-shaped, bright green above, leathery, with a single main vein. The few-flowered inflorescence originates on the base of the leaf. Flowers irregular, up to 10 mm long; sepals and petals modified, reddish pink with greenish yellow stripes. \\n", :distribution_en => " Ecuador. In Cajas it grows in rocky areas.", :old_id => "273", :provincias => [{ :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 93, :name => "steyermarkii", :genus => { :id => 20, :name => "Draba", :family => { :id => 10, :name => "brassicaceae", :old_id => "67" }, :old_id => "98" }, :scientific => "Draba steyermarkii", :author => "Al-Shehbaz", :tropicos => "4104861", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 50 cm de alto, laxas, algo reclinadas, cubiertas de pelos ásperos. Hojas alternas, lanceoladas, hasta de 1.5 cm de largo, amontonadas. Inflorescencia en la parte terminal de los tallos y tiene hasta 10 flores. Flores hasta 10 mm de largo, tienen 4 pétalos algo sobrepuestos, color púrpura con la base amarillo verdosa. Frutos lanceolados, alargados o algo curvos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Cajas. Se encuentra principalmente en áreas rocosas, ocasional­mente en bosques de Polylepis y en el páramo de pajonal.", :description_en => "Lax herbs up to 50 cm tall, somewhat reclining, covered with coarse hairs. Leaves alternate, lanceolate, up to 1.5 cm long, clustered. Inflorescence terminal on the stem, with about 10 flowers. Flowers up to 10 mm long, with 4 overlapping petals, purple with a greenish yellow base. Fruits lanceolate, elongate or curved. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Cajas. It is mainly found in rocky areas, occasionally in the Polylepis forests and grass páramo.", :old_id => "99", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 94, :name => "cumbalensis", :genus => { :id => 53, :name => "Passiflora", :family => { :id => 33, :name => "passifloraceae", :old_id => "241" }, :old_id => "242" }, :scientific => "Passiflora cumbalensis", :author => "(Karst.) Harms", :tropicos => "24200022", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 7, :name => "liana", :old_id => "240" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Son plantas trepadoras con zarcillos filamentosos enrollados. Hojas alternas, hasta 14 cm de largo, tienen tres lóbulos más o menos triangulares; márgenes aserrados. Flores solitarias, colgantes, hasta 10 cm de diámetro, color rosado violeta, con un tubo largo que hasta de 20 cm; pétalos son rosados; las brácteas florales son color verdoso azulado. Fruto carnoso, color amarillento. \\n", :distribution_es => " Desde el S Colombia al C Perú. En el Cajas se encuentra en los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Climbers with thin curled tendrils. Leaves alternate, up to 14 cm long, with 3 more or less triangular lobes, the margins serrate. Flowers solitary, pendent, up to 10 cm in diameter, violet pink, with a long tube up to 20 cm; petals pink; floral bracts greenish bluish. The fruit is fleshy, yellowish. \\n", :distribution_en => " S Colombia to C Peru. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "243", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 95, :name => "hartwegii", :genus => { :id => 48, :name => "Nototriche", :family => { :id => 30, :name => "malvaceae", :old_id => "220" }, :old_id => "221" }, :scientific => "Nototriche hartwegii", :author => "A. W. Hill", :tropicos => "19600568", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :description_es => "Hierbas forman almohadillas hasta de 1 m de diámetro, color verde grisáceo, densamente cubiertas por pelos blancos. Hojas amontonadas en la punta de los tallos, hasta 2 cm de largo, marcadamente lobuladas. Flores solitarias y se encuentran entre las hojas, erguidas, muy vistosas, hasta 2.5 cm; 5 pétalos traslapados y son color violeta intenso, con el centro verde; estambres forman una columna blanca con las anteras amarillas en la punta. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es una especie rara, endémica del S Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra sólo en sitios rocosos sobre los 4100 m.", :description_en => "Cushion-forming herbs, up to 1 m in diameter, grayish green, densely covered with white hairs. Leaves clustered at the tip of the stems, up to 2 cm long, markedly lobed. Flowers solitary and found among the leaves, erect, showy, up to 2.5 cm long; 5 overlapping petals, deep violet with a green center; stamens form a white column with the yellow anthers at the top. \\n", :distribution_en => " A rare endemic species to S Ecuador. In Cajas it is only found in rocky areas above 4100 m.", :old_id => "222", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }] }
{ :id => 96, :name => "jamesonii", :genus => { :id => 8, :name => "Brachyotum", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "49" }, :scientific => "Brachyotum jamesonii", :author => "Triana", :tropicos => "20300412", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 1.5 m de alto, con pelos blancos gruesos en toda la planta. Hojas lanceoladas, opuestas, hasta 1.6 cm de largo, tienen 3 venas principales que salen de la base. Flores colgantes, se las ve en pares, hasta 20 mm de largo, con brácteas y sépalos color rojo-rosado; pétalos sobrepuestos en forma de tubo, color morado oscuro. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del C y S del Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en el páramo de pajonal y en los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1.5 m tall, covered with coarse hairs. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 1.6 cm long, with 3 main veins from the base. Flowers pendent, in pairs, up to 20 mm long, with pinkish-red bracts and sepals; overlapping petals form a dark purple tube. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to C and S Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the grass páramo and in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "50", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }] }
{ :id => 97, :name => "glandulosum", :genus => { :id => 17, :name => "Diplostephium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "86" }, :scientific => "Diplostephium glandulosum", :author => "Hieron.", :tropicos => "2705432", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 3 m de alto; las ramas y la cara inferior de las hojas tienen pelos lanosos color blanco grisáceo. Hojas alternas y lineares, gruesas, hasta 1.2 cm de largo; márgenes doblados hacia abajo. Inflorescencia con forma de cabezuelas de alrededor 2 cm de largo, se encuentra al final de las ramas. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (± 20) irregulares, presentan una lengüeta de 15 mm de largo, color lila intenso; las internas (± 15) tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. El fruto tiene una corona de pelos rojizos. \\n", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. En el Cajas se encuentra en los bosques de Polylepis.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 3 m tall; branches and lower surface of leaves covered with wooly grayish-white hairs. Leaves alternate, linear, leathery, up to 1.2 cm long, and the margins curl downwards. Inflorescences heads around 2 cm long, at the tip of the branches. Flowers of two types: the external (± 20) irregular, strap-shaped, 15 mm long, deep lilac; internal (± 15) tubular with 5 yellow teeth. Fruits with a crown of reddish hairs. \\n", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador. In Cajas it is found in the Polylepis forests.", :old_id => "89", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 98, :name => "longibarbata", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella longibarbata", :author => "(Gilg) Fabris", :tropicos => "13801791", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas con tallos laxos, algo reclinados en la base, algo leñosos, hasta 80 cm de alto. Hojas lanceoladas, opuestas, hasta 6 cm de largo, y son algo duras. Flores hasta 40 mm de largo, tienen apariencia tubular por los pétalos algo sobrepuestos, algo colgantes, color verde amarillento o amarillo limón, a veces con manchas moradas. \\n", :distribution_es => " Es endémica del Cajas, crece dentro de los bosques de Polylepis o en el páramo arbustivo.", :description_en => "Plants with lax stems, somewhat reclining at base, somewhat woody, up to 80 cm tall. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 6 cm long, stiff. Flowers 40 mm long, appearing tubular by the overlapping petals, pendent, and yellowish green or lemon yellow, sometimes with purple dots. \\n", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Cajas, where it is found in the Polylepis forests or in the shrubby páramo.", :old_id => "139", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 99, :name => "myrtilloides", :genus => { :id => 25, :name => "Escalonia", :family => { :id => 17, :name => "escalloniaceae", :old_id => "116" }, :old_id => "117" }, :scientific => "Escalonia myrtilloides", :author => "L.f.", :tropicos => "29100693", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 3 m de alto. Hojas alternas, hasta 2.5 cm de largo, lanceoladas, con glándulas diminutas. Flores solitarias, colgantes, hasta 1.5 cm de largo, tienen forma de copa y 5 pétalos caedizos, color verde o crema verdoso; estigma es grande y claviforme. Fruto una cápsula seca que eventualmente se abre. \\n", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica, Panamá, Andes desde Venezuela hasta Argentina. En el Cajas se encuentra en restos de bosques y partes bajas del páramo.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 3 m tall. Leaves alternate, up to 2.5 cm long, lanceolate, with minute glands. Flowers solitary, pendent, up to 1.5 cm long, cup-shaped with 5 deciduous petals, green or greenish cream; stigma is nail-like and thick. Fruit a dry capsule that eventually opens. \\n", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica, Panama, and the Andes from Venezuela to Argentina. In Cajas it is found in forest remnants and lower páramo.", :old_id => "118", :provincias => [] }
{ :id => 100, :name => "paramoanus", :genus => { :id => 63, :name => "Potamogeton", :family => { :id => 36, :name => "potamogetonaceae", :old_id => "280" }, :old_id => "281" }, :scientific => "Potamogeton paramoanus", :author => "Haynes & Holm-Nielsen", :tropicos => "26300337", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas acuáticas sumergidas y flotantes, crecen en grupos densos; tallos de longitud variable de acuerdo a la profundidad del agua. Hojas de dos tipos: las sumergidas son alargadas, hasta 26 cm de largo, color verdoso algo translúcidas; las emergentes son espatuladas, hasta 7 cm de largo, y presentan un color verde-amarillento. Inflorescencias poco llamativas y sumergidas o emergentes, constituyen espigas de 1 cm de largo, color verde claro. Flores diminutas de 1.5 mm de largo. \\n", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Bolivia. En el Cajas crece en las lagunas.", :description_en => "Aquatic herbs submerged and floating, forming dense groups; stems of variable length according to the depth of the water. Leaves of two types: those submerged elongate, up to 26 cm long, greenish and translucent; emerging leaves spathulate, up to 7 cm long, yellowish-green. Inflorescences inconspicuous and submerged or emerging, spikes up to 1 cm long, light green. Flowers minute, 1.5 mm long. \\n", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia. In Cajas it grows in the lakes.", :old_id => "282", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 101, :name => "biloba", :genus => { :id => 3, :name => "Azorella", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" }, :old_id => "20" }, :scientific => "Azorella biloba", :author => "Azorella biloba (Schltdl.) Wedd.", :tropicos => "1701201", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas que crecen formando almohadillas compactas. Hojas amontonadas al final de las ramas, hasta 1 cm de largo, de oblongas a lanceoladas, algo carnosas, brillantes, el ápice entero o partido en 2-3 lóbulos, de glabros a densamente estrigosos; pecíolo dilatado en la base. Inflorescencias pequeñas, en umbelas alrededor de 1 cm, hasta con 10 flores, rodeadas por pequeñas brácteas de margen ciliado. Flores diminutas, de hasta 3 mm de largo, de un blanco verdoso o amarillento. Frutos alrededor de 2,5 mm, ovoides, glabros, con 3 costillas, con vesículas secretoras de aceites. Especies similares: Azorella pedunculata. ", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica a Argentina.", :description_en => "Plants growing forming cushions form. Leaves crowded at the end of the branches, up to 1 cm long, oblong to lanceolate, somewhat fleshy, bright, the apex entire or divided in 2-3 lobes, glabrous to densely strigose; petiole dilated at the base. Inflorescences small, in umbels about 1 cm, with up to 10 flowers, surrounded by small bracts with a ciliated margin. Flowers minute, up to 3 mm long, white or yellowish-green. Fruits about 2.5 mm, ovoid, glabrous, with 3 ribs, secretory oil vesicles present. Similar species: Azorella pedunculata. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Argentina.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 102, :name => "acaule ", :genus => { :id => 79, :name => "Chrysactinium", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" } }, :scientific => "Chrysactinium acaule ", :author => "Chrysactinium acaule (Kunth) Wedd.", :tropicos => "2700541", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, acaulescentes. Hojas opuestas que forman una roseta basal, largamente espatuladas (incluyendo la base de la hoja), la parte distal rómbica, hasta 5 cm, la base decurrente sobre el pecíolo, los márgenes irregularmente dentados con dientes negros hasta de 1 mm, el envés totalmente cubierto por una capa de tomento lanado blanquecino, el haz verde, cortamente tomentoso. Cabezuelas solitarias, campanuladas, hasta 2,5 cm de largo; pedúnculo erecto, de hasta 25 cm, café rojizo, de escasa a densamente aracnoide-tomentoso; brácteas involucrales en 5 hileras progresivamente más largas, color verde claro. Flores de dos tipos: marginales hasta 60, las corolas hasta 18 mm, liguladas con diminutos dientes en el ápice, color amarillo brillante, los estilos hasta de 10 mm; flores del disco hasta 100, las corolas hasta 8 mm, tubulares, amarillas; los estambres hasta 4 mm, los estilos hasta 9 mm. Vilano de cerdas, hasta 6 mm, blancas. ", :distribution_es => " Del norte del Ecuador al norte del Perú.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, acaulescent. Leaves opposite, forming a basal rosette, long-spatulate (including the base of the leaf), the distal part rhombic, up to 5 cm, base decurrent onto the petiole, the margins irregularly toothed with black teeth up to 1 mm, abaxially totally covered with a layer of white lanate tomentum, adaxially green, shortly tomentose. Flower heads solitary, bell-shaped, up to 2.5 cm long; peduncle erect up to 25 cm, reddish-brown, sparsely to densely arachnoid-tomentose; involucral bracts in 5 rows progressively longer, light green. Two types of flowers: marginal ones up to 60, the corolla up to 18 mm, ligulate, with minute teeth at the apex, bright yellow, styles up to 10 mm; disk flowers up to 100, the corolla up to 8 mm, tubular, yellow; stamens up to 4 mm, styles up to 9 mm. Pappus of bristles, up to 6 mm, white. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to N Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 103, :name => "azorelloides ", :genus => { :id => 80, :name => "Niphogeton", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" } }, :scientific => "Niphogeton azorelloides ", :author => "Niphogeton azorelloides Mathias & Constance", :tropicos => "1701339", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas cespitosas, bajas, que forman tapetes, 2-4 cm de alto, glabras, amarillo-verdosas, la base leñosa. Hojas alternas, amontonadas, oblongo-ovadas, 4-9 mm de largo, profundamente 3-lobuladas, los lóbulos linear-oblongos, 2-6 mm, angostos, enteros; los pecíolos de hasta 15 mm, alado-envainadores. Inflorescencias en pequeñas umbelas, el pedúnculo corto alrededor de 15 mm; involucro con 2 brácteas alrededor de 5 mm; rayos 1-3, ascendentes, los pétalos 5, ovados, blancos. Fruto de mericarpos alrededor de 2 mm, marcadamente 5-acostillados, con vesículas secretoras de aceites, el carpóforo bífido. Especies similares: Oreomyrrhis andicola, Niphogeton dissecta. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos del centro y sur del Ecuador y norte del Perú. En el Ecuador ha sido registrada en las provincias de Azuay, Cañar, Chimborazo, Cotopaxi, Napo y Pichincha, entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Low, caespitose herbs forming mats, 2-4 cm tall, glabrous, yellow-green, woody base. Leaves alternate, crowded, oblong-ovate leaves, 4-9 mm long, deeply 3-lobed, the lobes linear-oblong, 2-6 mm, narrow, entire; petioles up to 15 mm, winged-sheathed. Inflorescences in small umbels, peduncle short about 15 mm; involucre with 2 bracts about 5 mm; rays 1-3, ascendent, petals 5, ovate, white. Fruit of mericarps of about 2 mm, markedly 5-ribbed, with secretory oil vesicles, carpophore bifid. Similar species: Oreomyrrhis andicola, Niphogeton dissecta. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to N. Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }] }
{ :id => 104, :name => "dissecta ", :genus => { :id => 80, :name => "Niphogeton", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" } }, :scientific => "Niphogeton dissecta ", :author => "Niphogeton dissecta (Benth.) J. F. Macbr.", :tropicos => "1700751", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas delgadas o densas, caulescentes, ramificadas, hasta 35 cm de alto. Hojas alternas, 1–2 veces pinnadas, de oblongas a ovadas, 1,5–8 cm de largo, los folíolos hasta 12 mm de largo, profundamente lobados o pinnatífidos, las últimas divisiones lineares, hasta 6 mm; pecíolos 2–15 cm, envainadores en la base. Inflorescencias en umbelas corimbosas, el pedicelo hasta de 6 cm; involucro con 2 brácteas hasta de 35 mm de largo, lobuladas; rayos 5–12, hasta 30 mm de largo, flores numerosas, muy pequeñas; pétalos 5, ovados, blancos. Frutos, mericarpos alrededor de 4 mm, marcadamente 5-acostillados, con vesículas secretoras de aceites, el carpóforo bífido. Especies similares: Niphogeton ternata. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos desde Venezuela hasta Bolivia. En el Ecuador está registrada en toda la cordillera, sobre los 3000 m s.n.m., solo en la provincia de Loja se encuentra a alturas inferiores.", :description_en => "Thin to thick herbs, caulescent, branched, up to 35 cm high. Leaves alternate, 1-2-pinnate, oblong to ovate, 1.5-8 cm long, the leaflets up to 12 mm long, deeply lobed or pinnatifid, the last divisions linear, up to 6 mm; petioles 2-15 cm, sheathed at the base. Inflorescences corymbose in umbels, pedicel up to 6 cm; involucre bracts 2 to 35 mm long, lobed; rays 5-12, up to 30 mm long, flowers many, very small; petals 5, ovate, white. Fruits of mericarps about 4 mm, markedly 5-ribbed, with secretory oil vesicles, carpophore bifid. Similar species: Niphogeton ternata. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 105, :name => "ternata ", :genus => { :id => 80, :name => "Niphogeton", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" } }, :scientific => "Niphogeton ternata ", :author => "Niphogeton ternata (Willd. ex Schltr.) Mathias & Constance", :tropicos => "1703390", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas delgadas, hasta 1 m de alto, desparramadas, ramificadas, leñosas en la base. Hojas alternas, de ovadas a orbiculares, hasta 4,5 cm de largo, ternado-divididas, los folíolos obovados, alrededor de 3 mm, de enteros a dentados, las últimas divisiones dentadas; pecíolos hasta 10 cm, envainadores en la base. Inflorescencias en umbela, el pedúnculo hasta de 4 cm; involucro con 5–7 brácteas lineares, hasta de 20 mm de largo, lobuladas; rayos 5–12, hasta 30 mm de largo, de patentes a ascendentes; flores numerosas, muy pequeñas; pétalos 5, ovados, blancos. Frutos, mericarpos alrededor de 4 mm, marcadamente 5-acostillados, con vesículas secretoras de aceites, el carpóforo bífido, los ejes de las infrutescencias color café-rojizo. Especies similares: Niphogeton dissecta. ", :distribution_es => " Desde Venezuela hasta el Ecuador, donde se encuentra sobre los 3000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Slender herbs, up to 1 m high, scattered, branched, woody at the base. Leaves alternate, ovate to orbicular, up to 4.5 cm long, ternatly-divided, the leaflets obovate, about 3 mm, serrated to entire, the last divisions toothed; petioles up to 10 cm, sheathed at the base. Inflorescences in umbels, peduncle up to 4 cm; involucre with 5-7 bracts linear, up to 20 mm long, lobed; rays 5-12, up to 30 mm long, ascending to patent; flowers numerous,  very small; petals 5, ovate, white. Fruits of mericarps about 4 mm, markedly 5-ribbed, with secretory oil vesicles, bifid carpophore, infructescences axes reddish-brown. Similar species: Niphogeton dissecta. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 106, :name => "andicola ", :genus => { :id => 81, :name => "Oreomyrrhis", :family => { :id => 2, :name => "apiaceae", :old_id => "16" } }, :scientific => "Oreomyrrhis andicola ", :author => "Oreomyrrhis andicola (Kunth) Endl. ex Hook. f.", :tropicos => "1703586", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas cespitosas bajas, 3-5 cm de alto, blanco-tomentosas. Hojas alternas, pinnatisectas, en contorno de oblongo a ovado, 1-8 cm; los folíolos 9-17, 1,5-15 mm largo 1-10 mm ancho, las divisiones enteras o pinnatífidas, las divisiones finales densas, de ovadas a lineares; pecíolos 0,5-10 cm, envainadores en la base. Inflorescencias en umbelas sobre pedúnculos 1-40 cm, hirsutos; brácteas del involucro 6-10, de lanceoladas a obovadas, enteras a pinnatisectas, pubescentes, connatas, los pétalos 5, inconspicuos, blancos o matizados de rosado. Fruto de mericarpos, 3-5 mm de largo, acostillados, glabros o pubescentes, con vesículas secretoras de aceites; el carpóforo es bífido. Especies similares: Niphogeton azorelloides. ", :distribution_es => " De Costa Rica y Colombia a Bolivia y Argentina. En el Ecuador se distribuye en la región andina, entre 2500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Low caespitose herbs, 3-5 cm tall, white-tomentose. Leaves alternate, pinnatisect, in outline oblong to ovate 1-8 cm; leaflets 9-17, 1.5-15 mm long 1-10 mm wide, divisions entire or pinnatifid, final divisions dense, ovate to linear; petioles 0.5-10 cm, sheathed at the base. Inflorescences in umbels on 1-40 cm peduncles, hirsute; involucre bracts 6-10, lanceolate to obovate, entire to pinnatisect, pubescent, connate, petals 5, inconspicuous, white or tinged with pink. Fruit of mericarps, 3-5 mm long, ribbed, glabrous or pubescent, with secretory oils vesicles; the carpophore bifid. Similar species: Niphogeton azorelloides. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica and Colombia to Bolivia and Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 107, :name => "jamesoniana", :genus => { :id => 82, :name => "Aphanactis", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Aphanactis jamesoniana", :author => "Aphanactis jamesoniana Wedd.", :tropicos => "2743236", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, hasta 10 cm de alto, cespitosas, rastreras, enraizantes. Hojas opuestas, oblongo-espatuladas, de hasta 1,5 cm, color verde claro, trinervias, con tricomas largos y translúcidos, la base sésil, abrazadora, los entrenudos muy cortos. Inflorescencia de cabezuelas terminales, pequeñas, campanuladas, solitarias, 4 mm, a ras de suelo hasta el momento de la floración y progresivamente se extiende hasta el fructificación sobre un pedúnculo elevado, rojizo, de hasta 5 cm. Flores tubulares con una lígula muy corta, amarillo-limón; las flores marginales son pistiladas y las del disco son perfectas, cubiertas de tricomas largos, delgados. Vilano ausente. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador. Se distribuye ampliamente en los páramos de Imbabura, Pichincha, Cotopaxi, Tungurahua, Chimborazo y Azuay.", :description_en => "Small herbs up to 10 cm tall, tussock, creeping, rooting. Leaves opposite, oblong-spatulate, up to 1.5 cm, light green, trinerved, with long, translucent trichomes, base sessile, clasping, very short internodes. Inflorescence terminal heads, small, bell-shaped, solitary, 4 mm, at ground level until flowering and gradually extending to fruiting on a 5 cm, raised, reddish peduncle. Tubular flowers with a very short, lemon-yellow ligule; marginal flowers are pistillate and disc flowers are perfect, covered with long, slender trichomes. Pappus absent. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 108, :name => "tricuneata ", :genus => { :id => 4, :name => "Baccharis", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "24" }, :scientific => "Baccharis tricuneata ", :author => "Baccharis tricuneata (L. f.) Pers.", :tropicos => "2733106", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de hasta 2 m de alto, densamente ramificados, las ramas cenizo-rojizas, estriadas, los tallos rectangulares. Hojas alternas, erectas, hasta de 1 cm de largo, obovadas, el haz verde oscuro brillante, el envés verde con puntos oscuros; coriáceas, los márgenes con 1 o 2, a veces 3 dientes apicales a cada lado, la base subsésil y ancha que deja cicatrices en los tallos, los entrenudos muy cortos, menos de 5 mm. Inflorescencias axilares, corimbosas, hasta 1 cm, con 3-4 cabezuelas compactas, masculinas y femeninas, las brácteas ciliadas, color verde claro con la punta oscura, las flores tubulares, 4 mm, color de verde pálido a verde- amarillento. Vilano de tricomas pajizos de 4 mm de largo. ", :distribution_es => " De Venezuela a Bolivia, Chile y Argentina.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 2 m tall, densely branched, branches striate, ash-brown, rectangular stems. Leaves alternate, erect, up to 1 cm long, obovate, shiny dark green above, green with dark dots below, leathery, margins with 1 or 2 sometimes 3 apical teeth on each side, broad subsessile base leaving scars on stems. Very short internodes, less than 5 mm. Jnflorescences axillary, corymbose, up to 1 cm, with 3-4 compact, male and female heads, bracts ciliate, light green with dark tip, flowers tubular, 4 mm, pale green to yellowish-green. Pappus of trichomes straw-colored, 4 mm long. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia, Chile and Argentina.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 109, :name => "andicola", :genus => { :id => 83, :name => "Bidens", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Bidens andicola", :author => "Bidens andicola Kunth", :tropicos => "2701917", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas anuales rastreras, hasta de 50 cm de alto. Hojas opuestas, compuestas imparipinnadas. Inflorescencias en capítulos radiados, terminales sobre un pedúnculo largo de hasta 20 cm; involucro campanulado, los filarios rígidos, de color café.  Flores marginales de color amarillo, la corola de 10 mm de largo, ligulada; flores del disco amarillo-verdosas, tubulares con 5 dientes pequeños; estilo bifurcado, las ramas recurvadas. Fruto en aquenio provisto de dos tricomas espinosos. Especies similares: Bidens triplinervia Kunth. ", :distribution_es => " Desde Venezuela hasta Argentina. En el Ecuador se encuentra entre 2000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Annual herbs, crawling, up to 50 cm high. Leaves opposite, imparipinnate. Inflorescences radiated heads, terminal on a long peduncle up to 20 cm; involucre campanulate, phyllaries stiff and brown. Marginal flowers yellow, corolla 10 mm long, ligulate; disc flowers greenish-yellow, tubular with 5 small teeth; bifurcated style, branches recurved. Fruit an achene with two prickly trichomes. Similar species: Bidens triplinervia. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Argentina.", :provincias => [{ :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 110, :name => "mexicana ", :genus => { :id => 84, :name => "Cotula", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Cotula mexicana ", :author => "Cotula mexicana (DC.) Cabrera", :tropicos => "2716882", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas bajas, cespitosas, acaulescentes o con tallos aéreos cortos, estolonados; los estolones largos, hasta 15 cm de largo, de glabros a pilosos, con tintes morado-rojizos. Hojas 1-3-pinnatífidas, 1-3,5 cm, oblanceoladas en contorno, carnosas, amarillo-verdosas; el nervio principal marcado, los segmentos opuestos, 3-6 pares, enteros o lobulados, los ápices espinosos, el último segmento oblanceolado, alrededor de 3 mm de largo, el pecíolo dilatado en la base. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas axilares, los pedúnculos alrededor de 1 cm, vellosos, las cabezuelas alrededor de 5 mm de diámetro, el involucro con 10 brácteas con los ápices color lila, las flores marginales 7-10, sin corola, las flores del disco alrededor de 60, alrededor de 2 mm, tubulares, 3-lobuladas, blancas, las del centro con tintes lilas. Especies similares: Cotula australis (Sieber ex Spreng.) Hook. F. ", :distribution_es => " Originaria de Centro y Sudamérica, se distribuye desde México hasta, Bolivia, Chile y Argentina. En el Ecuador crece en la cordillera de los andes entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Low herbs, caespitose, acaulescent or with short aerial stems, runners present; runners long, up to 15 cm long, glabrous to hairy, tinged with purple-red. Leaves 1-3-pinnatifid, 1-3.5 cm, oblanceolate in outline, fleshy, yellow-green; midrib prominent, segments opposite, 3-6 pairs, entired or lobed, apex spiny, the last segment oblanceolate, about 3 mm long, the petiole dilated at base. Inflorescences in axillary heads, pedicels about 1 cm, villous, the heads about 5 mm in diameter, with 10 involucre bracts with purple apex, 7-10 marginal flowers without corolla, disk flowers around 60, about 2 mm, tubular, 3-lobed, white, the center tinged with purple. Similar apecies: Cotula australis. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to, Bolivia, Chile and Argentina.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 111, :name => "hartwegii ", :genus => { :id => 17, :name => "Diplostephium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "86" }, :scientific => "Diplostephium hartwegii ", :author => "Diplostephium hartwegii Hieron", :tropicos => "2705437", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles de hasta 8 m de alto y 12 cm de DAP, abundantemente ramificado, ramas infértiles alargadas y ramas cortas con capítulos terminales solitarios, cubierto de una pubescencia lanosa en las ramitas y envés de las hojas. Hojas subsésiles, dispuestas en espiral, lámina de elíptica a linear de 3 a 8 mm de largo por 1 a 3 mm de ancho, haz lustroso envés lanoso tomentoso, margen doblado hacia abajo. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas terminales de 1,2 cm de largo por 1 cm de diámetro; involucro campanulado con 5 series de filarias, filarias externas ovadas de 3 mm de largo por 1,5 mm de ancho, filarias internas lineares de 5 mm de largo por 1 mm de ancho. Flores marginales irregulares (alrededor de 12 por cabezuela) con una lígula lila claro de 12 mm de largo. Flores centrales tubulares de color amarillo claro, con 5 lóbulos. Fruto, un aquenio piloso con una corona de cerdas rojizas. Especies similares: Diplostephium oblanceolatum. ", :distribution_es => " Andes del Sur de Colombia y Ecuador, entre 2500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees up to 8 m high, 12 cm of DBH, densely branched, infertile branches elongated and short branches with terminal solitary heads covered with a wooly pubescence on twigs and leaves abaxially. Sub sessile leaves, spirally arranged, linear elliptical blade 3 to 8 mm long by 1-3 mm wide, bright upper leaf, undersides woolly-tomentose, margin folded down. Inflorescences in heads terminal 1.2 cm long by 1 cm diameter; involucre campanulate with 5 sets of filarial. External filarial ovate 3 mm long and 1.5 mm wide, linear internal filarial of 5 mm long by 1 mm wide. Irregular marginal flowers (around 12 per flower head) with a pale lilac ligule 12 mm long. Tubular central flowers pale yellow, with five lobes. Fruit, a pilous achene with a crown of reddish bristles. Similar species: Diplostephium oblanceolatum. ", :distribution_en => " S Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 112, :name => "oblanceolatum ", :genus => { :id => 17, :name => "Diplostephium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "86" }, :scientific => "Diplostephium oblanceolatum ", :author => "Diplostephium oblanceolatum S.F. Blake", :tropicos => "2743300", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de 0.5 a 2 m de alto, densamente ramificados, las ramitas y el envés de las hojas, densamente lanado-tomentosas. Hojas alternas, sésiles, amontonadas en las ramitas, lámina de oblanceolada a espatulada, de 7 a 12 mm de largo por 1,5 a 2,5 mm de ancho. Haz densamente glanduloso, envés lanado tomentoso, margen doblado hacia abajo. Inflorescencias de cabezuelas solitarias de alrededor de 2,2 cm de diámetro, dispuestas al final de las ramas; involucro campanulado, con 5 series de brácteas, brácteas externas ovadas y brácteas internas lanceoladas. Flores de dos tipos: flores marginales alrededor de 20, irregulares, liguladas; la lígula de color lila claro, hasta de 15 mm de largo, con tres dientes diminutos en el ápice; flores del disco hasta 15, tubulares, amarillas, con 5 dientes diminutos. El fruto presenta un vilano con corona de tricomas rojizos. Especies similares: Diplostephium hartwegii. ", :distribution_es => " Andes altos del centro y sur del Ecuador entre 3000 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Shrubs 0.5 to 2 m tall, densely branched, twigs and leaf blades below thick woolly-tomentose. Leaves alternate, sessile, crowded on twigs, blade oblanceolate to spatulat, 7 to 12 ×1.5 to 2.5 mm, leaf blade above densely glandular, below woolly tomentose, margin recurved downwards. Inflorescences of solitary heads, about 2.2 cm in diameter, arranged at the end of branches; involucre campanulate, with 5 series of bracts, external bracts ovate and internal bracts lanceolate. Flowers of two types: marginal flowers about 20, irregular, ligulate; ligule pale lilac, up to 15 mm long, with three minute teeth at apex; up disk flowers to 15, tubular, yellow, with five minute teeth. Fruit pappus with a crown of reddish trichomes. Similar species: Diplostephium hartwegii. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 113, :name => "rupestre ", :genus => { :id => 17, :name => "Diplostephium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "86" }, :scientific => "Diplostephium rupestre ", :author => "Diplostephium rupestre (Kunth) Wedd.", :tropicos => "2725156", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de 1 a 2 m de alto, pobremente ramificado; ramitas terminales cubiertas por una pubescencia lanosa.  Hojas sésiles, alternas, oblongo-lanceoladas, 3,5–4,5 × 0,3–0,5 cm, los márgenes revolutos, el haz cubierto con tricomas blancos largos, el envés densamente pubescente-lanoso. Inflorescencias en capítulos agrupados en tirsos, 4–4,5 × 4–4,5 cm. Capítulos heterógamos radiados, involucro campanulado, con 4 series de filarias, las filarias externas ovado-lanceoladas, 4–5 × 1,5 a 1,6 mm de ancho, las filarias internas oblongo- lanceoladas, 6–7 × 1,5–1,6 mm. Flores marginales liguladas en 3 series, la lígula blanca de 4 mm de largo, con 3 dientes diminutos apicales; flores centrales estaminadas; corola tubular-infundibuliforme, amarilla, de 4,2 mm de largo. Aquenios cafés, 2–2,5 mm de largo, glandulosos; pappus de cerdas escabrosas. Especies similares: Diplostephium ericoides. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos de Colombia, Ecuador y Perú, sobre los 3000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Shrubs 1-2 m tall, scarsely branched; terminal twigs covered by a woolly pubescence. Leaves sessile, alternate, oblong-lanceolate, 3.5-4.5 × 0.3-0.5 cm, margins revolute, leaf blade covered with white long trichomes above, densely woolly pubescent below. Inflorescences in heads grouped into thyrses, 4-4.5 × 4-4.5 cm. Heads radiated heterogamous, involucre campanulate, with 4 sets of filaries, external filaries ovate-lanceolate, 4-5 × 1.5 to 1.6 mm wide, internal filaries oblong-lanceolate, 6-7 × 1.5- 1.6 mm. Marginal flowers ligulate,  in 3 series, ligule white, 4 mm long with 3 minute apical teeth; central flowers staminate; corolla tubular-infundibuliform, yellow, 4.2 mm long. Achenes brown, 2-2.5 mm long, glandular; pappus of scabrous bristles. Similar species: Diplostephium ericoides. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 114, :name => "americana ", :genus => { :id => 85, :name => "Gamochaeta", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Gamochaeta americana ", :author => "Gamochaeta americana (Mill.) Wedd.", :tropicos => "2710236", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas 0,1-0,5 m, laxamente blanco-lanadas, los entrenudos basales y apicales muy cortos, más alargados en la mitad del tallo. Hojas hasta 5 cm de largo, que decrecen distalmente, oblanceoladas a obovadas; el haz verde opaco, el envés blanco-panoso, los márgenes remotamente dentados, la base abrazadora. Inflorescencias en espigas densas de varias cabezuelas, terminales, 1-5 cm de largo, sésiles; las cabezuelas hasta 4,5 mm, cilíndricas, las brácteas verdes tornándose cafés. Flores 2-3 mm de largo, de blanquecinas a amarillentas. Vilano de cerdas de 3 mm, blanco. Especies similares: Gamochaeta purpurea. ", :distribution_es => " Desde México y las Antillas hasta Brasil y Argentina. En el Ecuador presenta una amplia distribución a lo largo de la región andina.", :description_en => "Herbs 0.1-0.5 m, loosely white-woolly, basal and apical internodes very short, more elongated at the midstem. Leaves up to 5 cm long, decreasing distally, oblanceolate to obovate; leaf ablade above dull green, white below, margins remotely toothed, base clasping. Inflorescences in dense spikes of several heads, terminal, 1-5 cm long, sessile; heads up to 4.5 mm, cylindrical, bracts green turning brown. Flowers 2-3 mm long, whitish to yellowish. Pappus of bristle 3 mm, white. Similar species: Gamochaeta purpurea. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico and the West Indies to Brazil and Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 115, :name => "baccharoides ", :genus => { :id => 32, :name => "Gynoxys", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "151" }, :scientific => "Gynoxys baccharoides ", :author => "Gynoxys baccharoides (Kunth) Cass.", :tropicos => "2706383", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles pequeños hasta 5 m de alto, tienen una densa capa de tricomas color blanco grisáceo. Hojas opuestas, lanceoladas, hasta 10 cm de largo. Inflorescencias de varias cabezuelas, cada una hasta de 1,5 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las externas (alrededor de 8) son irregulares, presentan una lígula llamativa hasta de 13 mm de largo, color amarillo brillante, las internas (alrededor de 18) son tubulares y con 5 dientes, color amarillo. Fruto con una corona de tricomas ásperos, hasta de 15 mm de largo, blanco-pajizos. Especies similares: Gynoxys cuicochensis Cuatrec. ", :distribution_es => " Andes del Ecuador entre 3500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Shrubs or small trees up to 5 m tall, with a dense layer of grayish white trichomes. Leaves opposite, lanceolate, up to 10 cm long. Inflorescences of various heads, each up to 1.5 cm in diameter. Flowers of two types: external (around 8) irregular with conspicuous ligula up to 13 mm long, bright yellow. Internal (about 18) tubular, with 5 teeth, yellow. Fruit with a crown of rough trichomes, up to 15 mm long, white-straw-colored. Similar species: Gynoxys cuicochensis. ", :distribution_en => " Andes of Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 116, :name => "buxifolia ", :genus => { :id => 32, :name => "Gynoxys", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "151" }, :scientific => "Gynoxys buxifolia ", :author => "Gynoxys buxifolia (Kunth) Cass.", :tropicos => "2706386", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 5 m de alto. Copa irregular, ramificación opuesta; follaje de color blanquecino con inflorescencia de color amarillo intenso. Hojas simples, opuestas, con estípulas, sostenidas por un corto pecíolo hasta de 1,6 mm de largo, puberulento de color plomizo-blanquecino, el haz verde-oscuro lustroso, el envés blanquecino, puberulento. Inflorescencias paniculado-corimbosas de 5 a 7,5 cm de largo. Flores agrupadas en cabezuelas heterógamas de radiadas a discoides, cada cabezuela contiene alrededor de 18 flores: 8 flores marginales liguladas, la lígula tridentada de color amarillo intenso y 10 flores del disco con corola tubular con el ápice 5-partido. Fruto un pequeño aquenio café-oscuro con vilano blanco pajizo. Especies similares: Gynoxys miniphylla. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia, Ecuador, Perú. Es ampliamente distribuida en los Andes ecuatorianos.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 5 m high, crown irregular, branching opposite; foliage whitish with bright yellow inflorescence. Leaves simple, opposite, with stipules, petiole up to 1.6 mm long, grayish-white puberulent, leaf blade glossy dark-green above, whitish and puberulent below. Inflorescences paniculate-corymbose, 5 to 7.5 cm long. Flowers in heterogamous heads, radiated to discoid, each head contains about 18 flowers: 8 marginal ligulate, with tridentate bright yellow ligule and 10 disc flowers with tubular corolla with a 5-splited apex. Fruit a dark brown achene with white-straw pappus. Similar species: Gynoxys miniphylla. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 117, :name => "lingulatus ", :genus => { :id => 86, :name => "Lasiocephalus", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Lasiocephalus lingulatus ", :author => "Lasiocephalus lingulatus Schltdl.", :tropicos => "2733494", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Subarbustos erectos hasta de 0,5 m, densamente cubiertos en todas sus partes por una capa densa de indumento lanoso-aracnoideo, gris-blanquecino, el tallo redondeado. Hojas alternas, dirigidas hacia arriba, de lanceoladas a oblongo-lanceoladas, 1,5-3 cm de largo, los márgenes crenados y revolutos, el haz color verde oscuro con indumento laxo, el envés completamente cubierto por el indumento blanquecino, la base sésil y abrazadora. Inflorescencias terminales hasta 8 cm, con 3-4 cabezuelas hasta de 1,5 cm, sobre pedúnculos largos, nutantes, rodeados de brácteas alargadas densamente cubiertas por el indumento. Flores todas tubulares, color verde-limón. Vilano alrededor 8 mm, de aristas blancas. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador. Se distribuye en las montañas andinas entre 2900 y 4300 m s.n.m., en las provincias de Azuay, Chimborazo, Cotopaxi, Bolívar, Pichincha y Napo.", :description_en => "Erect subshrubs to 0.5 m, covered by a dense layer of woolly-arachnoid gray-white indumentum, stem rounded. Leaves alternate, directed upwards, lanceolate to oblong-lanceolate, 1.5-3 cm long, margins crenate and revolute, leaf blade dark green above with loose indumentum, completely covered by the whitish indumentum below, base sessile and clasping. Inflorescences terminal up to 8 cm, with 3-4 heads up to 1.5 cm on long peduncles, nodding, surrounded by elongated bracts densely covered by indumentum. Flowers all tubular, lime-green. Pappus about 8 mm, white edges. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 118, :name => "ovatus ", :genus => { :id => 86, :name => "Lasiocephalus", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Lasiocephalus ovatus ", :author => "Lasiocephalus ovatus Schltdl.", :tropicos => "2733501", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Subarbustos hasta de 0,8 m, flexuosos, con grueso indumento aracnoideo, gris-blanquecino sobre todo en las partes jóvenes, glabrescentes con la edad, los tallos con costillas notorias. Hojas dispuestas en espiral, los entrenudos muy cortos y las hojas muy cercanas unas de otras, patentes, ovadas, 0,8-1 cm de largo, enteras, gruesas, el haz color verde brillante, glabrescente; el envés completamente cubierto por el indumento gris-blanquecino, la base sésil y amplexicaule. Inflorescencias terminales, solitarias, las cabezuelas hasta de 1,5 cm, sésiles, nutantes, rodeados de brácteas alargadas densamente cubiertas por el indumento. Flores todas tubulares, color verde-limón. Vilano alrededor de 15 mm, de aristas blancas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador.", :description_en => "Subshrubs to 0.8 m, flexuous, with thick arachnoid indumentum, gray-white especially on young parts, glabrescent with age with notorious stems ribs. Leaves spirally arranged, very close to each other, patent, ovate, 0.8-1 cm long, entire, thick, internodes very shor, leaf blade bright green above, glabrescent, completely covered by gray-white indumentum below, sessile and clasping at base. Terminal inflorescences, solitary, heads up to 1.5 cm, sessile, nodding, surrounded by elongated bracts densely covered by indumentum. Flowers all tubular, lime-green. Pappus about 15 mm, of white bristlles. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 119, :name => "ferruginea ", :genus => { :id => 42, :name => "Loricaria", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "191" }, :scientific => "Loricaria ferruginea ", :author => "Loricaria ferruginea (Ruiz & Pav.) Wedd.", :tropicos => "2706777", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 1,5 m de alto, muy ramificados; ramas en un solo plano, lo que da al arbusto un aspecto aplanado. Hojas alternas, pequeñas y duras, hasta de 5 mm de largo, dobladas a lo largo de la nervadura central y con apariencia de escamas sobrepuestas en dos hileras, las inferiores color café rojizo y las superiores brillantes, color verde oscuro con las puntas rojizas, con abundantes tricomas sedosos y blancos en la parte interior. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas pequeñas hasta de 0,5 cm de diámetro. Flores de forma tubular, color amarillo pálido o crema. Fruto con una corona de tricomas hasta de 5 mm de largo, color blanco- pajizo. Especies similares: Loricaria azuayensis, Loricaria ilinissae.", :distribution_es => nil, :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1.5 m tall, densely branched; branches in a single plane, giving the shrub a flattened appearance. Leaves small, alternate, harden, up to 5 mm long, folded along the midrib and scale like overlapping in two rows, the lower ones reddish-brown and the upper ones, shiny, dark green with reddish tips, with abundant trichomes, silky and white on the inside. Inflorescences in small heads up to 0.5 cm diameter. Flowers tubular, pale yellow or cream color. Fruit with a crown of trichomes up to 5 mm long, white-stramineous. Similar species: Loricaria azuayensis, Loricaria ilinissae. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 120, :name => "ilinissae ", :genus => { :id => 42, :name => "Loricaria", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "191" }, :scientific => "Loricaria ilinissae ", :author => "Loricaria ilinissae (Benth.) Cuatrec.", :tropicos => "2706778", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de 0,8 a 1,5 m de alto. Tallos cilíndricos, de corteza externa gris. Ramificación alterna y densa que forma una copa de irregular a globosa; ramitas terminales lateralmente comprimidas, 0,3–0,4 cm de ancho. Hojas dísticas que abrazan los tallos; triángulo-cóncavas, alrededor de 3× 2 mm de profundidad, el haz glabro con puntos resinosos, el envés densamente pubescente lanoso. Capítulos terminales discoides, el involucro campanulado, con dos hileras de brácteas de color marrón; brácteas externas 4 × 1,5 mm de ancho, las brácteas internas 5 × 1 mm de ancho, todas las brácteas presentan el margen membranoso irregular. Flósculos 8–12 por capítulo; flósculos pistilados filiformes, de color amarillo crema, los flósculos estaminados amarillos, 5 mm de largo. Aquenio elipsoide, glabro, 6 mm de largo incluidas las cerdas del pappus. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador, registrada desde Carchi hasta Azuay.", :description_en => "Shrubs 0.8 to 1.5 m high. Stems cylindrical, outer bark gray. Branches alternate and dense branching, forming an irregular to globose treetop; terminal twigs laterally compressed, 0.3-0.4 cm wide. Leaves distichous clasping the stems, triangle-concave, about 3 × 2 mm, glabrous with resinous spots, densely pubescent-woolly below. Heads discoid terminal, involucre campanulate, with two rows of brown bracts; external bracts 4 x 1.5 mm wide, internal bracts 5 x 1 mm wide, all with irregular membranous margins. Flowers 8-12 per head; pistillate flowers filiforme, creamy yellow, staminate flowers yellow, 5 mm long. Achene ellipsoid, glabrous, 6 mm long including pappus bristles. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 121, :name => "andicola ", :genus => { :id => 87, :name => "Monticalia", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Monticalia andicola ", :author => "Monticalia andicola (Turcz.) C. Jeffrey", :tropicos => "2743568", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de 1 a 2 m de alto; tallos cilíndricos nudosos, con ramificación abierta. Hojas alternas, de oblongas a elípticas, 1,8–4,2 × 0,8–1,6 cm de ancho, los márgenes dentados, el haz verde oliváceo glabrescente, el envés tomentoso lanado, subsésiles. Inflorescencias terminales, corimbosas. Capítulos homógamos discoides, 0,8–1 cm de diámetro; receptáculo convexo con una hilera de 8 filarias libres, oblongas, 4–5 × 2 mm de ancho. Flósculos centrales de corola tubular amarilla, 4–5 mm de largo. Aquenios con 5 costillas; pappus de cerdas escabrosas basalmente connatas. ", :distribution_es => " Desde Costa Rica a Perú. En el Ecuador se encuentra a lo largo de toda la cordillera de los Andes.", :description_en => "Shrubs 1-2 m tall; stems cylindrical, knotted, with opened branching. Leaves alternate, oblong to elliptic, 1.8 -4.2 × 0.8-1.6 cm wide, margins dentate, leaf blade olive green above, glabrescent, lanate-tomentose below, subsessile. Inflorescences terminal, corymbose. Heads homogamous and discoid, 0.8-1 cm diameter; receptacle convex with a row of 8 free bracts, oblong, 4-5 × 2 mm. Central flowers with yellow tubular corolla, 4-5 mm long. Achenes with 5 ribs; pappus with scabrous bristles basally connate. ", :distribution_en => " From Costa Rica to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 122, :name => "empetroides ", :genus => { :id => 87, :name => "Monticalia", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Monticalia empetroides ", :author => "Monticalia empetroides (Cuatrec.) C. Jeffrey", :tropicos => "2743570", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 0,5 m de alto, muy ramificados, las ramas densamente blanco lanosas. Hojas alternas, diminutas, hasta de 5 mm de largo, ovado-lanceoladas, gruesas, rígidas, el ápice agudo, los márgenes enteros y revolutos, el haz lanoso cuando jóvenes y glabrescente con la edad, verde brillante; el envés totalmente cubierto por un denso tomento blanco lanoso, sésiles, los entrenudos muy cortos, lanosos. Inflorescencias de cabezuelas solitarias, terminales, brevemente pedunculadas, densamente blanco-lanosas, cada una hasta de 1,5 cm de largo. Flores de dos tipos, las flores marginales 11-13, hasta de 12 mm, la lígula angosta, color amarillo, las flores del disco alrededor de 25, tubulares, alrededor de 7 mm, con 5 dientes diminutos, amarillas. Vilano de tricomas sedosos hasta de 8 mm, blancos. Especies similares: Monticalia myrsinites. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador, ha sido colectada sólo en la provincia del Azuay.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 0.5 m tall, densely branched, branches densely white woolly. Leaves alternate, minute, up to 5 mm long, ovate-lanceolate, thick, rigid, acute apex, margins entire and revolute, leaf blade woolly when young and glabrescent with age, bright green,  completely covered by a white dense woolly tomentum below, sessile, internodes very short, wooly. Inflorescences in solitary heads, terminal, briefly stalked, densely white-woolly, each up to 1.5 cm long. Two types of flowers, marginal flowers 11-13, up to 12 mm, ligule narrow, yellow; disk flowers about 25, tubular, about 7 mm with 5 minute teeth, yellow. Pappus with silky trichomes up to 8 mm, white. Similar species: Monticalia myrsinites. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 123, :name => "myrsinites ", :genus => { :id => 87, :name => "Monticalia", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" } }, :scientific => "Monticalia myrsinites ", :author => "Monticalia myrsinites (Turcz.) C. Jeffrey", :tropicos => "2743572", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 1,5 m de alto, densamente ramificados. Hojas alternas, hasta de 0,5 cm de largo, ovado-elípticas, coriáceas; el haz verde brillante, el envés completamente cubierto por un denso indumento lanoso, blanco-grisáceo; el ápice apiculado, los márgenes ligeramente revolutos, con dientes pequeños espaciados los entrenudos muy cortos y las hojas aparecen amontonadas; pecíolo envainador. Inflorescencias de cabezuelas pequeñas, solitarias, terminales, cada una hasta de 1,5 cm de largo. Flores de dos tipos: flores marginales (alrededor de 10) liguladas, la lígula angosta, espatulada, hasta de 8 mm, color amarillo brillante, las flores del disco (alrededor de 20) tubulares, alrededor de 5 mm, con 5 dientes, color amarillo brillante. Vilano de tricomas sedosos, 8 mm de largo, blanco-grisáceos. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador. Se distribuye a lo largo de la cordillera de los Andes desde 2500 hasta 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1.5 m tall, densely branched. Leaves alternate up to 0.5 cm long, ovate-elliptic, leathery; leaf blade bright green above, completely covered by a dense woolly white-gray indumentum below, apex apiculate, margins slightly revolute, with small spaced teeth, very short internodes and leaves are stacked; petiole clasping. Inflorescences of small heads, solitary, terminal, each up to 1.5 cm long. Flowers of two types: marginal flowers (around 10) ligulate, ligule narrow, spatulate, up to 8 mm, bright yellow; disk flowers (around 20) tubular, about 5 mm, with 5 teeth, bright yellow. Pappus of silky trichomes, 8 mm long, white-gray. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.  ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 124, :name => "limnophilum ", :genus => { :id => 49, :name => "Oritrophium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "225" }, :scientific => "Oritrophium limnophilum ", :author => "Oritrophium limnophilum (Sch. Bip.) Cuatrec.", :tropicos => "2733751", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 7 cm de alto, el tallo erecto con entrenudos de 2-3 mm, con abundantes tricomas largos de color blanco entre los nudos. Hojas opuestas, algunos pecíolos son más largos que la lámina y tienen la base ensanchada; lámina oblongo-lanceolada, 1,8-2 cm de largo, 6-7 mm de ancho, el haz viloso, los márgenes enteros, el envés ligeramente tomentoso. Inflorescencia con un solo capítulo terminal, el pedúnculo púrpura, hasta de 6 cm de alto; receptáculo con 3 series de brácteas de color verde-púrpura. Flores marginales con la corola ligulada, cortamente lobulada, con la superficie superior de color blanco-liliáceo, las flores de disco tubulares de color amarillo-liliáceo. Aquenio con vilano transparente. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Venezuela a Bolivia. En el Ecuador se la encuentra en los páramos entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 7 cm tall, stem erect, internodes 2-3 mm with abundant long white trichomes. Leaves opposite, some petioles longer than the blade and with enlarged base, blade oblong-lanceolate, 1.8-2 cm long, 6-7 mm wide, leaf blade villous above, slightly tomentose below, margins entire. Terminal inflorescence with a single head, peduncle purple, up to 6 cm; receptacle bracts in 3 series, green-purple. Marginal flowers with ligulate corolla, shortly lobed, with the upper surface white-lilac, disc flowers tubular, yellow-lilac. Achenes with translucent pappus. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 125, :name => "peruvianum ", :genus => { :id => 49, :name => "Oritrophium", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "225" }, :scientific => "Oritrophium peruvianum ", :author => "Oritrophium peruvianum (Lam.) Cuatrec.", :tropicos => "2725738", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas rizomatosas de 10 a 30 cm de alto, con pubescencia lanosa parduzca en la base. Hojas dispuestas en una roseta basal de 10 a 20 cm de diámetro, peciolo ensanchado cubierto por una pubescencia lanosa, lámina oblonga de 4 a 8 cm de largo por 0,8 a 1,2 cm de ancho, margen entero y ápice acuminado, glabras, acanaladas en el haz y el envés con pubescencia tomentosa. Inflorescencias en cabezuelas solitarias, sostenidas por escapos, púrpuras de 12 a 25 cm de largo; cabezuelas de 1,5 a 2 cm de diámetro. Flores de dos tipos: las marginales son irregulares, largas, liguladas, de color blanco; las internas son cortas, tubulares de color amarillo-cremoso. Vilano con cerdas escábridas. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos desde Venezuela a Perú y noreste de Bolivia. En el Ecuador se distribuye a lo largo de la cordillera de los Andes entre 2500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Rhizomatous herbs, 10 to 30 cm tall, with brownish woolly pubescence at the base. Leaves arranged in a basal rosette of 10 to 20 cm diameter, petiole widened covered by a woolly pubescence, blade oblong, 4 -8 × 0.8 to 1.2 cm, margin entire and apex acuminate, glabrous, grooved above, with tomentose pubescence below. Inflorescences of solitary heads, on purple scapes 12-25 cm long; heads 1.5 to 2 cm diameter. Flowers of two types: marginal one are irregular, long, ligulate, white;internal ones are short, tubular, yellow-cream. Pappus of scabrid bristles. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru and northeastern Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 126, :name => "culcitioides ", :genus => { :id => 70, :name => "Senecio", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "310" }, :scientific => "Senecio culcitioides ", :author => "Senecio culcitioides Sch. Bip.", :tropicos => "2707691", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas rizomatosas, de 20 a 40 cm de alto, crecen formando rosetas basales. Hojas de elípticas a lanceoladas, 10–25 × 0,5–0,8 cm de ancho; el haz verde oliváceo, glabrescente, el envés blanco lanoso; pecíolos envainadores ensanchados, de color púrpura. Pedúnculo 15–40 cm de largo con pubescencia blanquecina lanosa. Capítulos caliculados, arreglados en cimas dicasiales, con una bráctea lateral de 2,5–4,5 cm de largo. Capítulos de 1,5 cm de diámetro, el involucro convexo con una hilera de filarias oblongo-lanceoladas, 6–8 × 1,2–1,6 mm de ancho, color púrpura, lanosas, con los márgenes membranosos translúcidos. Flósculos de color amarillo limón. Aquenios obovoides con una hilera de cerdas sedosas. ", :distribution_es => " De Ecuador a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Rhizomatous herbs, 20 to 40 cm tall, forming basal rosettes. Leaves elliptic to lanceolate, 10-25 × 0.5-0.8 cm, leaf blade olive green above, glabrescent, wooly white below, petioles sheathed, purple. Peduncle 15-40 cm long with woolly whitish pubescence. Heads calyculate, arranged in dichasial cymes, with a lateral bract 2.5-4.5 cm long. Heads 1.5 cm diameter, involucre convex with a row of oblong-lanceolate bracts, 6-8 × 1.2-1.6 mm, purple, wooly, with translucent membranous margins. Flowers lemon yellow. Achenes obovoid with a row of silky bristles. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 127, :name => "josei", :genus => { :id => 70, :name => "Senecio", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "310" }, :scientific => "Senecio josei", :author => "Senecio josei Sklenář", :tropicos => "100384077", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierba hasta de 60 cm. Hojas alternas, amontonadas hacia las puntas de las ramas, lineares, hasta de 50 × 5 mm, coriáceas, los márgenes revolutos, el envés densamente blanco-lanado.  Inflorescencias racemosas, hasta con 10 capítulos, el pedúnculo hasta de 6 cm, purpúreo. Capítulos discoides, hasta de 10 mm de largo, colgantes; involucro caliculado, purpúreo. Flores 30-45, tubulares, de color amarillo-verdoso; estilo bifurcado. Vilano de cerdas sedosas, blancas. ", :distribution_es => " Especie descrita en 2012, y registrada sólo en los páramos de Sabanilla, provincia de Loja y en Azuay.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 60 cm. Leaves alternate, crowded at tips of branches, linear, up to 50 × 5 mm, leathery, margins revolute, leaf blade densely white-wooly below. Inflorescences racemose, up to 10 heads, peduncle up to 6 cm, purple. Heads discoid, up to 10 mm long, nodding; involucre caliculate, purple. Flowers 30-45, tubular, greenish-yellow; style furcated. Pappus of silky, white bristles. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 128, :name => "rigida ", :genus => { :id => 6, :name => "Berberis", :family => { :id => 5, :name => "berberidaceae", :old_id => "38" }, :old_id => "39" }, :scientific => "Berberis rigida ", :author => "Berberis rigida Hieron.", :tropicos => "3500129", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos espinosos, hasta de 3 m de alto, con madera amarilla. Hojas alternas, amontonadas, hasta 3 cm de largo, brillantes en el haz y verde-blanquecinas en el envés, las nervaduras amarillentas en el haz, la punta espinosa, los márgenes espinosos. Inflorescencias en racimos colgantes, 5-8 cm de largo, el raquis y los pedicelos de un rosado oscuro. Flores de color amarillo brillante, teñidas de rosado o rojizo por fuera; alrededor de 10 mm de diámetro, con tépalos petaloides. Frutos subglobosos, carnosos, hasta 8 mm de largo, verdes, luego rojizos y finalmente de color negro-morado. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador, buena parte de las colecciones de los herbarios provienen del Azuay.", :description_en => "Spiny bushes, up to 3 m high, with yellow wood. Leaves alternate, crowded, up to 3 cm long, leaf blade shinny above, whitish-green below, venation yellow above, tip and margins spiny. Inflorescences in hanging racemes, 5-8 cm long, rachis and pedicels dark pink. Flowers bright yellow, tinged with pink or red on the outside, about 10 mm diameter, with petaloid tepals. Fruit subglobose, fleshy, up to 8 mm long, green, turning red and finally black-purple. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 129, :name => "nubigena ", :genus => { :id => 88, :name => "Eudema", :family => { :id => 10, :name => "brassicaceae", :old_id => "67" } }, :scientific => "Eudema nubigena ", :author => "Eudema nubigena Bonpl.", :tropicos => "4105058", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas acaulescentes, hasta de 3 cm de alto, que forman pequeñas almohadillas. Hojas basales en roseta, simples, espatuladas, hasta 10 mm de largo, los márgenes enteros, ciliados, con tricomas transparentes. Flores solitarias al final de las ramas; pétalos 4, alrededor de 3 mm de largo, blanco-crema, la base amarilla por dentro. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica de los Andes ecuatorianos, se encuentra prevalentemente sobre 4000 y hasta 4600 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Acaulescent herbs, up to 3 cm high, forming small cushions. Leaves in a basal rosette, simple, spatulate, up to 10 mm long, margins entire, ciliated, with translucent trichomes. Flowers solitary at the end of the branches; petals 4, about 3 mm long, white-cream, base yellow inside. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 130, :name => "cajasensis ", :genus => { :id => 65, :name => "Puya", :family => { :id => 37, :name => "bromeliaceae", :old_id => "289" }, :old_id => "290" }, :scientific => "Puya cajasensis ", :author => "Puya cajasensis Manzan. & W. Till", :tropicos => "50280625", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas sin tallo; hojas dispuestas en espiral, que forman una roseta basal. Hojas largas y angostamente triangulares, hasta 22 × 2,5 cm, la base dilatada, ancha y envainadora hasta 3 cm de ancho, el ápice largamente atenuado; coriáceas, rígidas, el envés glauco, los márgenes gruesamente espinoso-serrados, los dientes angostos, hasta 5 mm de largo, cafés, recurvados hacia arriba, espaciados a lo largo del margen. Inflorescencia simple, robusta, globosa, terminal, sobre un escapo erecto hasta 30 cm de alto, recubierto por brácteas muy traslapadas; brácteas anchamente ovadas, hasta 15 × 4 cm, el ápice de atenuado a largamente atenuado, los márgenes diminutamente espinosos; papiráceas y translúcidas, color pajizo-dorado; las brácteas de la inflorescencia, ovadas, reflexas; sépalos 3, hasta 15 mm de largo, ocultados por  las brácteas; pétalos 3,25 mm de largo, más o menos traslapados, de blanco-verdosos a verdosos. Fruto en cápsula, ovoide, alrededor de 15 mm. Especies similares: Puya pygmaea. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos húmedos del sur del Ecuador y norte del Perú. En el Ecuador ha sido registrada en las provincias de Azuay y Loja.", :description_en => "Stemless herbs; leaves spirally arranged forming a basal rosette. Leaves long, narrowly triangular, up to 22 × 2.5 cm, base dilated, wide and clasping up to 3 cm wide, apex long attenuated, leathery, stiff, glaucous below, margins coarsely spiny-serrated, teeth narrow, up to 5 mm long, brown, recurved, spaced along the margin. Inflorescence simple, robust, globose, terminal, on an erect scape up to 30 cm tall, covered with overlapping bracts; bracts broadly ovate, up to 15 × 4 cm, apex attenuate to long attenuate, margins spiny, papery and translucent, golden-straw color. Inflorescence bracts ovate, reflexed; sepals 3 to 15 mm long, concealed by bracts; petals 3.25 mm long, more or less overlapping, white-green to green. Fruit a capsule, ovoid, about 15 mm. Similar species: Puya pygmaea. ", :distribution_en => " S Ecuador to N Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 131, :name => "compacta", :genus => { :id => 65, :name => "Puya", :family => { :id => 37, :name => "bromeliaceae", :old_id => "289" }, :old_id => "290" }, :scientific => "Puya compacta", :author => "Puya compacta L.B. Sm.", :tropicos => "4303054", :color1 => { :id => 9, :name => "blue", :old_id => "127" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas gigantes, hasta de 1,2 m de alto con la inflorescencia policárpica, las hojas forman una roseta basal grande. Hojas lineares, 40-60 cm de largo, coriáceas, los márgenes serrados, espinosos; las espinas de 5 mm de largo. Inflorescencia elevada sobre un pedúnculo 40-70 × 2-3 cm, erecto, cubierto completamente por brácteas lanosas, traslapadas; la inflorescencia cilíndrica, 20-40 × 7 cm, compacta, con brácteas con indumento lanoso cinéreo. Flores actinomorfas, de color azul claro; pétalos 3, 4 cm de largo; anteras amarillas. Fruto en cápsula; semillas aladas. Especies similares: Puya clava-herculis, Puya maculata L.B. Sm. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador, restringida a la región austral. Debido a su estrecho rango de distribución y a que su hábitat está intervenido por quemas, es una especie considerada en peligro crítico (CR) de extinción.", :description_en => "Giant herbs, up to 1.2 m high with polycarpic inflorescence, the leaves forming a large basal rosette. Leaves linear, 40-60 cm long, leathery, serrated, margins thorny; thorns 5 mm long. Inflorescence raised on a stalk 40-70 × 2-3 cm, upright, completely covered by overlapping woolly bracts; inflorescence cylindrical, 20-40 × 7 cm, compact, woolly bracts ash-grey. Flowers actinomorphic, light blue; petals 3, 4 cm long; anthers yellow. Fruit a capsule; seeds winged. Similar species: Puya clava-herculis, Puya maculata. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 132, :name => "oellgaardii ", :genus => { :id => 44, :name => "Lysipomia", :family => { :id => 27, :name => "campanulaceae", :old_id => "198" }, :old_id => "199" }, :scientific => "Lysipomia oellgaardii ", :author => "Lysipomia oellgaardii Jeppesen", :tropicos => "5504406", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas rizomatosas. Hojas en rosetas acaulescentes, dispuestas en el ápice de los rizomas; hojas lustrosas, rígidas con la base ensanchada blanquecina, de 2 mm de ancho, lámina lanceolada de 5 a 8 mm de largo por 2 a 2,5 mm de ancho, margen con una estrecha banda hialina semejante a una callosidad; ápice terminado en un punto hialino. Flores solitarias casi ocultas por las hojas superiores; sépalos iguales, 1.5 mm de largo; corola zigomorfa, blanca, alrededor de 4 mm de largo, dispuesta en el centro de la roseta, débilmente bilabiada; los filamentos unidos en un tubo ± igual en longitud al tubo de la corola, las anteras negras. Cápsula papirácea campanulada 2,5 × 1,3 mm. Especies similares: Lysipomia vitreola. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica de los páramos del sur del Ecuador, en las provincias de Azuay y Loja entre 2850 y 4060 m. s.n.m.", :description_en => "Small rhizomatous herbs. Leaves acaulescent in rosettes, arranged at the apex of the rhizomes; leaves glossy, with whitish rigid expanded base, 2 mm wide, blade lanceolate, 5-8 × 2 to 2.5 mm, with a narrow hyaline margin like a callous; apex finishing in a hyaline point. Flowers solitary almost hidden by the upper leaves; sepals equal, 1.5 mm long. Corolla zygomorphic, white, about 4 mm long, arranged in the center of the rosette, weakly bilabiated; filaments joined into a tube ± equal in length to the corolla tube, anthers black. Capsule papery, campanulate, 2.5 × 1.3 mm. Similar species: Lysipomia vitreola. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to S Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 133, :name => "rhizomata", :genus => { :id => 44, :name => "Lysipomia", :family => { :id => 27, :name => "campanulaceae", :old_id => "198" }, :old_id => "199" }, :scientific => "Lysipomia rhizomata", :author => "Lysipomia rhizomata McVaugh", :tropicos => "5504407", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, arrosetadas, hasta de 4 cm de diámetro, crecen solitarias o en pequeños grupos. Hojas largamente lanceoladas, hasta 18 × 3 mm, muy angostas, el haz azul-morado, los márgenes ciliados. Flores numerosas en el centro de la roseta, pequeñas, hasta 8 mm de largo; corola blanca con 5 lóbulos; estambres unidos en un tubo de 5 mm, las anteras negras. Fruto en cápsula. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador, con distribución restringida a la provincia del Azuay.", :description_en => "Small herbs, in rosettes, up to 4 cm in diameter, solitary or in small groups. Leaves long lanceolate, up to 18 × 3 mm, very narrow, blue-purple upper leaf with ciliated margins. Numerous flowers in the center of the rosette, small, up to 8 mm long; white corolla 5-lobed; stamens connate in a tube 5 mm, anthers black. Fruit a capsule. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 134, :name => "sphagnophila subsp. variabilis ", :genus => { :id => 44, :name => "Lysipomia", :family => { :id => 27, :name => "campanulaceae", :old_id => "198" }, :old_id => "199" }, :scientific => "Lysipomia sphagnophila subsp. variabilis ", :author => "Lysipomia sphagnophila subsp. variabilis McVaugh", :tropicos => "5504411", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas con rizomas subterráneos profundos, los tallos cortos, hasta 2 cm. Hojas en una roseta basal, elípticas a oblanceoladas, hasta de 15 mm de largo, ovadas, ligeramente calloso-crenuladas, gruesas, con tintes morados, ciliadas. Flores numerosas en el centro de la roseta, hasta de 5 mm de largo, el cáliz morado, ciliado, la corola blanca o amarillo pálido, con 2 lóbulos diminutos dorsales y 3 ventrales, triangulares; estambres fusionados en una columna central. Especies similares: Lysipomia oellgaardii. ", :distribution_es => " Lysipomia sphagnophila se distribuye en los páramos desde el sur de Colombia hasta el norte del Perú, no obstante, la subespecie variabilis es endémica del sur del Ecuador y ha sido registrada en los páramos de Azuay y Loja.", :description_en => "Small herbs with deep underground rhizomes, stems short, up to 2 cm. Leaves in a basal rosette, elliptic to oblanceolate, up to 15 mm long, ovate, slightly callous-crenulated, thick, with purple tints, ciliated. Many flowers in the center of the rosette, up to 5 mm long, calyx purple, ciliate. Corolla white or pale yellow, with 2 minute dorsal lobes and 3 ventral triangular lobes; stamens fused in a central column. Similar species: Lysipomia oellgaardii. ", :distribution_en => " endemic S Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 135, :name => "bracteata ", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana bracteata ", :author => "Valeriana bracteata Benth.", :tropicos => "33500169", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, hasta de 10 cm de alto, fétidas. Hojas en una roseta basal, lanceolado-espatuladas, hasta de 5 cm de largo, gruesas, carnosas, la base dilatada en el pecíolo. Inflorescencia sobre un pedúnculo alrededor de 25 mm, capitada, hasta de 8 mm de largo, con 3 flores rodeadas por brácteas, las flores alrededor de 2 mm, con 4 lóbulos cortos, de color blanco con tintes morados; estambres 3. Fruto en aquenio alrededor de 2 mm, elipsoide, sin vilano. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Colombia a Ecuador. En el Ecuador se distribuye en los páramos entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Small herbs up to 10 cm high, fetid. Leaves in a basal rosette, spatulate-lanceolate, up to 5 cm long, thick, fleshy, base clasping the petiole. Inflorescence on a peduncule about 25 mm, capitate, up to 8 mm long, with 3 flowers surrounded by bracts, flowers about 2 mm, with 4 short lobes, white with purple tints; 3 stamens. Fruit an achene about 2 mm, ellipsoid, without pappus. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 136, :name => "hirtella ", :genus => { :id => 74, :name => "Valeriana", :family => { :id => 42, :name => "valerianaceae", :old_id => "323" }, :old_id => "324" }, :scientific => "Valeriana hirtella ", :author => "Valeriana hirtella Kunth", :tropicos => "33500208", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 5 m de alto. Tallos y ramas cuadrangulares, que pueden llegar hasta 10 cm de diámetro. Hojas caulinares simples, amontonadas hacia las partes apicales de las ramas, de lineares a elípticas, 1-6 × 0,2-0,8 cm, subcoriáceas; pecíolos 2-5 mm de largo. Inflorescencia paniculiforme, 2-23 × 1,5-17 cm. Flores ginodioicas; corola infundibuliforme, 1,5-2 mm de largo, generalmente de color blanco, ocasionalmente teñida de morado. Fruto en aquenio elíptico glabro, de 1-1,5 mm de largo, con vilano blanco de 2-4 mm de largo. Especies similares: Valeriana microphylla. ", :distribution_es => " Andes de Ecuador y Perú.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 5 m high. Stems and branches quadrangular,  reaching up to 10 cm diameter; stem simple; leaves crowded at the apical parts of the branches, linear to elliptic, 1-6 × 0.2-0.8 cm, subcoriaceous; petioles 2-5 mm long. Inflorescence paniculiform, 2-23 × 1.5 to 17 cm. Flowers gynodioecious; corolla infundibuliform, 1.5-2 mm long, usually white, occasionally tinged with purple. Fruit an elliptical glabrous achene, 1-1.5 mm long, with white pappus 2-4 mm long. Similar Species: Valeriana microphylla. ", :distribution_en => " Andes of Ecuador and Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 137, :name => "digyna", :genus => { :id => 89, :name => "Arenaria", :family => { :id => 11, :name => "caryophyllaceae", :old_id => "75" } }, :scientific => "Arenaria digyna", :author => "Arenaria digyna Willd. ex D.F.K. Schltdl.", :tropicos => "6301126", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas difusas, de procumbentes a suberectas, muy ramificadas, que forman tapices; glabras, hasta 5 cm de alto. Hojas opuestas, linear-oblongas, hasta 6 × 1-1,5 mm, glabras pero ciliadas en la superficie, el ápice agudo, los márgenes enteros, sésiles o cortamente pecioladas. Inflorescencia de flores solitarias, muy pequeñas, alrededor de 3-4 mm de largo, erectas, axilares o terminales, sobre pedicelos cortos; cáliz persistente, glabro; pétalos 5, lanceolados, glabros, blancos; anteras de color lila. Cápsula elíptica, 2 mm; semillas diminutas de color negro-grisáceo. ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador, Perú, Bolivia y Chile. En el Ecuador está registrada en Pichincha, Cotopaxi y Azuay.", :description_en => "Highly branched diffuse herbs, procumbent to suberect, forming cushions, glabrous, up to 5 cm tall. Leaves opposite, linear-oblong, up to 6 × 1-1.5 mm, ciliate on the surface, apex acute, margins entire, sessile or shortly petiolate. Inflorescence of solitary flowers, very small, about 3-4 mm long, erect, axillary or terminal on short pedicels; calyx persistent, glabrous; petals 5, lanceolate, glabrous, white; anthers purple. Capsule elliptical, 2 mm; seeds minute, black-gray. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Chile. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }] }
{ :id => 138, :name => "danguyi ", :genus => { :id => 14, :name => "Cerastium", :family => { :id => 11, :name => "caryophyllaceae", :old_id => "75" }, :old_id => "76" }, :scientific => "Cerastium danguyi ", :author => "Cerastium danguyi J.F. Macbr.", :tropicos => "6300618", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes hasta de 40 cm de alto, finamente pubescentes; tallos ascendentes. Hojas opuestas, linear-lanceoladas, 15-30 × 3-4 mm, conectadas en la base, densamente pubescentes, más o menos glandulosas, los márgenes enteros, revolutos. Inflorescencias contraídas, con pocas flores. Flores sobre pedicelos hasta 10 mm; cáliz profundamente 5-partido, hasta 6 mm, de color verde-claro; pétalos 5, alrededor de 8 mm de largo, que forman un tubo, el ápice emarginado-bilobado, blancos con finas líneas color lila. Cápsula 12 mm, membranácea, que contiene numerosas semillas redondeadas. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes de Colombia, Ecuador, Perú y Bolivia, entre 3200 y 4700 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs up to 40 cm tall, finely pubescent, stems ascending. Leaves opposite, linear-lanceolate, 15-30 × 3-4 mm, connected at the base, densely pubescent, more or less glandular, margins entire, revolute. Inflorescences contracted, with few flowers. Flowers on pedicels up to 10 mm; calyx deeply five-split, up to 6 mm, light green. Petals 5, about 8 mm long, forming a tube, apex emarginated, bilobed, white with fine purple lines. Capsule 12 mm, membranaceous, containing numerous rounded seeds. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 139, :name => "recurvata ", :genus => { :id => 90, :name => "Stellaria", :family => { :id => 11, :name => "caryophyllaceae", :old_id => "75" } }, :scientific => "Stellaria recurvata ", :author => "Stellaria recurvata Willd. ex D.F.K. Schltdl.", :tropicos => "6300816", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, ascendentes, hasta de 1 m de largo, los tallos pubescentes. Hojas opuestas, cortamente pecioladas, triangulares y cordadas en la base. Flores muy conspicuas hasta de 15 mm de diámetro, largamente pediceladas; cáliz verde; pétalos 5 profundamente bipartidos, más largos que los sépalos, blancos; estambres de tecas color café-amarillento. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica de los Andes ecuatorianos. Se distribuye desde los 2500 hasta los 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, ascending, up to 1 m long, pubescent stems. Leaves opposite, shortly stalked, triangular and cordate at base. Flowers showy up to 15 mm in diameter, long-pedicelate; calyx green; petals 5, deeply bipartite, longer than sepals, white; stamens yellowish-brown. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 140, :name => "azuayae", :genus => { :id => 91, :name => "Carex", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Carex azuayae", :author => "Carex azuayae Steyerm.", :tropicos => "9910400", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :description_es => "Hierbas semiacuáticas, erectas hasta de 40 cm de alto. Hojas lineares, aplanadas y duras, con vaina glabra. Inflorescencia terminal con espiguillas erectas pedunculadas de color café brillante. Flores abrazadas por escamas dispuestas en espiral, las mismas que son de color negro con una franja verde-brillante en el centro. El culmo sobresale de las hojas. Especies similares: Carex toreadora, Carex jamesonii. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador.", :description_en => "Semiaquatic herbs, erect, up to 40 cm high. Leaves linear, flat and hard, with glabrous sheath. Terminal inflorescence with pedunculated erect spikelets, bright-brown. Flowers embraced by spirally arranged scales, black with bright-green center. The culm longer than the leaves. Similar species: Carex toreadora, Carex jamesonii. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }] }
{ :id => 141, :name => "pichinchensis ", :genus => { :id => 91, :name => "Carex", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Carex pichinchensis ", :author => "Carex pichinchensis Kunth", :tropicos => "9902288", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 1 m de alto, fasciculadas en la base, los tallos triangulares, estriados, glabros, los ángulos escabrosos y cortantes. Hojas graminiformes, muy largas y angostas, hasta de 8 mm de ancho, rígidas, estriadas; el nervio principal muy prominente en el envés y la hoja doblada a lo largo de este, la base envainadora, rojiza. Inflorescencias colgantes de pedúnculos delgados, en espigas compuestas, masculinas y femeninas, cilíndricas, cada una hasta de 5 cm, negro-purpúreas, con brácteas escamiformes imbricadas, lanceoladas, hasta 5 mm, carinadas, negro-purpúreas, los márgenes claros, membranáceas. Flores modificadas, escuamiformes, los estambres y los estilos de un amarillo claro. Especies similares: Carex jamesonii Boott. ", :distribution_es => " Montañas andinas de Colombia a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 1 m high, fasciculate at base, stems triangular, striated, glabrous, angles rough and sharp. Leaves graminiform, very long and narrow, up to 8 mm wide, stiff, ridged, midrib very prominent below, the blade folded along it, base sheathed reddish. Inflorescences hanging from thin peduncules, in composite spikes, male and female, cylindrical, each up to 5 cm, black-purple, with imbricated squamiform bracts, lanceolate, up to 5 mm, keeled, black-purple, margins light, membranous. Flowers modified, squamiform, stamens and styles light yellow. Similar species: Carex jamesonii. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 142, :name => "pygmaea ", :genus => { :id => 91, :name => "Carex", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Carex pygmaea ", :author => "Carex pygmaea Boeckeler", :tropicos => "9905355", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas de 20 cm de alto, rizomatosas. Hojas agrupadas en la base, lineares, la lámina canaliculada, hasta 3 mm de ancho, la vaina glabra con el margen transparente. Inflorescencia terminal, con varias espiguillas pedunculadas de color café-marrón. Culmo más corto que las hojas. Flor abrazada por una escama persistente. Flores dispuestas abundantemente en la espiga, las flores estaminadas reducidas a 3 estambres de color amarillo-crema, las flores pistiladas con un solo ovario, el estilo con 2 estigmas cortos que salen a través de un orificio en el ápice del periginio aplanado. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Costa Rica a Ecuador.", :description_en => "Herbs, 20 cm high, rhizomatous. Leaves clustered at the base, linear, blade canaliculate up to 3 mm wide, sheath glabrous with translucent margin. Inflorescence terminal, with several pedunculated brown spikelets. Culm shorter than the leaves. Flowers subtended by a persistent scale. Flowers arranged in a spike, the staminate flowers reduced to 3 stamens yellow-cream colored, pistillate flowers with a single ovary, style with 2 short stigmas exserted through the apex of the flattened perigynium. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 143, :name => "toreadora", :genus => { :id => 91, :name => "Carex", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Carex toreadora", :author => "Carex toreadora Steyerm.", :tropicos => "9910405", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, subacuáticas, rizomatosas, de 25 cm de alto. Hojas escasamente agrupadas, revestidas con un tegumento transparente, canaliculadas, de 6 cm de ancho y 25 cm de alto. Inflorescencia terminal, de color café-marrón, con varias espiguillas sésiles, abrazada por una bráctea de 6 mm de largo con la misma apariencia que las escamas. Culmo hasta de 20 cm de alto, en algunos casos están a la misma altura que las hojas. Flores agrupadas en espiguillas pequeñas y ovoideas. Periginio de 4 mm de largo, de color amarillo con el ápice rojo-ladrillo; estigma café oscuro. Aquenio lenticular de color amarillo pálido. Especies similares: Carex azuayae. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador, se ha registrado en los páramos de las provincias del Azuay y Pichincha, entre 3700 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial, subacquatic, rhizomatous herbs, 25 cm high. Leaves sparsely grouped, coated with a transparent tegument, canaliculated, 6 cm wide and 25 cm high. Inflorescence terminal, brown, with several sessile spikelets, subtended by a bract 6 mm long similar to the scales. Culm up to 20 cm high, in some cases as tall as the leaves. Flowers grouped in small and ovoid spikelets. Perigynium 4 mm long, yellow with brick-red apex; stigma dark brown. Lenticular achene pale yellow. Similar species: Carex azuayae. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 144, :name => "tristicha ", :genus => { :id => 91, :name => "Carex", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Carex tristicha ", :author => "Carex tristicha Boeckeler", :tropicos => "9910111", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, hasta de 10 cm de alto, fasciculadas en la base y con forma de abanico. Hojas graminiformes, largamente lanceoladas, hasta de 4 mm de ancho, rígidos, estriados, el nervio principal muy prominente en el envés y la hoja doblada a lo largo de este, la base envainadora. Inflorescencias en espigas compuestas masculinas y femeninas pequeñas, compactas, hasta de 2 cm, con brácteas escamiformes imbricadas, lanceoladas, hasta 5 mm, carinadas, largamente apiculadas, de un verde claro, hialinas, membranáceas. Flores modificadas escuamiformes. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos del Ecuador y Colombia.", :description_en => "Small herbs up to 10 cm high, fasciculate at the base and fan-shaped. Leaves graminiform, long lanceolate, up to 4 mm wide, stiff, striate, midrib very prominent below and the blade folded along it, base sheathed. Inflorescences in compound male and female spikes, small, compact, up to 2 cm, with squamiform imbricated bracts, lanceolate, up to 5 mm, keeled, largely apiculate, light green, hyaline, membranous. Flowers modified, squamiform. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 145, :name => "acicularis ", :genus => { :id => 92, :name => "Eleocharis", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Eleocharis acicularis ", :author => "Eleocharis acicularis (L.) Roem. & Schult.", :tropicos => "9900077", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, cespitosas, de 20 cm de alto. Hojas pequeñas, 8 mm de largo, glabras, que abrazan la base del culmo. Inflorescencia terminal, pardo-rojiza. Culmos ligeramente arqueados, (1)4-11(22) cm de largo; espiguilla (1,5) 3,5 (6) mm, ovoide; las escamas dispuestas helicoidalmente, de color verde en el centro y pardo-rojizo a los lados. Flores estaminadas con 3 estambres, las anteras amarillentas; estilo con 3 estigmas. Fruto, aquenio obovoide, verdoso. Especies similares: Isolepis cernua (Vahl) Roem. & Schult. ", :distribution_es => " Se distribuye en toda América, inclusive en el Ártico. En el Ecuador se encuentra hasta los 4300 m.", :description_en => "Perennial, caespitose herbs, 20 cm high. Leaves small, 8 mm long, glabrous, clasping the base of the culm. Inflorescence terminal, reddish-brown. Culms slightly arched, (1)4-11(22) cm long; spikelet (1.5) 3.5 (6) mm, ovoid; scales helicoidally arranged, green in the center and red-brown on the sides. Staminate flowers with 3 stamens, anthers yellowish; style with 3 stigmas. Fruit an obovoid achene, greenish. Similar species: Isolepis cernua. ", :distribution_en => " American continent.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 146, :name => "inversa ", :genus => { :id => 93, :name => "Oreobolopsis", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Oreobolopsis inversa ", :author => "Oreobolopsis inversa Dhooge & Goetgh.", :tropicos => "50221268", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas rizomatosas, que crecen formando pequeñas macollas de 10 a 30 cm de alto. Culmos redondeados de 10 a 25 cm de largo por 0,6 a 0,8 mm de diámetro; hojas graminiformes, más cortas que los culmos, lámina triangular-cilíndrica, rígida, estriada, de 5 a 11 cm de largo por 0,5 a 0,7 mm de ancho, la base envainadora y lígula membranosa. Inflorescencias en una espiga compacta de 4-6 mm de largo por 2-3 mm de ancho, con brácteas escamiformes alrededor 3 mm, de un café claro, hialinas, membranáceas. Flores bisexuales pequeñas, con 6 escamas cortas, 3 estambres con largos filamentos y anteras de 1 mm de largo, ovario con 3 carpelos, estilo con tres ramas papilosas color crema. Fruto, un aquenio pequeño de color café. Especies similares: Trichophorum rigidum. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos del Ecuador y Perú, entre 3700 y 4400 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Rhizomatous herbs growing in small clumps, 10-30 cm high. Culms rounded, 10-25 cm long by 0.6 -0.8 mm in diameter. Leaves graminiform, shorter than the culms, triangular-cylindrical, blade rigid, striate, 5-11 cm long by 0.5-0.7 mm wide, base sheathed and ligule membranous. Inflorescences in a compact spike 4-6 × 2-3 mm, with squamiform bracts about 3 mm, light brown, hyaline, membranous. Flowers bisexual, small, with 6 short scales, stamens 3, with long filaments and anthers 1 mm long, ovary with 3 carpels, style with 3 cream papillose branches. Fruit a small achene, brown. Similar species: Trichophorum rigidum. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 147, :name => "vulcani ", :genus => { :id => 94, :name => "Rhynchospora", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Rhynchospora vulcani ", :author => "Rhynchospora vulcani Boeckeler", :tropicos => "9900798", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 0,6 m de alto, rizomatosas, fasciculadas en la base, los tallos triangulares, estriados, los ángulos escabrosos y cortantes. Hojas graminiformes, muy largas y angostas, hasta 5 mm de ancho, rígidas, estriadas, el nervio principal muy prominente en el envés y algunas hojas dobladas a lo largo de este, la base envainadora. Inflorescencias grandes, paniculadas, densas, en espigas compuestas, hasta de 6 cm, cilíndricas, café-rojizas, masculinas y femeninas, con brácteas escamiformes imbricadas, lanceoladas, hasta 6 mm, carinadas, largamente apiculadas, membranáceas. Flores modificadas, escamosas, los estilos muy largos; los estambres de un amarillo claro. Especies similares: Rynchospora ruiziana Boeckeler. ", :distribution_es => " Desde los Andes de Bolivia hasta Colombia y en Centroamérica hasta México.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 0.6 m high, rhizomatous, fasciculate at base, stems triangular, striated, angles rough and sharp. Leaves graminiform, very long and narrow, up to 5 mm wide, stiffed, ridged, the midrib prominent below and some blades folded along it, base sheathed. Inflorescences paniculate, large, dense, in composite spikes, up to 6 cm, cylindrical, red-brown, male and female, with imbricated squamiform bracts, lanceolate, up to 6 mm, keeled, largely apiculate, membranous. Flowers modified, scaly, styles very long; stamens light yellow. Similar species: Rynchospora ruiziana. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 148, :name => "tenuis ", :genus => { :id => 95, :name => "Uncinia", :family => { :id => 40, :name => "cyperaceae", :old_id => "306" } }, :scientific => "Uncinia tenuis ", :author => "Uncinia tenuis Poepp. ex Kunth", :tropicos => "9903475", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, cespitosas, hasta de 25 cm de alto. Hojas lineares de hasta 25 cm de largo, 2 mm de ancho, glabras, los márgenes cortantes, agrupadas cerca de la base, aplanadas, la vaina ligulada. Inflorescencia terminal en espiga, 4-5 cm de largo, de color verde-rojizo. Flores unisexuales, abrazadas por una escama persistente; flores estaminadas en la parte superior; flores pistiladas en la parte inferior, más numerosas que las flores estaminadas. Periginio 4 × 2 mm, del ápice del cual salen los 3 estigmas de color vino y la raquilla distalmente uncinada de 5-6 mm de largo, tiene la forma de un verdadero gancho que facilita la dispersión de las semillas. Aquenio trígono, ovoide, de 2,5 mm de largo. Especies similares: Uncinia hamata (Sw.) Urb. ", :distribution_es => " Centro y Sudamérica, desde México hasta Chile y Argentina. En el Ecuador se distribuye en la región andina entre 3000 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial, caespitose herbs, up to 25 cm high. Leaves linear up to 25 cm long, 2 mm wide, glabrous, grouped near the base, flattened, ligulate, margins sharp. Terminal inflorescence in spike, 4-5 cm long, green-red. Unisexual flowers subtended by a persistent scale; staminate flowers distal; pistillate flowers proximal, more numerous than male flowers. Perigynium 4 × 2 mm, apex with 3 stigmas wine color and distally uncinated rachilla 5-6 mm long, hook-like form that facilitates true seed dispersal. Achene trigonous, ovoid, 2.5 mm long. Similar species: Uncinia hamata. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Chile and Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 149, :name => "lasioglottis ", :genus => { :id => 96, :name => "Elaphoglossum", :family => { :id => 46, :name => "dryopteridaceae" } }, :scientific => "Elaphoglossum lasioglottis ", :author => "Elaphoglossum lasioglottis Mickel", :tropicos => "26611646", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos rupestres, el rizoma rastrero, densamente escamoso. Hojas con el pecíolo articulado a filopodios más oscuros que los pecíolos. Lámina linear, densamente escamosa; las escamas diferentes a las del tallo, de color plateado translúcido en el haz y café translucido en el envés. Soros de color pardo. ", :distribution_es => " De Colombia a Bolivia. En el Ecuador se ha registrado sobre los 3700 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Rock ferns, rhizome creeping, densely scaly. Leaves with petiole articulated to a phyllopodium, darker than the petioles. Blade linear, densely scaly, different scales from the ones of the stem, translucent silvery on leaf blade above and translucent brown below. Sori brown. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 150, :name => "lingua ", :genus => { :id => 96, :name => "Elaphoglossum", :family => { :id => 46, :name => "dryopteridaceae" } }, :scientific => "Elaphoglossum lingua ", :author => "Elaphoglossum lingua (C. Presl) Brack.", :tropicos => "26610790", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos terrestres, algunas veces epifitos que crecen sobre los troncos de Polylepis, con rizomas largos y pueden crecer hasta 40 cm de alto. Hojas oblongo-elípticas, rígidas, con la nervadura central conspicua, el haz densamente tomentoso, las nervaduras paralelas; pecíolo delgado, lustroso. Soros acrosticoides de color café-ferrugíneo. Esporas de color pardo. Elaphoglossum lingua, se reconoce por sus rizomas largamente rastreros provistos de pequeñas escamas de color negro. ", :distribution_es => " De Costa Rica a Bolivia. Ampliamente distribuido en el Ecuador, entre 500 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Terrestrial ferns, sometimes epiphytic growing on trunks of Polylepis, with long rhizomes up to 40 cm high. Leaves oblong-elliptic, rigid, with the midrib conspicuous, blade densely tomentose above, ribs parallel; petiole thin, glossy. Acrosticoid sori brown-ferruginous. Spores brown. Elaphoglossum lingua is recognized by its long creeping rhizomes with small black scales. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 17, :name => "esmeraldas" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }] }
{ :id => 151, :name => "orbiculatum", :genus => { :id => 97, :name => "Polystichum", :family => { :id => 46, :name => "dryopteridaceae" } }, :scientific => "Polystichum orbiculatum", :author => "Polystichum orbiculatum (Desv.) J. Rémy & Fée", :tropicos => "26612211", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos terrestres, con hojas muy estrechas. Rizoma de 2-4 cm de diámetro, no ramificado. Escamas lanceoladas. Hojas hasta de 35 cm de alto, 2 pinnado-crenulado; pinnas hasta 4×1 cm, oblicuas, las pínnulas obtusas, marcadamente revolutas. Raquis sin una yema prolífera, escamas del raquis anaranjado-amarillentas, descolorido cuando envejecen. Soros abaxiales sobre las nervaduras de color café. Especies similares: Polystichum spp. ", :distribution_es => " De Mesoamérica a Bolivia. En el Ecuador se distribuye en los picos más altos, hasta 5000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Terrestrial ferns, with very narrow leaves. Rhizome 2-4 cm diameter, unbranched, scales lanceolate. Leaves up to 35 cm high, 2 pinnately crenulate; pinnae up to 4 x 1 cm, oblique, pinnules obtuse, strongly revolute. Rachis without proliferous bud, rachis scales yellow-orange, paler with age. Abaxial sori on the veins brown. ", :distribution_en => " Mesoamerica to Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 152, :name => "rupestris", :genus => { :id => 21, :name => "Ephedra", :family => { :id => 14, :name => "ephedraceae", :old_id => "101" }, :old_id => "102" }, :scientific => "Ephedra rupestris", :author => "Ephedra rupestris Benth.", :tropicos => "14300030", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 50 cm de alto, densamente ramificados, color verde oliva; tallos erectos con estrías longitudinales. Hojas reducidas a escamas en anillos espaciados a lo largo del tallo, hasta de 3 mm de largo, color rojo-rosado. Las estructuras reproductivas se llaman estróbilos y son un conjunto de hojas modificadas (brácteas) gruesas, hasta de 8 mm de largo, color verde con rojo-rosado, amarillo o anaranjado, los estróbilos masculinos producen polen, los femeninos llevan óvulos. Las semillas amarillo-anaranjadas están envueltas por las brácteas engrosadas y carnosas, color rojo rosado. ", :distribution_es => " Ampliamente distribuida en los Andes desde Ecuador hasta Argentina.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 50 cm tall, densely branched, olive green. Stems erect with longitudinal grooves. Leaves reduced to scales in rings spaced along the stem, up to 3 mm long, red-pink. The reproductive structures called strobili are a set of modified thick leaves (bracts), up to 8 mm long, green with red-pink, yellow or orange, male strobili produce pollen, female ones carry ovules. The yellow-orange seeds are enveloped by thickened bracts, fleshy, pinkish-red. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Argentina.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 153, :name => "amoena ", :genus => { :id => 98, :name => "Gaultheria", :family => { :id => 13, :name => "ericaceae", :old_id => "91" } }, :scientific => "Gaultheria amoena ", :author => "Gaultheria amoena A. C. Sm.", :tropicos => "12303731", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos enanos, con frecuencia reptantes, rara vez hasta 30 cm de alto. Hojas alternas, de elípticas a subredondeadas, hasta de 20 mm de largo, coriáceas, los márgenes aserrados; pecíolo alrededor de 2 mm. Flores solitarias, los pedicelos 6–10 mm; cáliz alrededor de 5 mm; corola urceolada, alrededor de 7 mm de largo, con 5 lóbulos, de un rosado claro a rosado oscuro; estambres 10. Fruto en cápsula, 5-valvada, rodeada por el tejido carnoso del cáliz acrescente, que da la apariencia de ser una baya, redondeada, alrededor de 8 mm de diámetro, blanca con tintes rojizos. ", :distribution_es => " De Costa Rica a Perú.", :description_en => "Dwarf shrubs, often creeping, rarely up to 30 cm high. Leaves alternate, elliptical to subrounded, up to 20 mm long, leathery, margins serrate. Petiole about 2 mm. Flowers solitary, pedicels 6-10 mm; calyx about 5 mm; corolla urceolate, about 7 mm long, 5-lobed, light pink to dark pink. Stamens 10. Fruit a capsule, 5-valvate, surrounded by fleshy accrescent calyx tissue, which gives the appearance of being a berry, rounded, about 8 mm in diameter, white with reddish tints. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 154, :name => "pilosus ", :genus => { :id => 99, :name => "Paepalanthus", :family => { :id => 47, :name => "eriocaulaceae" } }, :scientific => "Paepalanthus pilosus ", :author => "Paepalanthus pilosus (Kunth) Kunth", :tropicos => "12400367", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 8 cm de alto, las hojas agrupadas en rosetas basales forman almohadillas pequeñas. Tallos 2–5 cm. Hojas hasta de 20 × 1–2 mm, lanceolado-lineares, glabras con el ápice agudo. Pedúnculos hasta de 8 cm de largo, rígidos, pajizos. Cabezuelas hasta de 5 mm de diámetro, de color blanco-ceniza, solitarias al final del pedúnculo. Flósculos estaminados con los sépalos ovados; tubo de la corola blanco, glabro, las anteras blancas. Flósculos pistilados con los sépalos ovados, negruzco; pétalos espatulados-obovados, de color blanco. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia, Costa Rica, Ecuador, Panamá, Perú, Venezuela.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 8 cm high, the leaves grouped in basal rosettes and forming small cushions. Stems 2-5 cm. Leaves up to 20 × 1-2mm, lanceolate-linear, glabrous with acute apex. Peduncle up to 8 cm long, rigid, straw-colored. Flower heads up to 5 mm in diameter, white-ash, solitary at the end of the peduncle. Staminate flowers with ovate sepals; corolla tube white, glabrous, anthers white. Pistillate flowers with ovate sepals, blackish; petals spatulate-obovate, white. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Colombia, Venezuela, Ecuador, Perú.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 18, :name => "los ríos" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }] }
{ :id => 155, :name => "tauris ", :genus => { :id => 43, :name => "Lupinus", :family => { :id => 26, :name => "fabaceae", :old_id => "194" }, :old_id => "195" }, :scientific => "Lupinus tauris ", :author => "Lupinus tauris Benth.", :tropicos => "13037130", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos erectos hasta de 2 m de alto. Hojas alternas, digitadas, en la base del pecíolo existen dos brácteas estipulares, compuestas entre 5 y 7 folíolos, los folíolos lanceolados de alrededor de 1 cm de largo, ligeramente pubescentes. Inflorescencia terminal, flores hasta de 10 mm de largo, papilionáceas, de color azul-morado con tintes magenta, violeta y blanco. Fruto, una vaina hasta de 3 cm de largo, presenta pubescencia blanca y contiene hasta 5 semillas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador entre los 3000 y 3500 m. Se ha registrado en las provincias de Azuay, Cañar, Carchi, Imbabura, Loja y Pichincha.", :description_en => "Erect shrubs up to 2 m high. Leaves alternate, digitated, at base of petiole two stipular bracts, composed of 5 to 7 leaflets, leaflets lanceolate about 1 cm long, slightly pubescent. Inflorescences terminal. Flowers up to 10 mm long, papilionaceous, blue-purple, tinged with magenta, violet and white. Fruit a legume up to 3 cm long, with white pubescence, containing up to 5 seeds. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 17, :name => "esmeraldas" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 156, :name => "limoselloides ", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella limoselloides ", :author => "Gentianella limoselloides (Kunth) Fabris", :tropicos => "13801749", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, hasta de 5 cm de alto, solitarias o en pequeños grupos. Hojas opuestas y amontonadas en la base, espatuladas, hasta 25 mm de largo. Flores solitarias, elevadas sobre un pedúnculo floral hasta 50 mm de largo, el cáliz hasta de 8 mm, con un tubo corto y 5 lóbulos triangulares, largos; la corola hasta 15 mm, los 5 pétalos erectos, color blanco con tintes lilas y nervios violetas; estambres 5. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador, en donde se encuentra ampliamente distribuida en los páramos entre 2500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Small herbs, up to 5 cm tall, solitary or in small groups. Leaves opposite, crowded at base, spatulate, up to 25 mm long. Flowers solitary, on a peduncule up to 50 mm long. Calyx up to 8 mm, with a short tube and 5 triangular long lobes. Corolla up to 15 mm, 5 erect petals, white with purple tints and violet nerves. Stamens 5. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 157, :name => "minima ", :genus => { :id => 33, :name => "Halenia", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "156" }, :scientific => "Halenia minima ", :author => "Halenia minima C. K. Allen", :tropicos => "13803128", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, en floración alcanzan máximo 15 cm de alto, con numerosos tallos, de decumbentes a erectos. Hojas de los tallos vegetativos en una roseta basal, las de los tallos floríferos opuestas a lo largo del corto tallo, angostamente elípticas, hasta 1 cm de largo; pecíolos hasta de 2 cm de largo. Flores solitarias o de 2 a 7, péndulas u horizontales, reunidas en una cima umbeloide, alrededor de 20 mm de largo, color verde-amarillo claro; los pedicelos delgados hasta de 20 mm, el cáliz alrededor de 5 mm, los lóbulos muy cortos, la corola hasta 7 mm, los espolones divergentes, alrededor de 4 mm de largo; estambres 5. Especies similares: Halenia taruga-gasso. ", :distribution_es => " Especie endémica del Ecuador, registrada en páramos de las provincias de Azuay, Loja y Morona Santiago entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Small herbs, up to 15 cm high when flowering, with numerous stems, decumbent to erect. Leaves pf vegetative stems in a basal rosette, those in flowering stems opposite along the short stems, narrowly elliptic, up to 1 cm long. Petioles up to 2 cm long. Flowers solitary or 2 to 7, horizontal or pendulous, in a cymose umbel, about 20 mm long, light green-yellow. Thin pedicels up to 20 mm, calyx around 5 mm, very short lobes, corolla up to 7 mm, spurs diverging, about 4 mm long, stamens 5. Similar species: Halenia taruga-gasso. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 158, :name => "taruga-gasso ", :genus => { :id => 33, :name => "Halenia", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "156" }, :scientific => "Halenia taruga-gasso ", :author => "Halenia taruga-gasso Gilg", :tropicos => "13800325", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas pequeñas, 10-25 cm de alto, con numerosos tallos, de decumbentes a erectos. Hojas de los tallos vegetativos en una roseta basal, las de los tallos floríferos opuestas a lo largo del corto tallo, angostamente de elípticas a lineares, hasta 15 mm de largo; pecíolo 2–20 mm. Flores solitarias o en cimas umbeloides de 2 a 8, péndulas u horizontales, hasta de 5 cm de largo, color verde-amarillo claro, el cáliz alrededor 7 mm, la corola hasta 12 mm, los espolones divergentes, hasta de 8 mm de largo. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del sur del Ecuador, registrada en las provincias de Azuay, Cañar, Loja, Morona Santiago, El Oro y Zamora, entre 2500 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Small herbs, 10-25 cm high, with numerous stems, decumbent to erect. Leaves on vegetative stems in a basal rosette, those in flowering stems opposite along the short stem, narrowly elliptic to linear, up to 15 mm long; petiole 2-20 mm. Flowers solitary or in umbeloid cymes of 2 to 8, pendulous or horizontal, up to 5 cm long, light green-yellow, calyx around 7 mm, corolla up to 12 mm, spurs diverging, up to 8 mm long. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 159, :name => "maniculatum ", :genus => { :id => 30, :name => "Geranium", :family => { :id => 20, :name => "geraniaceae", :old_id => "143" }, :old_id => "144" }, :scientific => "Geranium maniculatum ", :author => "Geranium maniculatum H. E. Moore", :tropicos => "13900971", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, de 2-4 cm de largo, el tallo vegetativo corto. Hojas en una roseta basal, obovadas en contorno, hasta 1.2×1.6 cm, profundamente palmatidivididas en 5 segmentos, el más grande, el central; cada segmento lanceolado, con 1-3 cerdas apicales, el nervio principal elevado en el envés, membranáceas, glabras, brillantes por el haz. Flores solitarias en el centro de la roseta, sobre un pedicelo corto, alrededor de 10 mm, tomentoso, los sépalos alrededor de 6 mm de largo, lanceolados, verdes; los pétalos 5, alrededor de 8 mm de largo, oblongos, erecto-patentes, enteros, glabros, color de blanco a rosado pálido con el centro verde-amarillento, los 5 nervios más oscuros; estambres 10, las anteras amarillentas. Frutos alrededor de 8 mm de largo, erectos, café-rojizos, que proyectan las semillas. Especies similares: Geranium sibbaldioides. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Colombia hasta Perú. En el Ecuador se distribuye en la zona de páramo entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, 2-4 cm long, vegetative stem short. Leaves in a basal rosette, obovate in outline, up to 1.2 × 1.6 cm, deeply palmatidivided into 5 segments, the largest is the central one, each segment lanceolate, with 1-3 apical bristles, midrib elevated on the surface below, glabrous, membranous, bright green ablove. Solitary flowers in the center of the rosette on a short pedicel, about 10 mm, tomentose, sepals about 6 mm long, lanceolate, green. Petals 5, about 8 mm long, oblong, erect-patent, entire, glabrous, white to pale pink with yellow-green center, the 5 ribs darker; stamens 10, anthers yellow. Fruit about 8 mm long, erect, reddish-brown, projecting the seeds. Similar species: Geranium sibbaldioides. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 160, :name => "sibbaldioides subsp. sibbaldoides", :genus => { :id => 30, :name => "Geranium", :family => { :id => 20, :name => "geraniaceae", :old_id => "143" }, :old_id => "144" }, :scientific => "Geranium sibbaldioides subsp. sibbaldoides", :author => "Geranium sibbaldioides Benth. subsp. sibbaldoides", :tropicos => "50182116", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, hasta de 4 cm de alto, forman tapetes pequeños, el tallo vegetativo corto. Hojas en una roseta basal, de contorno poligonal, hasta 17 mm de ancho, profundamente palmatidivididas en 5 segmentos, blanco-pilosos en ambas superficies, el lóbulo más grande el central, cada segmento de lanceolado a oblancelado, hasta 7 mm de largo, el ápice rojizo, membranáceos; pecíolo hasta de 18 mm, delgado, blanco-piloso. Flores solitarias en el centro de la roseta, sobre un pedicelo alrededor 10 mm, piloso; los sépalos alrededor de 6 mm de largo, lanceolados, verdes, con cerdas apicales, los pétalos 5, alrededor de 5 mm de largo, oblongos, erecto-patentes, enteros, glabros, color blanco o rosado pálido con el centro verde-amarillento, los 5 nervios más oscuros, morados; estambres 10, las anteras amarillentas. Frutos alrededor de 5 mm de largo, erectos, café-rojizos, que proyectan las semillas. Especies similares: Geranium maniculatum. ", :distribution_es => " La especie desde Venezuela hasta Bolivia. La subespecie se distribuye en la región andina desde el sur de Colombia hasta el norte del Perú, entre 2700 y 5000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, up to 4 cm tall, forming small cushions, vegetative stem short. Leaves in a basal rosette of polygonal contour, up to 17 mm wide, deeply palmatidivided into 5 segments, white-pilose on both surfaces, the largest lobe is the central one, each segment lanceolate to oblanceolate, up to 7 mm long, apex reddish, membranaceous, petiole up to 18 mm, thin, white-pilose. Solitary flowers on the center of the rosette on a stalk about 10 mm, pilose. Sepals about 6 mm long, lanceolate, green with apical bristles, petals 5, about 5 mm long, oblong, erect-patent, entire, glabrous, white or pale pink with yellow-green center, 5 nerves darker, purple. Stamens 10, anthers yellow. Fruit about 5 mm long, erect, reddish-brown, projecting the seeds. Similar species: Geranium maniculatum. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 161, :name => "decandrum ", :genus => { :id => 37, :name => "Hypericum", :family => { :id => 23, :name => "hypericaceae", :old_id => "170" }, :old_id => "171" }, :scientific => "Hypericum decandrum ", :author => "Hypericum decandrum Turcz.", :tropicos => "7801435", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 60 cm de alto; tallos de color marrón-rojizo o marrón-amarillento, la corteza exfoliable en escamas irregulares, la ramificación escasa, con 4-6 alineadas. Hojas sésiles, oblanceoladas, 4-15 × 0,7-3 mm, ligeramente coriáceas, apretadas y que se traslapan entre sí. Inflorescencia terminal, las flores solitarias hasta de 20 mm de diámetro, con los pétalos brillantes de color amarillo; estambres amarillos. Cápsula hasta de 5 mm de largo; semillas diminutas. ", :distribution_es => " Andes del Ecuador y norte del Perú, entre 2500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 60 cm tall; stems reddish-brown or yellowish-brown, bark exfoliating into irregular scales, scarcely branching, with 4-6 aligned. Leaves sessile, oblanceolate, 4-15 × 0.7-3 mm, slightly leathery, tight and overlapping each other. Terminal inflorescences of solitary flowers up to 20 mm in diameter, with bright yellow petals; stamens yellow. Capsule to 5 mm long; seeds minute. ", :distribution_en => " Andes of Ecuador and northern Peru, between 2500 and 4500 m AMSL.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 162, :name => "quitense", :genus => { :id => 37, :name => "Hypericum", :family => { :id => 23, :name => "hypericaceae", :old_id => "170" }, :old_id => "171" }, :scientific => "Hypericum quitense", :author => "Hypericum quitense R. Keller", :tropicos => "7800326", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos muy ramificados, hasta de 1 m de alto; tallo leñoso de color pardo-rojizo. Hojas opuestas, decusadas, angostamente ovadas, hasta de 8 mm de largo, subsésiles. Flores solitarias de color amarillo-anaranjado, abundantes en la parte terminal de pequeñas ramitas, hasta 1 cm de diámetro. Fruto capsular de 4 mm de largo, de color rojizo. Especies similares: Hypericum spp. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador, distribuida ampliamente en el centro y sur de los Andes, en varios hábitats entre los 2000 y 4050 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Profusely branched shrubs, up to 1 m high; stem woody, reddish-brown. Leaves opposite, decussate, narrowly ovate, up to 8 mm long, subsessile. Solitary flowers yellow-orange, abundant in terminal twigs, up to 1 cm in diameter. Capsular fruit 4 mm long, reddish. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 163, :name => "andina", :genus => { :id => 100, :name => "Isoetes", :family => { :id => 48, :name => "isoetaceae" } }, :scientific => "Isoetes andina", :author => "Isoetes andina Spruce ex Hook.", :tropicos => "26623010", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Plantas acuáticas, que crecen formando rosetas duras de 6 a 8 cm de diámetro. Tallos cortos y gruesos de donde se disponen las hojas de manera helicoidal. Hojas de color verde oliva, rígidas, 40–50 mm de largo, la base ensanchada de 5–5,5 mm de ancho, la parte media algo terete transversalmente de 1– 1,5 mm de largo, el ápice agudo. Esporangio ovoide de 5,5 × 2,5 mm de ancho, de color café claro y cubierto por una membrana hialina. Especies similares: Isoetes novo-granadensis. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes de Venezuela, Colombia y Ecuador, entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Aquatic plants, growing into firm rosettes 6-8 cm in diameter. Short thick stems, where the leaves are arranged helically. Olive-green leaves, rigid, 40-50 mm long, wide base 5-5.5 mm wide, the middle part terete transversely of 1- 1.5 mm long, acute apex. Ovoid sporangium 5.5 × 2.5 mm wide, light brown and covered by a hyaline membrane. Similar Species: Isoetes novo-granadensis. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 164, :name => "acicularis ", :genus => { :id => 101, :name => "Distichia", :family => { :id => 49, :name => "juncaceae" } }, :scientific => "Distichia acicularis ", :author => "Distichia acicularis Balslev & Laegaard", :tropicos => "16900987", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas que forman almohadillas laxas, hasta de 50 cm de diámetro. Plantas individuales hasta de 15 cm de largo, ramificadas, la parte proximal cubierta de hojas marchitas, la parte distal con 6-8 hojas verdes. Hojas divergentes, hasta de 2 cm de largo, abrazadoras entre sí por las vainas prominentes, estas dobladas con forma de U, los márgenes escariosos que continúan en 2 aurículas puntiagudas de hasta 3 mm. Flores solitarias, axilares, dioicas; las flores masculinas con estambres alrededor de 4 mm, las flores femeninas con el estilo filiforme, alrededor de 5 mm, exerto. Especies similares: Distichia muscoides. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos de las cordilleras occidentales del centro y sur del Ecuador entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Herbs forming loose cushions, up to 50 cm diameter. Individual plants up to 15 cm long, branched, proximal portion covered with withered leaves, the distal part with 6-8 green leaves. Leaves divergent up to 2 cm long, clasping each other by prominent sheaths, U-shaped bent, margins scarious continuing in 2 pointed auricles up to 3 mm. Flowers solitary, axillary, dioecious; male flowers with stamens about 4 mm, female flowers with filiform style, about 5 mm, exserted. Similar species: Distichia muscoides. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 165, :name => "muscoides ", :genus => { :id => 101, :name => "Distichia", :family => { :id => 49, :name => "juncaceae" } }, :scientific => "Distichia muscoides ", :author => "Distichia muscoides Nees & Meyen", :tropicos => "16900203", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas muy apretadas que forman en conjunto almohadillas de varios metros de diámetro. Plantas individuales hasta de 15 cm de largo, ramificadas. Hojas dísticas, pajizas, que se marchitan progresivamente a lo largo del tallo y solo 2 o 3 hojas verdes salen del cojín, dobladas y con forma de V, alrededor de 2 cm, duras y brillantes, los márgenes escariosos, el ápice puntiagudo, los entrenudos cortísimos y las hojas traslapadas. Flores solitarias, axilares, dioicas, los tépalos alrededor de 5 mm, las flores masculinas con estambres, alrededor de 3 mm, las flores femeninas con el estilo filiforme exerto. Fruto en cápsula, alrededor de 6 mm, café-amarillento. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Colombia hasta el norte de Argentina. En el Ecuador crece en los páramos entre 3500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Herbs forming compact cushions of several meters diameter. Individual plants up to 15 cm long, branched. Leaves distichous, straw-colored, which gradually fade along the stem and only 2 or 3 green leaves come out of the cushion, bent and V-shaped, about 2 cm, hard and shiny, margins scarious, apex pointed, very short internode and overlapping leaves. Solitary flowers, axillary, dioecious, tepals about 5 mm, male flowers have stamens, about 3 mm, female flowers have an exserted and filiform style. Fruit in capsule, about 6 mm, yellowish-brown. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to N Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 166, :name => "scilloides", :genus => { :id => 102, :name => "Lilaea", :family => { :id => 50, :name => "juncaginaceae" } }, :scientific => "Lilaea scilloides", :author => "Lilaea scilloides (Poir.) Hauman", :tropicos => "17000024", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :description_es => "Plantas acuáticas hasta de 40 cm de alto, tienen la forma de un penacho de hojas, las mismas que están dispuestas en un corto tallo. Hojas aciculares, hasta de 35 cm de largo y 2 mm de ancho, la vaina transparente en la base. Inflorescencias en espigas de flores estaminadas y bisexuales en la punta de un tallo estrecho así como flores pistiladas en las axilas bajo el agua, diminutas, alrededor de 2 mm; la flor pistilada se compone de un estilo filiforme extremadamente largo que puede ser de hasta de 20 cm, con un estigma en la punta, que flota sobre la superficie del agua. Especies similares: Lilaeopsis schaffneriana (Schltdl.) J.M. Coult. & Rose. ", :distribution_es => " Desde Estados Unidos hasta Argentina. En el Ecuador se distribuye en la región andina entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Aquatic plants, up to 40 cm high, forming a tuft of leaves, leaves arranged on a short stalk. Leaves acicular, up to 35 cm long and 2 mm wide, sheath transparent at the base. Inflorescences in staminate and bisexuals spikes at the tip of a narrow stem. Pistillate flowers in the axils underwater, minute, about 2 mm. Pistillate flower consisting of an extremely long threadlike style that can be up to 20 cm, with a stigma at the tip, which floats on the water surface. Similar species: Lilaeopsis schaffneriana. ", :distribution_en => " United States to Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 167, :name => "magellanicum ", :genus => { :id => 103, :name => "Austrolycopodium", :family => { :id => 22, :name => "lycopodiaceae", :old_id => "166" } }, :scientific => "Austrolycopodium magellanicum ", :author => "Austrolycopodium magellanicum (P. Beauv.) Holub", :tropicos => "26617643", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas herbáceas, rastreras, desparramadas o colgantes de barrancos; el tallo enraizando a intervalos, las ramas hasta 15 cm de largo, ramificadas en forma desigual. Hojas en espiral, laxas, con forma de escamas linear-aciculares, hasta de 5 mm de largo, de un verde claro, apiculadas. Estróbilos terminales hasta de 50 mm de largo, a veces bifurcados, verde-amarillentos; esporofilos dispuestos en verticilos alternos 4, peltados, los márgenes erosos. Se conocía anteriormente como Lycopodium magellanicum. Especies similares: Lycopodium clavatum. ", :distribution_es => " Caribe, Costa Rica, los Andes desde Venezuela a Chile y Argentina. En el Ecuador entre los 2500 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Herbaceous plants, creeping, sprawling or hanging from ravines; stem rooting at intervals, branches up to 15 cm long, branched unevenly. Leaves arranged in spiral, loose, linear, needle-like scales, up to 5 mm long, light green, apiculate. Strobili terminal up to 50 mm, sometimes bifurcated, green-yellow. Sporophylls arranged in 4 alternating whorls, peltate, margins erose. Similar Species: Lycopodium clavatum. ", :distribution_en => " Caribbean, Costa Rica, Venezuela to Chile and Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 168, :name => "clavatum ", :genus => { :id => 104, :name => "Lycopodium", :family => { :id => 22, :name => "lycopodiaceae", :old_id => "166" } }, :scientific => "Lycopodium clavatum ", :author => "Lycopodium clavatum L.", :tropicos => "26600197", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Plantas herbáceas, rastreras, desparramadas o colgantes de barrancos; el tallo enraizando a intervalos, las ramas hasta 50 cm de largo, ramificadas en forma desigual. Hojas en espiral, dispuestas en 10 hileras, con forma de escamas linear-aciculares, hasta de 8 mm de largo, verde claro, que terminan en un pelo largo translúcido. Pedúnculos de hasta 30 cm, simples o ramificados y hasta con 6 estróbilos, los estróbilos hasta de 60 mm de largo, a veces bifurcados, verde-plateados o verde-amarillentos; esporofilos dispuestos en verticilos alternos de 5-6, subpeltados, los márgenes erosos. ", :distribution_es => " Subcosmopolita, ausente de Australia. En el Ecuador se encuentra en la región andina, entre 1000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Herbaceous plants, creeping, sprawling or hanging from ravines. Stem rooting at intervals, branches up to 50 cm long, branched unevenly. Leaves spirally arranged in 10 rows, linear-shaped needle-like scales, up to 8 mm long, light green, ending in a translucent long hair. Peduncles up to 30 cm, simple or branched and with up to 6 strobili. Strobili up to 60 mm long, sometimes bifurcated, green-silver or green-yellow; sporophylls arranged in alternating 5-6 whorls, subpeltate, margins erose. ", :distribution_en => " Subcosmopolitan.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 19, :name => "galapagos" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 169, :name => "alpinum ", :genus => { :id => 8, :name => "Brachyotum", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "49" }, :scientific => "Brachyotum alpinum ", :author => "Brachyotum alpinum Cogn.", :tropicos => "20300401", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o arbolitos hasta de 8 m de alto y 18 cm de DAP; tallo exfoliable de color blanco-grisáceo, la copa redondeada con escaso follaje, las ramas de color rojo-rosado con tricomas blanquecinos. Hojas opuestas, de ovadas a lanceoladas, hasta 1,5 cm de largo, trinervias, con pubescencia tosca blanquecina, el pecíolo corto, rojizo. Inflorescencias ternadas con 3 flores colgantes. Flores 4-meras, pediceladas; cáliz rosado-verdoso, 4-lobulado; corola púrpura, con 4 pétalos traslapados que forman un falso tubo, el estilo rosado. Fruto, una cápsula seca con los restos de los lóbulos del cáliz, con numerosas semillas. Especies similares: Brachyotum jamesonii. ", :distribution_es => " Páramos del Ecuador, entre 2900 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Shrubs or small trees, up to 8 m high; stem peeling off, bark grayish-white, crow rounded with sparse foliage, branches red-pink with whitish trichomes. Leaves opposite, ovate to lanceolate, to 1.5 cm long, trinerved, with rough whitish pubescence; petiole, short, reddish. Inflorescences ternate, with 3 hanging flowers. Flowers 4-merous, pedicelate; calyx pink-green, 4-lobed. Corolla purple with 4 overlapping petals forming a false tube, style pink. Fruit a dry capsule with the remains of the calyx lobes, with many seeds. Similar species: Brachyotum jamesonii. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 20, :name => "guayas" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 170, :name => "fontana", :genus => { :id => 105, :name => "Montia", :family => { :id => 51, :name => "montiaceae" } }, :scientific => "Montia fontana", :author => "Montia fontana L.", :tropicos => "26200137", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta de 40 cm de largo, semiacuáticas. Tallos muy delgados de color rojizo, ramificados en los nudos, carnosos. Hojas opuestas, oblongo-lanceoladas o algo espatuladas, hasta 10 × 3 mm de largo, con un solo nervio central, a veces redondeadas en el ápice. Flores reunidas en grupos terminales o laterales, muy pequeñas, alrededor de 2 mm; pétalos 5, de color blanco. Especies similares: M. meridiensis Friedrich y M. biapiculata Lourteig.", :distribution_es => nil, :description_en => "Herbs up to 40 cm long, semiaquatic. Stems thin, reddish, branched at knots, fleshy. Leaves opposite, oblong-lanceolate or slightly spatulate, up to 10 × 3 mm long, with a single midrib, sometimes rounded at apex. Flowers arranged in terminal or lateral groups, very small, about 2 mm; petals 5, white. Similar species: M. meridiensis and M. biapiculata. ", :distribution_en => " Worldwide.", :provincias => [{ :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 171, :name => "epilobiifolia", :genus => { :id => 106, :name => "Oenothera", :family => { :id => 18, :name => "onagraceae", :old_id => "120" } }, :scientific => "Oenothera epilobiifolia", :author => "Oenothera epilobiifolia Kunth", :tropicos => "23200379", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas rastreras hasta de 30 cm. Tallos pubescentes, rosado-rojizos. Hojas alternas, las basales oblongas, hasta 4,5 cm, y las hojas caulinares hasta de 2,5 cm, glabras en el haz y ligeramente tomentosas en el envés, los márgenes aserrados, color púrpura. Flores solitarias, axilares, el pedicelo corto, cubierto densamente por tricomas; pétalos hasta 10 mm, anchamente ovados y traslapados en un falso tubo, rojos con matices amarillos; cáliz dialisépalo con matices púrpuras. Especies similares: Oenothera multicaulis Ruiz & Pav. ", :distribution_es => " De México a Perú. En el Ecuador se distribuye en la cordillera de los Andes, entre 2000 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Creeping herbs, up to 30 cm. Stems pubescent, reddish-pink. Leaves alternate, basal ones oblong, to 4.5 cm, and the stem leaves up to 2.5 cm, glabrous above and slightly hairy below, margins serrate, purple. Flowers solitary, axillary, pedicel short, densely covered by trichomes. Petals up to 10 mm, broadly ovate and overlapping in a false tube, red with yellow tints; calyx dialisepalous with purple tints. Similar Species: Oenothera multicaulis. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 172, :name => "parvifolia ", :genus => { :id => 107, :name => "Pterichis", :family => { :id => 15, :name => "orchidaceae", :old_id => "105" } }, :scientific => "Pterichis parvifolia ", :author => "Pterichis parvifolia (Lindl.) Schltr.", :tropicos => "23510564", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas terrestres de hasta 45 cm de alto. Raíces fasciculadas blancas. Hojas cuando presentes son basales; lámina linear-lanceolada, glabra, de 10 a 15 cm de largo por 1 a 1,5 cm de ancho, base caniculada y ápice agudo, peciolo de 12 a 15 cm de largo. Inflorescencia erecta, sostenida por un escapo de 40 cm de largo, pubescente. Flores con brácteas ovadas glabras de color verde; sépalos pubescentes, ovados, de color amarillo-limón; pétalos papilosos, linear oblongos, con 3 nervios, de color amarillo con líneas cafés; labio triangular cordado papiloso amarillo. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia, Ecuador y Perú; crece en los Andes desde los 2500 hasta los 4000 m.", :description_en => "Terrestrial herbs, up to 45 cm high. Fasciculate roots white. Leaves basal when present, linear-lanceolate, glabrous, 10-15 × 1-1.5 cm, caniculate at base, apex acute, petiole 12-15 cm. Inflorescence erect, supported by an 40 cm long escape, pubescent. Flowers with glabrous ovate bracts, green; sepals pubescent, ovate, lemon yellow; petals papillose, linear oblong, with 3 nerves, yellow with brown lines; lip triangular papilate chordate, yellow. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia, Ecuador and Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 173, :name => "stricta ", :genus => { :id => 5, :name => "Bartsia", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "31" }, :scientific => "Bartsia stricta ", :author => "Bartsia stricta (Kunth) Benth.", :tropicos => "29205031", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Subarbustos hasta de 40 cm de alto, pubescentes. Hojas opuestas, hasta de 2 cm de largo estrechamente lanceoladas, los márgenes gruesamente crenados, color púrpura. Inflorescencias espigadas, pubescentes, con brácteas similares a hojas con los márgenes gruesamente crenados, color púrpura-magenta; cáliz 7–9,5 mm, color púrpura-magenta; corola 6–7,2 mm, blanca, bilabiada y galeada, vellosa. Frutos en cápsula, dehiscentes, 8 mm de largo. ", :distribution_es => " De Venezuela a Perú. En el Ecuador se ha registrado en toda la cordillera desde los 3000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Subshrubs up to 40 cm tall, pubescent. Leaves opposite up to 2 cm long, narrowly lanceolate, the margins coarsely crenate, purple. Inflorescences slender, pubescent, with bracts similar to leaves with margins coarsely crenate, purple-magenta. Calyx 7-9.5 mm, purple-magenta; corolla 6-7.2 mm, white, bilabiate and galeate, villous. Fruit a capsule, dehiscent, 8 mm. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 174, :name => "ecuadorensis ", :genus => { :id => 13, :name => "Castilleja", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "72" }, :scientific => "Castilleja ecuadorensis ", :author => "Castilleja ecuadorensis N. Holmgren", :tropicos => "29206507", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas de hasta 30 cm de alto, el follaje está a menudo teñido de morado. Hojas alternas, hasta 3 cm de largo, lineares, la basales enteras, las apicales divididas en lóbulos estrechos. Inflorescencias en racimos hasta de 5 cm de largo; brácteas con apariencia de pétalos color rojo brillante y que sostienen a cada flor. Flores irregulares, más o menos tubulares, algo recurvadas, hasta 25 mm de largo, color verde claro, con tricomas diminutos. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica del Ecuador. Se ha registrado en Azuay, Cotopaxi, Imbabura y Loja. ", :description_en => "Herbs up to 30 cm high, the foliage often tinged with purple. Leaves alternate, up to 3 cm long, linear, basal leaves entire, the apical ones divided into narrow lobes. Inflorescences in clusters up to 5 cm long; bracts petaloid, bright red and subtending each flower. flowers Irregular, more or less tubular, somewhat recurved, up to 25 mm long, light green with minute trichomes. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }] }
{ :id => 175, :name => "nubigena ", :genus => { :id => 13, :name => "Castilleja", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "72" }, :scientific => "Castilleja nubigena ", :author => "Castilleja nubigena Kunth", :tropicos => "29202226", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes hasta de 8 cm; tallos erecto-ascendentes. Hojas alternas, 1-2.5 cm, de lanceoladas a ovadas, pinnatidivididas en lóbulos angostos, sésiles, los márgenes enteros. Inflorescencias en espigas de cortas a alargadas o en racimos; brácteas frecuentemente foliáceas por debajo, a menudo conspicuamente coloreadas y más vistosas que las flores. Flores marcadamente bilabiadas; cáliz tubular; corola de color verdoso pálido, el labio superior entero y estrechamente galeado, que envuelve las anteras; el labio inferior más corto y externo al labio superior en el botón; estambres 4, didínamos, adheridos casi o más arriba de la mitad del tubo de la corola. Fruto en cápsula más o menos asimétrica, ovada o globosa; semillas numerosas. Especies similares: Castilleja fisifolia, Castilleja ecuadorensis. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Venezuela a Perú. En el Ecuador se encuentra ampliamente distribuida en los páramos entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs up to 8 cm; stems erect-ascending. Leaves alternate, 1-2.5 cm, lanceolate to ovate, pinnately divided in narrow lobes, sessile, margins entire. Inflorescences in spikes or short to elongated clusters; bracts often foliaceous below, often colorful and more conspicuous than the flowers. Flowers markedly bilabiate; calyx tubular; corolla pale greenish, upper lip entire and closely galeate, covering the anthers; shorter lip lower and external from the upper lip in bud. Stamens 4 didynamous, connate above half the corolla tube. Fruit a more or less asymmetrical capsule, ovate or globose; seeds numerous. Similar species: Castilleja fisifolia, Castilleja ecuadorensis. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 176, :name => "deflexa", :genus => { :id => 108, :name => "Callitriche", :family => { :id => 31, :name => "plantaginaceae", :old_id => "228" } }, :scientific => "Callitriche deflexa", :author => "Callitriche deflexa A. Braun ex Hegelm.", :tropicos => "5200007", :color1 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Plantas herbáceas muy delicadas, acuáticas, flotantes, que forman tapetes finos de color verde claro. Presentan raíces adventicias. Hojas simples, membranáceas, opuestas, brevemente unidas en la base, espatuladas, hasta 3 mm de largo, sésiles. Flores solitarias, unisexuales, axilares, de tamaño diminuto, alrededor de 1,5 mm; pétalos café-liláceo. Cápsulas diminutas, achatadas y dehiscentes, de color oscuro. Especies similares: Callitriche terrestris Raf. ", :distribution_es => " Nativa de Brasil y Argentina, en la actualidad se distribuye desde Estados Unidos hasta Argentina, en Europa y en Asia. En el Ecuador ha sido registrada en los Andes, Costa y Galápagos, desde el nivel del mar hasta los 3500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Delicate, aquatic, floating herbaceous plants, forming thin light green cushions. Presenting adventitious roots. Leaves simple, opposite, membranaceous, shortly joined at the base, spatulate, up to 3 mm long, sessile. Flowers solitary, unisexual, axillary, small, about 1.5 mm; petals brown-lilac. Capsules minute, flattened and dehiscent, dark. Similar species: Callitriche terrestris. ", :distribution_en => " Native to Brazil and Argentina, at present Americas, Europe and Asia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 19, :name => "galapagos" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }] }
{ :id => 177, :name => "tubulosa ", :genus => { :id => 60, :name => "Plantago", :family => { :id => 31, :name => "plantaginaceae", :old_id => "228" }, :old_id => "267" }, :scientific => "Plantago tubulosa ", :author => "Plantago tubulosa Decne.", :tropicos => "25200237", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas arrosetadas, los rizomas gruesos. Hojas lineares, angostas, hasta de 5 cm de largo, los márgenes escasamente dentados, la base expandida y densamente vellosa. Flores solitarias, verdosas, tubulares, los pedicelos vellosos, con 4 sépalos, ovados, alrededor de 8 mm, la corola tubular, 8-12 mm, con 4 lóbulos alrededor de 1,5 mm de largo. Fruto en cápsula, cuya parte inferior durante la maduración se transforma en un carpóforo tubular de hasta 50 mm de largo. Especies similares: Plantago rigida. ", :distribution_es => " Desde México hasta el NO. de Argentina. En el Ecuador se distribuye en los Andes entre 2500 y 5000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Herbs forming rosettes with thick rhizomes. Leave linear, narrow, up to 5 cm long, margins sparsely toothed, base expanded densely villous. Solitary flowers, greenish, tubular, villous pedicels, with 4 sepals, ovate, about 8 mm, corolla tubular, 8-12 mm, with 4 lobes about 1.5 mm long. Fruit a capsule, the lower part during maturaty becomes a tubular carpophore up to 50 mm long. Similar species: Plantago rigida. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to NW of Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 178, :name => "repens ", :genus => { :id => 109, :name => "Sibthorpia", :family => { :id => 31, :name => "plantaginaceae", :old_id => "228" } }, :scientific => "Sibthorpia repens ", :author => "Sibthorpia repens (L.) Kuntze", :tropicos => "29201878", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas diminutas postradas. Hojas alternas, 0,5–2 × 0,5–2,5 cm, enteras, orbiculado-reniformes, profundamente cordadas, los márgenes con lóbulos redondeados, el envés de color lila, con tricomas blancos ascendentes, largamente pecioladas. Inflorescencias axilares de flores solitarias, largamente pediceladas. Flores ligeramente bilabiadas de color lila-rojizo, hasta 3 mm de largo; estambres 4, iguales que salen desde la base de la corola, las anteras con tecas paralelas y contiguas en el ápice. ", :distribution_es => " Regiones montañosas de México, América Central y Andes sudamericanos entre 3000 y 4550 m.", :description_en => "Small prostrate herbs. Leaves alternate, 0.5-2 × 0.5-2.5 cm, entire, orbiculate-reniform, deeply cordate, margins with rounded lobes, leaf blade lilac below, with white ascendant trichomes, petioles long. Inflorescences axillary, of solitary flowers long-pedicellate. Flowers slightly bilabiate, lilac-red, up to 3 mm long; stamens 4, equal. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to South American Andes.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 179, :name => "breviculmis ", :genus => { :id => 110, :name => "Agrostis", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" } }, :scientific => "Agrostis breviculmis ", :author => "Agrostis breviculmis Hitchc.", :tropicos => "25512920", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Macollas densas cespitosas, los culmos erectos, 3-8 cm de largo; hojas basales dobladas a lo largo del nervio principal, 1,5-3,5 × 0,5 cm; lígula membranácea. Panículas espiciformes, 1-3 cm de largo, las espiguillas de color morado, 2 mm de largo, con un flósculo, las glumas iguales, que cubren totalmente el flósculo, con tricomas escabrosos en la parte dorsal, la lema membranácea, elíptica, 1,4 mm de largo, la pálea ausente. ", :distribution_es => " Desde Venezuela a Chile y Argentina. En el Ecuador se distribuye en la región andina entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Dense tussock grasses, culms erect, 3-8 cm long. Basal leaves folded along the midrib, 1.5-3.5 × 0.5 cm; ligule membranous. Panicles spiciform, 1-3 cm long, spikelets purple, 2 mm long, with one floret, glumes equal completely covering the floret, trichomes scabrous dorsally, lemma membranaceous, elliptical, 1,4 mm, palea absent. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Chile and Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 180, :name => "perennans ", :genus => { :id => 110, :name => "Agrostis", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" } }, :scientific => "Agrostis perennans ", :author => "Agrostis perennans (Walter) Tuck.", :tropicos => "25502790", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas suaves de 20 a 40 cm de alto, las hojas son en su mayor parte basales y forman pequeñas macollas. Hojas basales lineares, acanaladas, 8-15 cm × 1-1,2 mm, las hojas caulinares lineares, 3-5 cm × 1,3 mm. Panículas laxas, 4-12 cm de largo, de color morado, las espiguillas de 2 mm de largo; glumas con un nervio central, ligeramente escabrosas, la lema 5-nervia con una arista dorsal geniculada de 1,5 mm de largo. Especies similares: Agrostis tolucensis. ", :distribution_es => " Especie de amplia distribución en el continente americano. En el Ecuador se ha registrado entre 2000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Soft herbs, 20 to 40 cm tall, the leaves are mostly basal and forming small clumps. Basal leaves linear,  8-15 cm × 1-1.2 mm, ribbed, stem leaves linear, 3-5 cm × 1.3 mm. Panicles lax, 4-12 cm long, purple, spikelets 2 mm long; glumes with midrib, slightly scabrous, lemma 5-ribbed with a geniculate dorsal ridge, 1.5 mm long. Similar species: Agrostis tolucensis. ", :distribution_en => "  Americas. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 181, :name => "lanatus ", :genus => { :id => 111, :name => "Bromus", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" } }, :scientific => "Bromus lanatus ", :author => "Bromus lanatus Kunth", :tropicos => "25512670", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas cespitosas, crecen formando macollas laxas; culmos 15-30 cm de largo, entrenudos cilíndricos, villosos; hojas mayormente basales, la vaina cilíndrica, 3-4 cm de largo, la lígula membranosa, la lámina linear, suave, aplanada, villosa, 10-16 cm × 1,2-1,5 mm. Panículas abiertas con pocas espiguillas grandes, 1,8-2,2 cm de largo, las glumas villosas, oblongo-lanceoladas, 9–10 ×1,1 mm, las lemas villosas, elíptico-oblongas, 13 ×3 mm, con una arista dorsal de 4 mm largo. Especies similares: Bromus lanatus. ", :distribution_es => " Nativa de los Andes, distribuida desde los páramos de Colombia y Venezuela hasta las montañas del norte de Chile y Argentina. En el Ecuador entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Caespitose herbs growing into loose clumps; culms 15-30 cm long, internodes cylindrical, villous; leaves mostly basal, sheath cylindrical, 3-4 cm long, ligule membranous, blade linear, soft, flattened, villous, 10-16 cm × 1.2-1.5 mm. Panicles open with few large spikelets, 1.8-2.2 cm long, glume villous, oblong-lanceolate, 9-10 × 1.1 mm, lemma villous, elliptical-oblong, 13 × 3 mm, with a dorsal awn 4 mm long. Similar species: Bromus lanatus. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to N Chile and Argentina. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 182, :name => "fibrovaginata ", :genus => { :id => 9, :name => "Calamagrostis", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" }, :old_id => "55" }, :scientific => "Calamagrostis fibrovaginata ", :author => "Calamagrostis fibrovaginata Lægaard", :tropicos => "50101170", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Macollas suaves, de 20-30 cm de largo; rizomas cortos; vainas fibrosas que envuelven la base de la macolla, la lígula membranosa. Hojas basales, dobladas a lo largo del nervio principal, 6-12 cm de largo, glabras. Panículas contraídas, densas, 4 -6 cm de largo; espiguillas pajizas, fusiformes, 5 mm de largo; glumas elíptico-lanceoladas, subiguales que cubren completamente el flósculo, la primera gluma de 5 mm largo, la segunda gluma de 4,6 mm de largo, la lema membranácea de 2,3 mm de largo con 3 dientes apicales y una arista dorsal geniculada de 3,5 mm de largo, el callo del flósculo barbado con tricomas cortos y largos de color blanco. Especies similares: Agrostis tolucensis. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Venezuela al Perú. En el Ecuador se distribuye en los páramos entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Smooth tussocks, 20-30 cm long; rhizomes short; sheaths fibrous surrounding the base of the tussocks, ligule membranaceous. Leaves basal, folded along the midrib, 6-12 cm long, glabrous. Panicle contracted, dense, 4 -6 cm long; spikelets straw-colored, fusiform, 5 mm long; glumes elliptic-lanceolate, subequal, completely covering the floret, the first glume about 5 mm long, the second glume 4.6 mm long. Lemma membranous, 2.3 mm long with 3 apical teeth and a dorsal geniculate awn 3.5 mm long, floret’s callus bearded with short and long white trichomes. Similar species: Agrostis tolucensis. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 183, :name => "steyermarkii ", :genus => { :id => 9, :name => "Calamagrostis", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" }, :old_id => "55" }, :scientific => "Calamagrostis steyermarkii ", :author => "Calamagrostis steyermarkii Swallen", :tropicos => "25524487", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas fasciculadas, de hasta 65 cm. Hojas 15–25 cm de largo, involutas, rígidas, las superiores reducidas, las vainas inferiores cortas, amontonadas, glabras, las del culmo más largas que los entrenudos. Panículas angostas, hasta 18 cm, las ramas delgadas en fascículos distantes, flexuosos, color morado oscuro; glumas alrededor de 3,5 mm, lanceoladas, aquilladas, escábridas. Especies similares: Calamagrostis intermedia. ", :distribution_es => " Endémica de los páramos del Azuay y Cañar, se encuentra entre 3000 y 4150 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Fasciculate herbs, up to 65 cm. Leaves 15-25 cm long, involute, stiff, the upper ones reduced and the lower ones shorter, crowded, glabrous, those of the culm longer than those of the internodes. Panicles narrow, up to 18 cm, branches slender in distant fascicles, flexuous, dark purple. Glumes about 3.5 mm, lanceolate, keeled, scabrid. Similar species: Calamagrostis intermedia. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }] }
{ :id => 184, :name => "sericantha ", :genus => { :id => 112, :name => "Cortaderia", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" } }, :scientific => "Cortaderia sericantha ", :author => "Cortaderia sericantha (Steud.) Hitchc.", :tropicos => "25512795", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Macollas robustas de 30-50 cm de alto; hojas basales con vainas fibrosas que envuelven la base de los tallos y en su parte apical están cubiertas por una densa masa de tricomas largos, blancos, que cubren también la base de la lámina; culmos simples, erectos con una hilera de tricomas barbados bajo los nudos. Hojas involutas, 5-20 cm × 2-3 mm, los márgenes escabrosos. Panículas contraídas, elípticas, 4-10 × 2-3 cm, con ramificaciones cortas y cubiertas por tricomas blancos largos y cortos. Espiguillas lateramente comprimidas con 2 a 3 flósculos; glumas 3-nervias, lanceoladas, color crema, 2,4 cm de largo, que cubren totalmente los flósculos; lema estrechamente lanceolada, 6 mm de largo, con el ápice bífido y una arista apical de 5 mm, originada en la mitad de los lóbulos; pálea lanceolada, 5 mm de largo, con 2 quillas laterales ciliadas; callo cubierto con tricomas blancos, 4-5 mm de largo. Especies similares: Cortaderia bífida Pilg. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes desde Colombia hasta Perú. En el Ecuador se distribuye en los páramos entre 3300 y 4300 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Robust tussocks, 30-50 cm tall; basal leaves with fibrous sheaths that surround the base of the stems. The apical part covered by a dense mass of long white trichomes, which also cover the base of the blade. Culms simple, erect with a row of bearded trichomes under the nodes. Leaves involute, 5-20 cm × 2.3 mm, margins rough. Panicle contracted, elliptic, 4-10 × 2-3 cm, with short branches and covered with long and short white trichomes. Spikelets laterally compressed, with 2-3 flowers; glumes 3-nerved, lanceolate, cream color, 2.4 cm long, completely covering the flowers. Lemma tightly lanceolate, 6 mm long, with bifid apex and an apical awn 5 mm, originating in the middle of the lobes. Palea lanceolate, 5 mm long, with 2 lateral ciliate keels; callus covered with white trichomes, 4-5 mm long. Similar species: Cortaderia bífida. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 185, :name => "parciflora subsp. parcifora", :genus => { :id => 113, :name => "Festuca", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" } }, :scientific => "Festuca parciflora subsp. parcifora", :author => "Festuca parciflora Swallen subsp. parcifora", :tropicos => "50263545", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Macollas delgadas, 25-40 cm de alto, con rizomas cortos; culmos levemente escabrosos, 0,4-0,5 mm de diámetro. Hojas basales, las vainas membranosas; lígula membranosa de 0,8 mm de largo; lámina conduplicada, 6-15 × 0,4 cm, glabra en su mayor parte. Panículas contraídas, 3-8 cm × 3-4 mm, el raquis escabroso; espiguillas lanceoladas, púrpuras, 0,6-0,7 mm de largo, con 2 a 3 flósculos; glumas persistentes membranosas, púrpuras o blancas cuando maduras, la gluma inferior lanceolada, 2,4-2,6 mm de largo, la gluma superior ovada, alrededor de 3 mm de largo; lema membranácea, 6 mm de largo con una arista apical de 1 mm de largo; pálea 0,5 mm de largo, lanceolada de margen alado, densamente piloso. Especies similares: Calamagrostis fibrovaginata. ", :distribution_es => " Festuca parciflora es endémica de los Andes del sur del Ecuador, específicamente en los páramos de las provincias del Azuay y Loja, entre 3600 y 4200 m s.n.m. La subespecie Festuca parciflora subsp. parciflora está restringida a los páramos del macizo del Cajas entre 3500 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Slender tussocks, 25-40 cm tall, with short rhizomes; culms slightly scabrous, 0.4-0.5 mm diameter. Leaves basal, sheath membranous; ligule membranous, 0.8 mm long; blade conduplicate, 6-15 × 0.4 cm, mostly glabrous. Panicles contracted, 3-8 cm × 3-4 mm, rachis scabrous. Spikelets lanceolate, purple, 0.6-0.7 mm long, with 2 to 3 flowers; membranous glumes persistent, purple or white when mature, lower glume lanceolate, 2.4-2.6 mm long, upper glume ovate, about 3 mm long; lemma membranous, 6 mm long with an apical ridge 1 mm long; palea 0.5 mm long, lanceolate, margin winged, densely pilose. Similar species: Calamagrostis fibrovaginata. ", :distribution_en => "  endemic to S Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }] }
{ :id => 186, :name => "subulifolia ", :genus => { :id => 113, :name => "Festuca", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" } }, :scientific => "Festuca subulifolia ", :author => "Festuca subulifolia Benth.", :tropicos => "25523471", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas robustas, crecen formando macollas densas, hasta 120 cm de alto. Culmos erectos, escábridos, 30-80 cm de largo. Hojas basales involutas, 20-60 cm de largo, las vainas finamente surcadas, ligeramente escabrosas, la lígula membranosa de 1 mm de largo. Panículas contraídas o abiertas en la madurez, 10-30 cm de largo. Espiguillas de color púrpura, 7-8 cm de largo; raquilla cubierta por diminutos dientes; glumas membranáceas, agudas, la primera gluma lanceolada, 3,2-3,5 mm de largo, la segunda gluma oblonga, 5-5,5 mm de largo; lema oblongo-lanceolada, púrpura, escabrosa, 6,5-7 mm de largo con una arista terminal de 1 mm de largo; pálea membranosa, lanceolada, de 6 mm de largo; estambres 3, con anteras de 2 mm de largo; cariópside de forma oblongo-lanceolada. Especies similares: Calamagrostis intermedia. ", :distribution_es => " De Colombia a Perú. En Ecuador ha sido registrada entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Robust herbs, growing into dense clumps, up to 120 cm tall. Culms erect, scabrid, 30-80 cm long. Basal leaves involute, 20-60 cm long, sheaths finely ridged, slightly scabrous, ligule membranous 1 mm long. Panicles contracted or open at maturity, 10-30 cm long. Spikelets purple, 7-8 cm long; raquilla covered with minute teeth; glumes membranous, acute, the first glume lanceolate, 3.2-3.5 mm long, second glume oblong, 5-5.5 mm long. Lemma oblong-lanceolate, purple, scabrous, 6.5-7 mm long with a terminal awn 1 mm long. Palea membranous, lanceolate, 6 mm long; stamens 3, anthers 2 mm long; caryopsis oblong-lanceolate. Similar species: Calamagrostis intermedia. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 187, :name => "pauciflora ", :genus => { :id => 114, :name => "Poa", :family => { :id => 44, :name => "poaceae", :old_id => "54" } }, :scientific => "Poa pauciflora ", :author => "Poa pauciflora Roem. & Schult.", :tropicos => "25540515", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 4, :name => "grass", :old_id => "53" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, 20-60 cm de alto, que forman macollas laxas; culmos simples, huecos, cilíndricos, de color verde con manchas púrpuras; hojas basales, la vaina tubular de color púrpura, la lígula membranosa, la lámina plegada, redondeada, con la superficie áspera estrigosa de 4 mm de largo. Panículas abiertas de 10 a 25 cm de largo. Espiguillas lateralmente comprimidas, púrpuras, de 3,3 mm de largo; glumas trinervias de 3 mm de largo; lemas púrpuras, carinadas, de 2,6 mm de largo con un callo y tricomas aracnoides en la base; ovario glabro con 2 estilos plumosos de color blanco. ", :distribution_es => " Andes de Venezuela a Perú. En el Ecuador está registrada entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, 20-60 cm tall, forming loose tussocks; culms simple, hollow, cylindrical, green with purple spots. Leaves basal, sheath tubular, purple, ligule membranous, blade folded, rounded, with a strigose rough surface, 4 mm long. Panicles open, 10 to 25 cm long. Spikelets laterally compressed, purple, 3.3 mm long; glumes 3-nerved, 3 mm long. Lemma purple, keeled, 2.6 mm long with a callus and arachnoid trichomes at the base; ovary glabrous with 2 plumose styles, white. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 188, :name => "moniliformis", :genus => { :id => 115, :name => "Melpomene", :family => { :id => 52, :name => "polypodiaceae" } }, :scientific => "Melpomene moniliformis", :author => "Melpomene moniliformis (Lag. ex Sw.) A.R. Sm. & R.C. Moran", :tropicos => "26614792", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos terrestres, rupícolas o epifitos, hasta de 20 cm de alto, los rizomas cortos, rastreros, las escamas rojizas que se vuelven negruzcas; pecíolo hasta 6 cm. Hojas angostas, erectas, divididas en múltiples segmentos más o menos rectangulares de 5 mm de ancho, algo cóncavos, el haz verde-grisáceo, el raquis negro lustroso. Soros redondeados de color café, sin indusio. Esporas de color verde. ", :distribution_es => " Centro y Sur América en zonas montañosas.", :description_en => "Terrestrial ferns, on rocks or epiphytic, up to 20 cm tall, rhizome short creeping, scales reddish becoming blackish. Petiole up to 6 cm. Leaves narrow, erect, divided into multiple, more or less, rectangular segments 5 mm wide, somewhat concave, the upper leaf surface green-gray, the rachis black, lustrous. Sori rounded, brown, without indusium. Spores green. ", :distribution_en => " Central and South America.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 189, :name => "angustifolium", :genus => { :id => 116, :name => "Campyloneurum", :family => { :id => 52, :name => "polypodiaceae" } }, :scientific => "Campyloneurum angustifolium", :author => "Campyloneurum angustifolium (Bory ex Willd.) Kaulf.", :tropicos => "26601748", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos terrestres o epifitos, hasta de 25 cm de alto. Rizomas largos de 3 mm de ancho. Escamas clatradas, peltadas, lanceoladas. Hojas fértiles e infértiles presentes, largamente lanceoladas, los márgenes enteros; las hojas fértiles más largas y angostas que las infértiles. Pecíolo articulado a filopodios cortos; lámina entera, elíptica. Soros sin indusio, redondeados, dispuestos en una sola hilera entre el raquis y el margen, ubicados en la mitad superior de la lámina. Esporas amarillas. ", :distribution_es => " Especie de amplia distribución, registrada en América y África.", :description_en => "Terrestrial or epiphytic ferns, up to 25 cm high. Rhizomes long, 3 mm wide. Clathrate scales peltate, lanceolate. Fertile and infertile leaves present, long lanceolate, margins entire. Fertile leaves longer and narrower than the infertile ones. Petiole articulated to short phyllopodia; blade entire, elliptical. Sori without indusium, rounded, arranged in a single row between the rachis and the margin, located in the upper half of the blade. Spores yellow. ", :distribution_en => " America and Africa.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }] }
{ :id => 190, :name => "cinnamomea", :genus => { :id => 40, :name => "Jamesonia", :family => { :id => 25, :name => "pteridaceae", :old_id => "182" }, :old_id => "183" }, :scientific => "Jamesonia cinnamomea", :author => "Jamesonia cinnamomea A.F. Tryon", :tropicos => "26606395", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos terrestres, el rizoma de 2 a 3 mm de ancho, rastreros, pubescentes, los tricomas gruesos como cerdas. Hojas hasta de 60 × 1,5 cm, lineares, erectas, pinnadas, pubescentes, el ápice enrollado, indeterminado; contiene más de 100 pinnas, de 4 mm de ancho, redondeadas, casi sésiles, imbricadas y coriáceas, los márgenes típicamente enrollados, nervaduras libres. Soros a lo largo de las nervaduras, sin indusios, protegidos por los márgenes reflexos de las pinnas; esporangios patentes a lo largo de las pinnas. Esporas de color negro. Especies similares: Jamesonia goudotii. ", :distribution_es => " De Ecuador a Bolivia. En el Ecuador se ha registrado en Azuay, Imbabura, Loja, Morona Santiago y Zamora Chinchipe.", :description_en => "Terrestrial ferns; rhizome 2 to 3 mm wide, creeping, pubescent, trichomes as thick as bristles. Leaves up to 60 × 1.5 cm, linear, erect, pinnate, pubescent, apex rolled, indeterminate, containing more than 100 pinnae, 4 mm wide, rounded, almost sessile, imbricate, leathery, margins typically rolled, nerves free. Sori along the ribs, without indusia, protected by the reflexed pinnae margins. sporangia patents along the pinnae. Spores black. Similar species: Jamesonia goudotii. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }] }
{ :id => 191, :name => "limoselloides", :genus => { :id => 66, :name => "Ranunculus", :family => { :id => 38, :name => "ranunculaceae", :old_id => "293" }, :old_id => "294" }, :scientific => "Ranunculus limoselloides", :author => "Ranunculus limoselloides Turcz.", :tropicos => "27101863", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :description_es => "Hierbas acuáticas o semi-acuáticas, tallos largos reptantes de hasta 60 cm. Hojas flotantes en la superficie del agua, láminas de elípticas a ovadas de 10 a 15 mm de largo por 5 a 8 mm de ancho; pecíolos delgados y largos de hasta 15 cm, con una vaina basal que envuelve al tallo. Flores emergentes, hasta 7 mm de diámetro, tienen 5 pétalos de color blanco; pistilos numerosos, amarillos. Fruto un pequeño aquenio semiovoideo de 1 mm de diámetro. Especies similares: Ranunculus flagelliformis. ", :distribution_es => " Desde Costa Rica y Venezuela hasta Bolivia. En el Ecuador se encuentra en los Andes, entre 3000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Aquatic or semi-aquatic herbs, stems long-creeping, up to 60 cm. Leaves floating on the water surface, elliptic to ovate, 10-15 × 5-8 mm; petioles thin and long, up to 15 cm, with a basal sheath surrounding the stem. Emergent flowers up to 7 mm diameter, with 5 white petals; pistils numerous, yellow. Fruit a small semi ovoid achene, 1 mm in diameter. Similar species: Ranunculus flagelliformis. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica and Venezuela to Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 192, :name => "peruvianus ", :genus => { :id => 66, :name => "Ranunculus", :family => { :id => 38, :name => "ranunculaceae", :old_id => "293" }, :old_id => "294" }, :scientific => "Ranunculus peruvianus ", :author => "Ranunculus peruvianus Pers.", :tropicos => "27101034", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 6, :name => "aquatic", :old_id => "177" }, :description_es => "Hierbas terrestres, a veces semiacuáticas de hasta 10 cm de alto. Hojas de dos tipos: las de la base miden hasta 1 cm de largo, tienen pecíolos largos y delgados de hasta 5 cm de largo y las láminas tienen la forma arriñonada con los márgenes crenados; las otras son alternas en el tallo y profundamente divididas. Flores solitarias y terminales, miden hasta 15 mm de diámetro, con 5 pétalos de forma espatulada, de color amarillo limón y brillantes; pistilos numerosos, amarillos. El fruto se presenta como un conjunto de pequeños frutos secos que mide cada uno alrededor de 1 mm de largo. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes del sur de Colombia hasta el Perú. En el Ecuador se distribuye en los páramos entre 2700 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Terrestrial herbs, sometimes semi-aquatic, up to 10 cm high. Leaves of two types: the basal ones up to 1 cm long, with long slender petioles up to 5 cm, and the blades are kidney-shaped with crenate margins; the other leaves are alternate on the stem and deeply divided. Flowers solitary and terminal, up to 15 mm diameter, with 5 petals, spatulate, bright lemon yellow; pistils numerous, yellow. Fruit a set of small nuts each measuring about 1 mm long. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 193, :name => "nivalis ", :genus => { :id => 41, :name => "Lachemilla", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "186" }, :scientific => "Lachemilla nivalis ", :author => "Lachemilla nivalis (Kunth) Rothm.", :tropicos => "27801671", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => { :id => 7, :name => "brown", :old_id => "52" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas erectas, hasta 0,60 m de alto, con varios tallos desde la base; toda la planta es muy pubescente con largos tricomas de color blanco. Hojas reducidas, hasta 10 mm de largo, unidas formando vainas alrededor del tallo con 10-15 lóbulos angostamente lanceolados. Inflorescencia terminal o axilar con las brácteas florales lobadas. Flores pequeñas 1,8-2,5 mm de largo, de color verde o teñidas de marrón-rojizo; carpelos 3-4 hasta 6; estigma claviforme. Especies similares: Lachemilla hispidula. ", :distribution_es => " De Venezuela a Perú. En el Ecuador se ha registrado desde los 3200 hasta los 4700 m.", :description_en => "Erect herbs, up to 0.60 m high, with several stems from the base. The entire plant is pubescent with long white trichomes. Leaves reduced, up to 10 mm long, forming sheaths together around the stem with 10-15 lobes narrowly lanceolate. Inflorescences terminal with lobed axillary floral bracts. Small flowers 1.8-2.5 mm long, green or reddish-brown; carpels 3-4 to 6; stigma clavate. Similar species: Lachemilla hispidula. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 194, :name => "incana ", :genus => { :id => 62, :name => "Polylepis", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "276" }, :scientific => "Polylepis incana ", :author => "Polylepis incana Kunth", :tropicos => "27800829", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles hasta de 12 m de alto, el tronco retorcido con la corteza color anaranjado que se desprende en láminas delgadas como papel. Hojas compuestas imparipinnadas, hasta 2 cm, de forma lanceolada u oblonga, crecen amontonadas en las puntas de las ramas, cubiertas por tricomas cortos, escasos, el haz liso. Inflorescencias en racimos simples hasta 8 cm con 4 a 7 flores.  Flores alrededor de 6 mm de longitud, verdosas. Fruto en aquenio dehiscente de 3-5 × 1,5-3 mm. Semillas 2-3 mm de largo. Especies similares: Polylepis racemosa Ruiz & Pav. ", :distribution_es => " Andes desde el norte del Ecuador hasta el sur del Perú y Bolivia.", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees up to 12 m tall; trunk twisted with flaky orange bark like thin paper like sheets. Leaves compound imparipinnate, up to 2 cm, lanceolate or oblong, crowded at tips of the branches, covered below with short, sparse, trichomes, smooth above. Inflorescences simple, in clusters up to 8 cm with 4-7 flowers. Flowers about 6 mm long, greenish. Fruit in dehiscente achenes, 3-5 × 1.5-3 mm. Seeds 2-3 mm long. Similar species: Polylepis racemosa. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Peru and Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 195, :name => "lanuginosa ", :genus => { :id => 62, :name => "Polylepis", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "276" }, :scientific => "Polylepis lanuginosa ", :author => "Polylepis lanuginosa Kunth", :tropicos => "27800736", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Árboles o arbustos de hasta 8 m de alto; los troncos son retorcidos y tienen la corteza color anaranjado, que se desprende en láminas delgadas como papel. Pecíolo de 0,5-1 cm de largo. Hojas 3-6,5 × 3-5,5 cm con 2-4 pares de folíolos; folíolo elíptico de 1,6-3,3 × 0,7-1,8 cm, glabro en el haz y cubierto de tricomas blanquecino-amarillentos en el envés, el raquis con entrenudos seríceos. Inflorescencias en racimos colgantes, ramificados en la base, 5-15 cm de largo con 10 a 20 flores; brácteas florales 5-12 mm de largo, villosas. Flores 5-8 mm de largo, verdosas; sépalos ovados o elípticos; estambres 9-24, las anteras lanosas, mayormente en el ápice; estilo villoso en la base. Fruto fusiforme, 3-6 × 4-8 mm; semillas 2-3 mm de largo. Polylepis lanuginosa se reconoce fácilmente por su abundante pubescencia lanosa de aspecto ferruginoso, concentrado en el envés de sus hojas y base de las ramitas. ", :distribution_es => " Andes del centro y sur del Ecuador. En las provincias de Azuay, Bolívar, Cañar y Chimborazo, entre 2700 y 3800 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Trees or shrubs, up to 8 m tall; trunks twisted with orange flaky bark, like thin paper like sheets. Petiole 0.5-1 cm long. Leaves 3 -6.5 × 3-5.5 cm with 2-4 pairs of leaflets; leaflets elliptical, 1.6-3.3 × 0.7-1.8 cm, glabrous above and covered with whitish-yellow trichomes on the lower surface, with sericeous rachis internodes. Inflorescences in hanging clusters, branched at base, 5-15 cm long with 10 to 20 flowers; bracts 5-12 mm long, villous. Flowers 5-8 mm long, greenish; sepals ovate or elliptical; stamens 9-24, anthers wooly, mostly at the apex; style villous at base. Fruit fusiform, 3-6 × 4-8 mm; seeds 2-3 mm long. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }] }
{ :id => 196, :name => "weberbaueri ", :genus => { :id => 62, :name => "Polylepis", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "276" }, :scientific => "Polylepis weberbaueri ", :author => "Polylepis weberbaueri Pilg.", :tropicos => "27800842", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Árboles o arbustos hasta de 6 m de alto; vaina estipular panosa principalmente en el ápice. Hojas muy amontonadas en la punta de las ramas, 1,5-5 × 0,6-2,5 cm, con 2-4 pares de folíolos; pecíolo 0,2-0,6 cm de largo; raquis con entrenudos panosos o densamente lanosos. Folíolos ovados, 0,7-1,5 cm de largo, la base cordada, los márgenes enteros, revolutos, el envés densamente panoso, el haz piloso. Inflorescencia en racimos simples de 2-8 cm de largo con 4-10 flores. Brácteas florales de 3-4 mm de largo. Flores de 4-6 mm de largo; estambres 8-16, las anteras barbadas; estilo villoso. Fruto turbinado 3-5 × 3-4 mm; semillas 2-3 mm de largo. Especies similares: Polylepis reticulata. ", :distribution_es => " Andes del centro y sur del Ecuador y norte del Perú. En el Ecuador se ha registrado en Azuay, Cañar y Chimborazo, entre 3000 y 4000 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Trees or shrubs, up to 6 m high; stipular sheath panose primarily at the apex. Leaves crowded at tips of branches, 1.5-5 × 0.6-2.5 cm, with 2-4 pairs of leaflets; petiole 0.2-0.6 cm long; rachis panose or densely woolly. Leaflets ovate, 0.7-1.5 cm long, base cordate, margins entire, revolute, below densely panose, above pilose. Inflorescence in simple clusters, 2-8 cm long with 4-10 flowers. Bracts 3-4 mm long. Flowers 4-6 mm long; stamens 8-16, anthers barbed; style villous. Fruit turbinate 3-5 × 3-4 mm; seeds 2-3 mm long. Similar species: Polylepis reticulata. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and N Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 197, :name => "granadensis ", :genus => { :id => 117, :name => "Nertera", :family => { :id => 1, :name => "rubiaceae", :old_id => "6" } }, :scientific => "Nertera granadensis ", :author => "Nertera granadensis (Mutis ex L. f.) Druce", :tropicos => "27902981", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas postradas, algunas veces forman tapetes esparcidos, enraizando en los nudos; tallos herbáceos; estípulas envainadas en la base, interpeciolares, ampliamente triangulares, enteras o bidentadas. Hojas opuestas, de espatuladas a anchamente ovadas, hasta 8 mm de largo, algo carnosas. Inflorescencias de flores solitarias, terminales. Flores 4-meras; cáliz extremadamente reducido; corola campanulada, de color blanco-crema a blanco-verdoso, los lóbulos patentes, estrechamente ovados; anteras alargadas, exertas; estilo 2-lobulado, exerto. Fruto en drupa, carnosa, globosa, hasta 8 mm de diámetro, anaranjada o roja. ", :distribution_es => " Presenta una distribución transcontinental, Nueva Zelandia, oeste de Australia, Indonesia, Malasia, Papua, Nueva Guinea, Filipinas y Taiwán. En América se distribuye desde Costa Rica hasta Argentina y Chile. En el Ecuador se distribuye en la cordillera de los Andes entre 2000 y 4500 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Prostrate herbs, sometimes forming scattered mats, rooting at nodes; stems herbaceous; stipules sheathed at base, interpetiolar, broadly triangular, entire or bidentate. Leaves opposite, spatulate to broadly ovate, up to 8 mm long, somewhat fleshy. Inflorescences of solitary flowers, terminal. Flowers 4-merous; calyx extremely reduced; corolla campanulate, white-cream to white-green, lobes patent, narrowlty ovate; anthers elongated, exserted. Style 2-lobed, exserted. Fruit a drupe, fleshy, globose, up to 8 mm in diameter, orange or red. ", :distribution_en => " transcontinental distribution. In America from Costa Rica to Argentina and Chile.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 198, :name => "nana ", :genus => { :id => 118, :name => "Symplocos", :family => { :id => 53, :name => "symplocaceae" } }, :scientific => "Symplocos nana ", :author => "Symplocos nana Brand", :tropicos => "30900094", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta de 3 m de alto, brotes tiernos y ramitas glabros, corteza lisa de color marrón, con las cicatrices de las hojas prominentes. Hojas alternas, ovadas u oblanceoladas, 0,8-1,2 × 0,3-0,6 cm, coriáceas, glabras, los márgenes crenados; pecíolo 1-2 mm de largo. Flores solitarias con pedicelo corto; corola rosada, glabra, 5-7 mm de largo; estambres 35-40 en 3 verticilos. Frutos cilíndricos, 10,5-16 × 5,5-11 mm, glabros, de color negro cuando maduros. ", :distribution_es => " De Ecuador a Bolivia. En el Ecuador se ha registrado en Azuay, Loja y Morona Santiago.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 3 m tall, tender shoots and twigs glabrous, bark smooth, brown, with prominent leaf scars. Leaves alternate, ovate or oblanceolate, 0.8-1.2 × 0.3-0.6 cm, leathery, glabrous, margins crenate; petiole 1-2 mm long. Flowers solitary with short pedicel; corolla pink, glabrous, 5-7 mm long; stamens 35-40 in 3 whorls. Fruits cylindrical, 10.5-16 × 5.5-11 mm, glabrous, black when mature. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }] }
{ :id => 199, :name => "bangii", :genus => { :id => 75, :name => "Viola", :family => { :id => 43, :name => "violaceae", :old_id => "338" }, :old_id => "339" }, :scientific => "Viola bangii", :author => "Viola bangii Rusby", :tropicos => "33801117", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 9, :name => "blue", :old_id => "127" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Plantas en roseta, solitarias o en pequeñas almohadillas debido a la ramificación. Hojas de oblongo-lanceoladas a espatuladas, hasta de 20 × 4 mm, verde-brillante con un falso pecíolo membranoso de color púrpura. Flores solitarias entre las hojas, de color blanco, manchado con azul, la garganta amarilla. Fruto en cápsula que emerge ligeramente de las hojas. Especies similares: Viola pygmaea. ", :distribution_es => " En los Andes de Ecuador a Bolivia. En el Ecuador se ha registrado a alturas mayores a 3900 m s.n.m.", :description_en => "Plants in rosettes, solitary or in small cushions due to branching. Leaves oblong-lanceolate to spatulate, up to 20 × 4 mm, bright green with a false membranous petiole, purple. Solitary flowers among the leaves, white, spotted with blue, throat yellow. Fruit in capsule slightly emerging from the leaves. Similar species: Viola pygmaea. ", :distribution_en => " I Ecuador to Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }] }
{ :id => 200, :name => "nodosus", :genus => { :id => 119, :name => "Aetanthus", :family => { :id => 54, :name => "loranthaceae" } }, :scientific => "Aetanthus nodosus", :author => "Aetanthus nodosus (Desr.) Engl.", :tropicos => "19100497", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos parásitos. Ramitas colgantes, dicotómicas, las más jóvenes rojizas. Hojas simples, opuestas, decusadas, elípticas, o menos frecuente ovadas, 5–10 × 3.5–6 cm, crasas, muy quebradizas, enteras, papilosas, la base redondeado-decurrente, el ápice agudo u obtuso; nervadura no visible. Inflorescencia un fascículo; pedicelos y el cáliz rojizos o púrpuras a negros. Flores tubulares, carnosas; cáliz ca. 6 mm de largo, ciatiforme; corola 6–8 cm de largo, roja en ¾ de su longitud, apicalmente amarilla; estambres amarillos; estilo delgado, rojo con bandas amarillas. Fruto una baya ovoide, ca. 1.2 cm, púrpura-negra, jugosa. Semilla solitaria. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. ", :description_en => "Parasitic shrubs. Branches hanging, dichotomous, the younger ones reddish. Leaves simple, opposite, decussate, elliptical, or less frequently ovate, 5-10 × 3.5-6 cm, succulent, very brittle, entire, papillose, base rounded-decurrent, apex acute or obtuse; venation not visible. Inflorescence a fascicle; pedicels and calyx red or purple to black. Flowers tubular, fleshy; calyx ca. 6 mm long, cyathiform; corolla 6-8 cm long, 3/4 red, yellow apically; stamens yellow; style slender, red with yellow bands. Fruit an ovoid berry, ca. 1.2 cm, purple-black, juicy. Seed solitary. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 201, :name => "macrophylla", :genus => { :id => 120, :name => "Axinaea", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" } }, :scientific => "Axinaea macrophylla", :author => "Axinaea macrophylla (Naudin) Triana", :tropicos => "20300343", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles de 2.5–5 m de alto, algunas veces llegan hasta 15 m. Tallos jóvenes cuadrangulares, las líneas interpeciolares elevadas ca. de 1 mm; glabros o esparcidamente furfuráceos, especialmente en las partes jóvenes. Hojas simples, opuestas, 4.5–10 × 3–5 cm, ovado-elípticas, subcoriáceas, lustrosas, la base aguda a obtusa, los márgenes dentados, ligeramente revolutos en la base, el ápice agudo, ligeramente acuminado, 7-nervias (incluye el par marginal tenue); pecíolos rojizos, 1.5–1.8 cm de largo, ligeramente acanalados. Inflorescencia en panícula terminal, con pocas flores, por lo general pendulares, 4–6 cm de largo. Flores pentámeras, vistosas, 1.5–2.5 cm de largo (incluye el hipanto); pedicelos 0.5–1.2 cm de largo; hipantos color rosado-violeta, urceolados, 5–6 mm de largo; cáliz violeta, truncado, 2-3 mm de largo, con dientes diminutos de color verde; pétalos color violeta a rosados, 1.2–1.7 cm de largo; estambres ligeramente isomórficos, los filamentos rosados, las anteras amarillas, los conectivos globosos, amarillos; estilo rosado. Frutos capsulares, acostillados. ", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. ", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees 2.5-5 m tall, sometimes reaching 15 m. Young stems quadrangular, interpetiolars lines ca. 1 mm high; glabrous or sparsely furfuraceous, especially in the young parts. Leaves simple, opposite, 4.5-10 × 3-5 cm, ovate-elliptic, subcoriaceous, lustrous, base from acute to obtuse, margins toothed slightly revolute at the base, acute apex, slightly acuminate, 7-nerved (includes marginal pair); petioles reddish, 1.5-1.8 cm long, slightly grooved. Inflorescence a terminal panicle, with few flowers, usually pendulous, 4-6 cm long. Flowers 5-merous, colorful, 1.5-2.5 cm long (including hypanthium); pedicels 0.5-1.2 cm long; hypanthia pink-violet, urceolate, 5-6 mm long; calyx violet, truncate, 2-3 mm long, with minute green teeth; petals violet to pink, 1.2-1.7 cm long; stamens slightly isomorphic, filaments pink, anthers yellow, connective globose yellow.; style pink. Fruit capsular, ribbed. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 202, :name => "quitensis", :genus => { :id => 120, :name => "Axinaea", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" } }, :scientific => "Axinaea quitensis", :author => "Axinaea quitensis Benoist  ", :tropicos => "20303909", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Árboles de 5–10 m de alto, glabro. Tallos teretes, flexibles; líneas interpeciolares elevadas ca de 0.2 mm; corteza café-rojiza, lisa. Flores pentámeras, vistosas, 1.5–1.8 cm de largo (incluye el hipanto); pedicelos 0.8–2 cm de largo; hipantos verdes, urceolados, 3–4 mm de largo. Hojas simples, opuestas, 4.5–8 × 3–4 cm, elípticas a ovado-elípticas, subcoriáceas, lustrosas, la base ligeramente atenuada con los márgenes recurvados hacia abajo, los márgenes diminutamente dentados, el ápice agudo,  5-nervias (incluye el par marginal tenue); pecíolos rojizos, 1.7–2.2 cm de largo. Inflorescencia en panícula terminal, por lo general con flores pendulares, 4–6 cm de largo. Cáliz verde, con los márgenes de los lóbulos rojizos, 1–2 mm de largo; pétalos rosado-blanquecinos a blanco-lila con los márgenes más oscuros, 1–1.3 cm de largo, traslapados en botón y semi-abiertos en la floración; estambres ligeramente isomórficos, los filamentos rosados, las anteras color vino, los conectivos globosos, amarillos; estilo rosado. Frutos capsulares, acostillados; semillas numerosas, ovoide-triangulares. Categoría UICN NT (Casi Amenazado). ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Trees 5-10 m tall, glabrous; stems terete, flexible; interpetiolare lines ca 0.2 mm high; bark red-brown smooth. Leaves simple, opposite, 4.5-8 × 3-4 cm, elliptic to ovate-elliptic, subcoriaceous, glossy, base slightly attenuated with recurved margins facing down, margins minutely toothed, apex acute, 5-nerved (includes marginal pair); petioles reddish, 1.7-2.2 cm long. Inflorescence a terminal panicle, usually with pendulous flowers, 4-6 cm long. Flowers 5-merous, colorful, 1.5-1.8 cm long (including hypanthium); pedicels 0.8-2 cm long. Hipantia green, urceolate, 3-4 mm long. Calyx green with lobes margins reddish, 1-2 mm long. Petals whitish-pink to white-lilac with darker margins, 1-1.3 cm long, petals overlapping and semi-open in bloom. Stamens slightly isomorphic, filaments pink, anthers wine color, connective globose, yellow; style pink. Fruit capsular, ribbed; seeds numerous, ovoid-triangular. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 203, :name => "pichinchensis", :genus => { :id => 6, :name => "Berberis", :family => { :id => 5, :name => "berberidaceae", :old_id => "38" }, :old_id => "39" }, :scientific => "Berberis pichinchensis", :author => "Berberis pichinchensis Turcz.", :tropicos => "3500117", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 3 m, densamente ramificados, espinosos; madera amarilla. Inflorescencia terminal, racimosa, péndula, con numerosas flores; pedúnculo rojizo. Hojas alteras, amontonadas en los nudos, elípticas, hasta 8 cm de largo, rígidas, los márgenes serrado-espinosos, el haz verde oscuro con nervaduras más claras, el envés verde claro, la nervadura reticulada; pecíolo articulado en la base. Flores amarillo-anaranjadas, con tintes rosados por fuera, 3-meras, ca. 5 mm de diámetro; perianto petaloide; estambres 6, amarillos; estigma grande redondeado. Fruto una baya jugosa, ovoide, ca. 5 mm de largo, verde con tintes rojizos y tornándose negro-morada al madurar. ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador. ", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 3 m, densely branched, thorny; wood yellow. Inflorescence terminal, racemose, pendulous, with numerous flowers; peduncle reddish. Leaves alternate, crowded at nodes, elliptical, up to 8 cm long, rigid, margins serrate-spiny, dark green with lighter veins, light green below, venation reticulated; petiole articulated at base. Flowers yellow-orange with pink tints on the outside, 3-merous, ca. 5 mm in diameter; perianth petaloid; stamens 6, yellow; stigma large rounded. Fruit a juicy berry, ovoid, ca. 5mm long, green with reddish tints and turning black-purple when mature. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 204, :name => "ledifolium", :genus => { :id => 8, :name => "Brachyotum", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "49" }, :scientific => "Brachyotum ledifolium", :author => "Brachyotum ledifolium (Desr.) Triana", :tropicos => "20302170", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbusto de 1–3 m de alto. Ramitas jóvenes, hojas, hipanto y cáliz cubiertos de indumento estrigoso; corteza fisurada, desprendiéndose en pequeñas láminas delgadas, longitudinales. Hojas simples, opuestas, ovado-elípticas, cartáceas, 1.5–5 × 1–2 cm, la base obtusa, los márgenes  setulosos, el ápice agudo a obtuso, el haz y el  envés estrigosos, trinervias desde la base, con varias nervaduras transversales. Flores solitarias en las axilas de las hojas apicales, péndulas, pediceladas, con un par de brácteas caducas; hipanto campanulado, rojo-anaranjado, 4–8 mm de largo; cáliz con 5 lóbulos conspicuos, triangulares, 5–7 mm de largo; corola con 5 pétalos imbricados, 9–17 mm de largo, amarillo- claro; estilo filiforme, amarillo claro, exerto. Fruto una cápsula seca, encerrado por el tálamo del hipantio; semillas numerosas, diminutas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. ", :description_en => "Shrubs 1-3 m tall. Young twigs, leaves, hypanthium and calyx covered with strigose indumentum; bark fissured, shedding in small thin longitudinal strips. Leaves simple, opposite, ovate-elliptic, cartaceous, 1.5-5 × 1-2 cm, base obtuse, margins setulous, apex acute to obtuse, leaf surfaces above and below strigose,  trinerved from base, with several transverse nerves. Solitary flowers in the axils of apical leaves, pendulous, pedicels, with a couple of deciduous bracts. Hypanthium campanulate, red-orange, 4-8 mm long; calyx of 5 conspicuous lobes, triangular, 5-7 mm; corolla with 5 petals, imbricated, 9-17 mm long, light yellow; style filiform, exserted, light yellow. Fruit is a dry capsule, enclosed by the thalamus of the hypanthium; seeds minute, numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 205, :name => "lindenii", :genus => { :id => 8, :name => "Brachyotum", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "49" }, :scientific => "Brachyotum lindenii", :author => "Brachyotum lindenii Cogn.", :tropicos => "20300413", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de 0.7–2 m de alto. Ramitas jóvenes; envés de las hojas e hipanto cubiertos de tricomas estrigosos; corteza fisurada, desprendiéndose en pequeñas láminas delgadas, longitudinales. Hojas simples, opuestas, ovado-elípticas, cartáceas, 0.7–1.8 × 0.4–0.8 cm, la base obtusa; los márgenes crenulados, setulosos, el ápice agudo; el haz glabro, lustroso, el envés estrigoso sobre los nervios primarios, 3-nervias desde la base con varias nervaduras laterales. Inflorescencia en cimas cortas de 3 a 5 flores, en los ápices de las ramas. Flores, péndulas, pediceladas, con un par de brácteas deciduas; hipanto campanulado, 4–6 mm de largo, rojo-rosado; cáliz con 5 lóbulos triangular-lanceolados, 4–8 mm de largo, ciliados; corola con 5 pétalos, 10–16 mm de largo, negro-morados, ciliados, libres e imbricados formando un falso tubo; estambres el doble número de pétalos; estilo filiforme, rosado o lila, exerto. Fruto una cápsula seca; semillas numerosas, diminutas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador. ", :description_en => "Shrubs 0.7 to 2 m high. Young twigs, undersides of leaves and hypanthium covered with strigose trichomes; bark fissured, shedding in small thin longitudinal strips. Leaves simple, opposite, ovate-elliptic, cartaceous, 0.7-1.8 × 0.4-0.8 cm, base obtuse; margins crenulated, setulous, apex acute. leaf surface clabrous, glossy above, strigose below on the primary nerves, 3-nerved from the base with several lateral nerves. Inflorescence in short cymes with 3 to 5 flowers on the end of branches. Flowers pendulous, pedicels with a couple of deciduous bracts; hypanthium campanulate, 4-6 mm long, red-pink; calyx with 5 lobes, triangular-lanceolate, 4-8 mm long, ciliate; corolla with 5 petals 10-16 mm long, black-purple, ciliate, free and imbricated forming a false tube; stamens twice the number of petals; style filiform, pink or lilac, exserted. Fruit a dry capsule; seeds minute, numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 206, :name => "incana", :genus => { :id => 121, :name => "Buddleja", :family => { :id => 55, :name => "scrophulariaceae" } }, :scientific => "Buddleja incana", :author => "Buddleja incana Ruiz & Pav.", :tropicos => "19000596", :color1 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles, hasta 8 m de altura. Tallos, hojas y flores recubiertos de un denso tomento lanoso, blanquecino. Hojas simples, opuestas, lanceoladas, 5–15 × 2–5 cm, coriáceas, la base cuneada, los márgenes crenulados o serrados, el ápice acuminado, el haz con las nervaduras prominentes, ampolloso, el envés grisáceo densamente lanoso con tricomas estrellados. Inflorescencia una panícula cimosa, terminal, ca. 5 cm de largo, con 2–3 ejes de ramificación, terminado en cabezuelas compactas, cada cabezuela con 15–40 flores; bractéolas ligulares, 1–3 cm de largo. Flores ca. 3.5 mm de largo; cáliz con 5 lóbulos cremas y pubescencia blanquecina; corola anaranjada, 3–4 mm de largo, con 4 lóbulos reflexos; estambres 4. Fruto capsular, 4–5 mm de largo, bivalvado. ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador y Perú. ", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees up to 8 m tall. Stems, leaves and flowers covered by a dense woolly, whitish tomentum. Leaves simple, opposite, lanceolate, 5-15 × 2-5 cm, leathery, base cuneate, margins crenulated or serrated, apex acuminate, leaf surface prominently nerved and bullate above,  densely woolly below with gray stellate trichomes. Inflorescence a cymose panicle, terminal, ca. 5 cm long, with 2-3 branching axes, ending in compact heads, each with 15-40 flowers; bractlets ligulate, 1-3 cm long. Flowers ca. 3.5 mm long; calyx with 5 lobes cream color and whitish pubescence. Corolla orange, 3-4 mm long, with 4 reflexed lobes and 4 stamens. Fruit capsular, 4-5 mm long, bivalvate. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador and Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 207, :name => "bullata", :genus => { :id => 121, :name => "Buddleja", :family => { :id => 55, :name => "scrophulariaceae" } }, :scientific => "Buddleja bullata", :author => "Buddleja bullata Kunth", :tropicos => "19000597", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles hasta 8 m de altura. Corteza finamente agrietada. Ramitas jóvenes con tricomas estrellados densos que dan un aspecto lanuginoso o lanoso. Hojas simples, opuestas, lanceoladas u oblongas-lanceoladas, 12–18 × 3–6 cm, coriáceas, la base obtusa, los márgenes crenulados, el ápice agudo, el haz bullado; el envés grisáceo, tomentoso, lanuginoso o lanoso, con tricomas estrellados; nervaduras prominentes. Inflorescencia una panícula cimosa, terminal, con 4-5 ejes de ramificación, 5–15 cm de largo, terminando en cabezas, cada cabeza con 6–18 flores; bractéolas ligulares, 1–2 cm de largo. Flores ca. 3.5 mm de largo; cáliz con 5 lóbulos, 1.5–2.5 mm de largo, crema, con pubescencia blanquecina; corola 2.5–3.4 mm de largo, crema o amarilla al madurar, con 4 lóbulos reflexos; estambres 4. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú. ", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees up to 8 m tall. Bark finely fissured. Young twigs with dense stellate trichomes giving a woolly appearance. Leaves simple, opposite, lanceolate or oblong-lanceolate, 12-18 × 3-6 cm, leathery, base obtuse, margins crenulated, apex acute, leaf surface bullate above, greyish, tomentose, lanate with stellate trichomes below; venetion prominent. Inflorescence a cymose panicle, terminal, with 4-5 branching axes, 5-15 cm long, ending in heads, each head with 6-18 flowers; bracteoles ligulate, 1-2 cm long. Flowers ca. 3.5 mm long; calyx 5-lobed, 1.5-2.5 mm long, cream colored, with whitish pubescence; corolla 2.5-3.4 mm long, cream colored or yellow when mature, with 4 reflexed lobes; stamens 4. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 208, :name => "perfoliata", :genus => { :id => 11, :name => "Calceolaria", :family => { :id => 9, :name => "calceolariaceae", :old_id => "63" }, :old_id => "64" }, :scientific => "Calceolaria perfoliata", :author => "Calceolaria perfoliata L. f.", :tropicos => "29201863", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas robustas escandentes, hasta 5 m de altura, con tricomas blanquecinos en toda la planta. Inflorescencia cimosa, hasta 20 cm de largo, con numerosas flores. Hojas opuestas, triangular-ovadas, 3–12 × 2.5–8 cm, cartáceas, la base cordata a truncada, los márgenes doblemente serrados, el haz verde claro, el envés blanco-lanado; pecíolos unidos alrededor del tallo. Flores vistosas; sépalos ovados, hasta 15 mm, amarillo-limón, pilosos, ciliados; corola globosa, hasta 18 mm, amarillo brillante, bilabiada, el labio inferior inflado; estambres 2, las anteras grandes, cafés. Fruto una cápsula, ovoide, hasta 7 mm de ancho, pilosa a vellosa, amarillo-limón cuando inmadura. ", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Scandent robust herbs, up to 5 m tall, with whitish trichomes throughout the plant. Inflorescence cymose, up to 20 cm long, with numerous flowers. Leaves opposite, triangular-ovate, 3-12 × 2.5-8 cm, papery, base truncate to cordate, margins twice serrate, light green above, white-wooly below; petioles clasping the stem. Flowers conspicous; sepals ovate, up to 15 mm, lemon-yellow, pilose, ciliate; corolla globose, up to 18 mm, bright yellow, bilabiate, lower lip inflated; stamens 2, anthers large, brown. Fruit a capsule, ovoid, up to 7 mm wide, pilous to villous, lemon-yellow when immature. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }] }
{ :id => 209, :name => "fissifolia", :genus => { :id => 13, :name => "Castilleja", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" }, :old_id => "72" }, :scientific => "Castilleja fissifolia", :author => "Castilleja fissifolia L. f.", :tropicos => "29202221", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas hasta 40 cm de alto. Tallos erectos o ascendentes, a veces escandentes, por lo general varios desde una base gruesa, leñosa, y con frecuencia ramificados. Tricomas finos y ligeramente recurvados o glabros. Hojas simples, alternas, lanceoladas, 2–3 cm de largo, caulinares, pilosas, de color verdes o púrpura distalmente, enteras o divididas en 1–2 pares de lóbulos laterales, angostos, filiformes. Inflorescencia en racimos cortos; brácteas superiores distalmente rojo o rojo naranja, más llamativas que las flores; pedicelos 5–15 mm de largo; cáliz verde o verde amarillento, con márgenes de color amarillento o rojizo; corola 21–35 mm largo, verde o verde amarillenta, el labio inferior reducido y con tres dientes. Frutos, cápsulas ovoideas, ca. 15 mm de largo; semillas numerosas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia, Ecuador.", :description_en => "Herbs up to 40 cm tall. Stems erect or ascending, sometimes scandent, usually several stems from a thick woody base, and often branched. Trichomes fine and slightly recurved or glabrous. Leaves simple, alternate, lanceolate, 2-3 cm long, caulinar, pilose, green or distally purple, entire or divided into 1-2 pairs of lateral, narrow, thread-like lobes. Inflorescence in short racemes; upper bracts distally red or orange red, more conspicuous than the flowers; pedicels 5-15 mm long; calyx green or yellowish green, with yellowish or reddish margins; corolla 21-35 mm long, green or yellow-green, lower lip with 3 reduced teeth. Fruits ovoid capsules, ca. 15 mm long; seeds numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 210, :name => "alatum", :genus => { :id => 122, :name => "Ceratostema", :family => { :id => 13, :name => "ericaceae", :old_id => "91" } }, :scientific => "Ceratostema alatum", :author => "Ceratostema alatum (Hoerold) Sleumer  ", :tropicos => "12303248", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos de 1–1.5 m de alto, raramente epífitos, los tallos estriados, glabros, la corteza grisácea con finos agrietamientos. Hojas alternas, gruesas, coriáceas, elípticas 2–5 × 1–3 cm, la base anchamente cuneada o redondeada, el ápice agudo a redondeado, los márgenes enteros a ligeramente crenados o menudamente serrados; pecíolo corto, erecto, grueso. Inflorescencias axilares, racimosas, con 4–7 flores, glabras. Flores tubulares, conspicuas; cáliz 6–9 mm de largo; corola pentagonal, basalmente dilatada, 35–54 × 12–16 mm de diámetro basal, carnosa, de un carmesí escarlata oscuro, los lóbulos extendidos y marcadamente deflexos, los estambres y el estilo expuestos; pedicelos gruesos, articulados con el cáliz. Frutos bayas pentagonales, ca. 1.5 × 2 cm de diámetro, verde tornando rojizo, ligeramente dulces, el pedicelo craso, rojizo.", :distribution_es => nil, :description_en => "Shrubs 1-1.5 m tall, rarely epiphytic, stems striated, glabrous, bark grayish with fine cracks. Leaves alternate, thick, leathery, 2-5 × 1-3 cm elliptical, cuneate or rounded broadly base, rounded to acute apex, margins entire to lightly crenate or minutely serrated; petiole short, erect, thick. Inflorescences axillary, racemose, with 4-7 flowers, glabrous. Flowers tubular, conspicuous; calyx 6-9 mm long; corolla pentagonal, dilated basally, 35-54 × 12-16 mm diameter at base, fleshy, dark scarlet crimson, and markedly deflexed extended lobes, stamens and style exposed; pedicels thick, articulated with the calyx. Berries pentagonal, ca. 1.5 × 2 cm in diameter, green turning reddish, slightly sweet, pedicel thick, reddish.", :distribution_en => nil, :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 211, :name => "oblonga subsp. sericea", :genus => { :id => 123, :name => "Columellia", :family => { :id => 56, :name => "columelliaceae" } }, :scientific => "Columellia oblonga subsp. sericea", :author => "Columellia oblonga subsp. sericea (Kunth) Brizicky", :tropicos => "8100010", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles de hasta 5 m de altura y 15 cm de diámetro. Ramitas jóvenes amarillentas, con tricomas seríceos. Corteza externa grisácea, frecuentemente papirácea. Hojas simples, opuestas, obovadas a espatuladas, 2.5–3 × 0.8–1.5 cm,  semicoriáceas, la base decurrente sobre el pecíolo, los márgenes enteros, el ápice obtuso y mucronado, el haz glabro, lustroso, el envés pubescente, seríceo y blanquecino; pecíolo ca. 10 mm de largo. Inflorescencias en cimas cortas, terminales; los pedicelos ca. 5 mm de largo. Flores vistosas; cáliz verde, densamente pubescente, lóbulos lanceolados, 2–3 mm de largo; corola tubular, amarilla, con 5 lóbulos; estambres 2, amarillos, las anteras conspicuamente plegadas; estigma verde, bilobulado. Fruto una cápsula bilocular, septicida, verde, con numerosas semillas. ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador a Bolivia. ", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees up to 5 m tall and 15 cm in diameter. Young twigs yellowish with sericeous trichomes. Outer bark greyish, often papery. Leaves dimple, opposite, obovate to spatulate, 2.5-3 × 0.8-1.5 cm, semicoriaceous, base decurrent ontopetiole, margins entire, apex obtuse and mucronate, glabrous, leas surface glossy above, pubescent, sericeous and white below; petiole ca. 10 mm long. Inflorescences in short cymes, terminal. Pedicels ca. 5mm long. Flowers conspicuos, densely pubescent, lobes lanceolate, 2-3 mm long, calyx green; corolla tubular, yellow, 5-lobed; stamens 2, yellow, anthers conspicuously folded; stigma green bilobed. Fruit a bilocular capsule, septicidal, green, with numerous seeds. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 212, :name => "ruscifolia", :genus => { :id => 124, :name => "Coriaria", :family => { :id => 57, :name => "coriariaceae" } }, :scientific => "Coriaria ruscifolia", :author => "Coriaria ruscifolia L.", :tropicos => "8600003", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Sufrútice de hasta 2 m de altura. Los tallos cuadrangulares, café-rojizos. Las ramas largas, colgantes. Hojas simples, opuestas, ovadas a lanceoladas, ca. 12 × 7 mm, sésiles o subsésiles; la base obtusa-cordada, los márgenes enteros, el ápice agudo a ligeramente acuminado; 3-7 palmatinervias. Inflorescencia racemosa, ca. 25 cm de largo, colgante, con flores numerosas. Flores ca. 5 mm de largo, rojo oscuras; pedicelos ca. 2 mm de largo; estambres 5–7, rosados. Frutos aquenios diminutos, recubiertos por los pétalos engrosados y carnosos, dando una apariencia de pseudo-drupa, ca. 8 mm de diámetro, de color vino-tinto oscuro. ", :distribution_es => " México a Perú. ", :description_en => "Subshrubs up to 2 m high. Stems quadrangular, reddish-brown with long, hanging branches. Leaves simple, opposite, ovate to lanceolate, ca. 12 × 7 mm, sessile or subsessile, 3-7-palmatinerved; base obtuse-cordate, margins entire, apex acute to slightly acuminate. Inflorescence racemous, ca. 25 cm long, hanging, with numerous flowers. Flowers ca. 5 mm long, dark red; pedicels ca. 2 mm long; stamens 5-7, pink. Fruits minute achenes, covered by thickened, fleshy petals, giving an appearance of pseudo-drupes, ca. 8 mm in diameter, dark red wine color. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 213, :name => "confertifolia", :genus => { :id => 20, :name => "Draba", :family => { :id => 10, :name => "brassicaceae", :old_id => "67" }, :old_id => "98" }, :scientific => "Draba confertifolia", :author => "Draba confertifolia Turcz.", :tropicos => "4105039", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas ca. 30 cm de alto. Tallos, hojas e inflorescencias cubiertos de abundantes tricomas seríceos. Las hojas viejas se acumulan en la base alrededor del tallo. Hojas simples, opuestas, espatuladas, 18–45 × 4–5 mm, sésiles, caulinares, la base truncada, los márgenes enteros, el ápice agudo, el haz y el envés cubiertos de abundantes tricomas grisáceos. Inflorescencia en racimo, 8–15 cm de largo, por lo general las flores se amontonan apicalmente; bractéolas lineares, 1–1.2 cm de largo.  Flores ca. 11 mm; pedicelo ca. 13 mm; cáliz verde con tintes color violeta, los lóbulos triangulares, ca. 5 mm; corola cruciforme, blanca; estambres amarillos; estilo color violeta, el estigma puntiforme. Fruto una silicua aplanada, ca. 19 × 4 mm, verde, con diminutos tricomas grisáceos. ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Herbs ca. 30 cm tall. Stems, leaves and inflorescences covered with sericeous abundant trichomes. Older leaves packed at the base around the stem. Leaves simple, opposite, spatulate, 18-45 × 4-5 mm, sessile, cauline, base truncated, margins entire, apex acute, leaf surfaces covered by abundant greyish trichomes. Inflorescences in racemes 8-15 cm long, usually the flowers crowded apically; bracteoles linear, 1-1.2 cm long. Flowers ca. 11 mm; pedicel ca. 13 mm; calyx green with violet tints, lobes triangular, ca. 5 mm; corolla cruciform, white; stamens yellow; style violet and punctate stigma. Fruit a flattened siliqua, ca. 19 × 4 mm, green with minute grayish trichomes. ", :distribution_en => " endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 214, :name => "obovata", :genus => { :id => 20, :name => "Draba", :family => { :id => 10, :name => "brassicaceae", :old_id => "67" }, :old_id => "98" }, :scientific => "Draba obovata", :author => "Draba obovata Benth.", :tropicos => "4100816", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas de ca. 3 cm de alto, solitarias o en grupos pequeños, acaulescentes. Recubiertas con tricomas grises en hojas, flores y frutos.  Hojas basales simples, amontonadas o arrosetadas, espatuladas, ca. 4 × 2 mm, carnosas, la base truncada, el margen entero, el ápice obtuso-mucronado; el haz y envés cubiertos de abundantes tricomas estrellados grisáceos. Inflorescencia en corimbo, terminal, cubierta con tricomas. Flores ca. 4 mm de largo; cáliz verde claro; pétalos 4, traslapados, amarillos o verdosos; el pedicelo ca. 3 mm; estambres 6, amarillos. Fruto una silicua, ovoide y más o menos aplanada, ca. 4 × 2 mm, con abundantes tricomas estrellados, grisáceos, las valvas se separan y dejan un replo membranoso argénteo. Categoría UICN de NT (Casi Amenazado). ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Herbs ca. 3 cm tall, solitary or in small groups, acaulescent. Leaves, flowers and fruits covered with gray trichomes. Leaves simple, basal, crowded or in a rosette, spatulate, ca. 4 × 2 mm, fleshy, base truncate, margins entire, apex obtuse-mucronate, leaf surfaces covered with abundant and greyish stellate trichomes. Inflorescences in corymbs, terminal, covered with trichomes. Flowers ca. 4 mm long; calyx light green; petals 4, overlapping, yellow or greenish; pedicel ca. 3 mm; stamens 6, yellow. Fruit a siliqua, ovoid and more or less flattened, ca. 4 × 2 mm, with abundant and greyish stellate trichomes, the valves separated and leaving a silvery membranous replum. ", :distribution_en => " endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 215, :name => "engelii", :genus => { :id => 96, :name => "Elaphoglossum", :family => { :id => 46, :name => "dryopteridaceae" } }, :scientific => "Elaphoglossum engelii", :author => "Elaphoglossum engelii (H. Karst.) H. Christ", :tropicos => "26607175", :color1 => { :id => 10, :name => "fern/other" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Helechos terrestres. Rizoma rastrero, corto o largo, generalmente grueso, escamoso, las escamas lanceoladas con cilios, café obscuro a rojizas. Filopodios presentes, ocultos bajo las escamas. Hojas con pecíolo no articulado; lámina linear, entera, 6–25 cm de largo; pecíolo cilíndrico, medianamente grueso, densamente escamoso, las escamas lanceoladas, con cilios. Las láminas infértiles, 6–23 cm de largo, coriáceas, lanceoladas a oblongas, la base ampliamente cuneada, el ápice obtuso, escamosas, las escamas denticulares-estrelladas, color marrón. Láminas fértiles cubiertas totalmente de soros, sin inducio, generalmente más alargadas y más estrechas que las infértiles. ", :distribution_es => " México a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Terrestrial ferns. Rhizome creeping, short or long, usually thick, scaly, scales lanceolate with dark to reddish brown cilia. Filopodia present, hidden under the scales. Leaves with unarticulated petiole; blade linear, entire, 6-25 cm long; petiole cylindrical, medium-thick, densely scaly, scales lanceolate, ciliate. Infertile blades 6-23 cm long, leathery, lanceolate to oblong, base widely cuneate, obtuse, apex squamous, scales denticulate-stellate, brown color. Fertile blades entirely covered with sori, without inducium generally more elongated and narrower than the infertile ones. ", :distribution_en => " Mexico to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 19, :name => "galapagos" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 216, :name => "punctatum", :genus => { :id => 125, :name => "Gaiadendron", :family => { :id => 54, :name => "loranthaceae" } }, :scientific => "Gaiadendron punctatum", :author => "Gaiadendron punctatum (Ruiz & Pav.) G. Don", :tropicos => "19100506", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Árboles parásitos sobre raíces de otros árboles, crecen hasta 20 m de altura. La corteza agrietada. Hojas simples, opuestas, elípticas u obovadas, 5–12 × 3–5 cm, crasas, tiesas, punteadas por el envés, la base aguda, los márgenes enteros, el ápice obtuso, glabras; nervadura pinnada, los nervios inconspicuos. Inflorescencia una panícula terminal formada de varias cimas, estas con 3 flores, ca. 15 cm de largo, con 3 bractéolas por cada cima. Flores vistosas; el cáliz tubular, 3–5 mm de largo, verde o amarillo; los pétalos 5–6, lineares, 2–3 cm de largo, amarillo-mostaza, recurvados; estambres 5–6, adnados a los pétalos, 2–3 cm de largo. Fruto una baya globosa o redondeada, ca. 1 cm de largo, amarilla o rojo-anaranjada en la madurez. ", :distribution_es => " Nicaragua a Perú. ", :description_en => "Trees parasitic on roots of other trees, growing up to 20 meters tall. Bark cracked. Leaves simple, opposite, elliptic or obovate, 5-12 × 3-5 cm, succulent, stiff, leaf surface punctate below, base acute, margins entire, apex obtuse, glabrous, pinnately veined, the nerves inconspicuous. Inflorescence a terminal panicle composed of several cymes, with 3 flowers, ca. 15 cm long, with 3 bracteoles in each cyme. Flowers conspicous; calyx tubular, green or yellow, 3-5 mm long; petals 5-6, linear, 2-3 cm long, yellow-mustard, recurved; stamens 5-6, adnate to the petals, 2-3 cm long. Fruit a berry globose or rounded, ca. 1 cm long, yellow or red-orange at maturity. ", :distribution_en => " Nicaragua to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 17, :name => "esmeraldas" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 217, :name => "foliosa", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella foliosa", :author => "Gentianella foliosa (Kunth) Fabris ", :tropicos => "13801780", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 9, :name => "blue", :old_id => "127" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, solitarias o en grupos, hasta 50 cm de alto; tallos decumbentes, erectos. Hojas opuestas, arqueadas, aquellas de la base oblongo-oblanceoladas, hasta 8 cm de largo, las más altas ovado-lanceoladas, con 3 a 7 nervaduras, el ápice subagudo, verdes con tintes morados. Flores terminales o en cimas dicasiales, a veces solitarias, hasta 25 mm de largo. Corola de 20–36 mm de largo, globosa, de un rosa-violeta pálido a un azul-violeta con venas más oscuras, el tubo corto, estambres 5, rosa-violeta, las anteras moradas; ovario amarillento, el estigma bilobulado. Cáliz tubular, hasta 18 mm de largo, los lóbulos hasta 1.3 veces el largo del tubo, lanceolados a agudamente triangulares, rojo-morados. Categoría UICN de LC (Preocupación Menor). ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Perennials herbs, solitary or in groups, up to 50 cm tall. Stems decumbent, erect. Leaves opposite, arched, oblong-oblanceolate at the base, up to 8 cm long, the distal ones ovate-lanceolate, with 3 to 7 nerves, apex subacute, green with purple tints. Flowers terminal or in dichasial cymes, sometimes solitary, up to 25 mm long. Corolla 20-36 mm long, globose, pale pink-violet to blue-violet with darker veins, tube short, stamens 5, pink-violet, anthers purple; ovary yellow, stigma bilobed. Calyx tubular, up to 18 mm long, the lobes up to 1.3 times the length of the tube, lanceolate to sharply triangular, red-purple. ", :distribution_en => " endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 218, :name => "jamesonii", :genus => { :id => 29, :name => "Gentianella", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "132" }, :scientific => "Gentianella jamesonii", :author => "Gentianella jamesonii (Hook.) Fabris ", :tropicos => "13801793", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes; tallos solitarios o en grupos, robustos, decumbentes a suberectos, hasta 2 m de alto. Hojas opuestas, hasta 13 cm de largo, lanceoladas a ovadas, de 3 a 7 nervaduras, largamente acuminadas. Flores en una cima umbeloide terminal de 4–13 o a veces en fascículos auxiliares o en cimas de 3–5, hasta 11 cm de largo. Cáliz hasta 17 mm de largo, de color morado rojizo, cortamente tubular y los lóbulos angostamente lanceolado-triangulares, acuminados; corola hasta 30 mm, cilíndrico-campanulada, roja o anaranjada con venas rojas, los lóbulos ovado-elípticos, obtusos a subagudos. Estambres 5, de un rosado pálido a oscuro, las anteras azul-moradas. Ovario morado, el estigma bilobulado, morado-magenta. Categoría UICN de EN (En Peligro). ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, solitary or in groups, robust, stems decumbent to suberect, up to 2 m high. Leaves opposite, up to 13 cm long, lanceolate to ovate, 3-7-nerved, long-acuminate. Flowers in terminal umbeloid cymes of 4-13 or sometimes in auxiliary fascicles or cymes of 3-5, up to 11 cm long. Calyx up to 17 mm long, reddish purple, shortly tubular, the lobes narrowly lanceolate-triangular, acuminate. Corolla up to 30 mm, cylindrical-campanulate, red or orange with red veins, lobes ovate-elliptic, obtuse to subacute. Stamens 5, pale to dark pink, anthers blue-purple; ovary purple, stigma bilobed, purple-magenta. ", :distribution_en => " endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 219, :name => "hallii ", :genus => { :id => 32, :name => "Gynoxys", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "151" }, :scientific => "Gynoxys hallii ", :author => "Gynoxys hallii Hieron.", :tropicos => "2706400", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles hasta 6 m de altura. Ramitas opuesto-decusadas, grises. Ramas, envés de las hojas e inflorescencias densamente blanco-lanosas. Corteza parda, agrietada. Hojas simples, opuestas, decusadas, oblongas u oblongo-lanceoladas, 5–8 × 1–3 cm, la base redondeada u obtusa, los márgenes enteros y engrosados, el ápice agudo, el haz verde brillante, el envés completamente gris y tomentoso por la presencia de tricomas muy densos; nervadura pinnada, los nervios secundarios poco visibles. Inflorescencia una panícula terminal con ramitas opuesto-decusadas, ca.7 cm de largo, formada de varios capítulos. Flores alrededor de 15 por capítulo, amarillas. Capítulos 1–1.4 cm de largo, grises. Flores externas con lígulas oblongo-espatuladas, amarillas, con la base atenuada y el ápice con 3–4 dientes; flores internas tubulares con 5 lóbulos triangulares cortos, recurvados; estilo con 2 ramas recurvadas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees up to 6 m tall. Branchlets opposite-decussate, gray. Branches, undersides of leaves and inflorescences densely white-woolly. Bark brown, cracked. Leaves simple, opposite, decussate, oblong or oblong-lanceolate, 5-8 × 1-3 cm, base rounded or obtuse, margins entire and thick, apex acute, leaf surface bright green above, completely gray and tomentose below due to the presence of very dense trichomes, pinnately veined, secondary veins inconspicuous. Inflorescence a terminal panicle with opposite-decussate twigs, ca.7 cm long, composed of several heads. Flowers around 15 per head, yellow. Heads 1-1.4 cm long, gray. Outer flowers with oblong-spatulate ligules, yellow, with attenuated base and apex with 3-4 teeth; internal flowers tubular with 5 triangular short lobes, recurved; style with 2 recurved branches. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 220, :name => "ferruginea", :genus => { :id => 126, :name => "Herperomeles", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" } }, :scientific => "Herperomeles ferruginea", :author => "Hesperomeles ferruginea (Pers.) Benth.", :tropicos => "27800532", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Árboles hasta 10 m de altura, la copa ancha, muy densa. Corteza fuertemente agrietada. Ramas, envés de las hojas y cáliz cubiertos de un denso tomento ferrugíneo. Hojas simples, alternas, ovado-oblongas, 5–10 × 4–6 cm, serradas, tiesas, el envés ferrugíneo por la presencia de tricomas muy densos, la base redondeada o truncada, los márgenes serrados o dentados, el ápice obtuso; nervadura pinnada, prominente por el envés. Inflorescencia una cima terminal, ca.10 cm de largo. Flores numerosas; receptáculo cupuliforme, profundo; cáliz con 5 lóbulos ovados, pardos, 2–3 mm de largo; pétalos 5, blanquecino-rosados, obovados con la base decurrente, ca. 10 mm de largo. Fruto un pomo, más o menos redondeado, ca. 1 cm de diámetro, truncado en el ápice, verde tornando rojo-púrpura, agridulce. ", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Bolivia. ", :description_en => "Trees up to 10 m tall, with wide very dense crown. Bark heavily cracked. Branches, undersides of leaves and calyx covered with dense ferruginous tomentum. Leaves simple, alternate, ovate-oblong, 5-10 × 4-6 cm, serrated, stiff, ferruginous below due to the presence of very dense trichomes, base rounded or truncated, margins serrated or toothed, apex obtuse, pinnately veined, veins prominent below. Inflorescence a terminal cyme, ca. 10 cm long. Flowers numerous; receptacle cupuliform, deep; calyx lobes 5, ovate, brown, 2-3 mm long; petals 5, white-pink, obovate with decurrent base, ca. 10 mm long. Fruit a pome, more or less rounded, ca. 1 cm in diameter, truncate at the apex, green turning red-purple, bittersweet. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 221, :name => "sessiliflora", :genus => { :id => 38, :name => "Hypochaeris", :family => { :id => 3, :name => "asteraceae", :old_id => "23" }, :old_id => "174" }, :scientific => "Hypochaeris sessiliflora", :author => "Hypochaeris sessiliflora Kunth", :tropicos => "2702714", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 5, :name => "rosette", :old_id => "58" }, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, generalmente pilosas, solitarias o formando grupos pequeños. Hojas en rosetas basales de 3 cm de diámetro. Raíz leñosa, contráctil. Hojas largamente oblanceoladas, 3.5–10 × 0.5–1.4 cm, la base ahusada, los márgenes conspicuamente dentados, el ápice agudo, el haz glabro, lustroso; nervios secundarios conspicuos por el envés. Inflorescencia en capítulo homógamo, solitario, ligulado; filarias multiseriadas, glabras, lanosas en la superficie externa; receptáculo plano. Flores liguladas, hasta 3 cm de largo, oblongas, amarillas, denticuladas en el ápice; limbo de las flores externas más largo que el de las internas; papus de cerdas plumosas color crema; estilo con dos ramas recurvadas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, usually hairy, solitary or in small groups. Leaves in basal rosettes 3 cm in diameter. Root woody, contractile. Leaves long oblanceolate, 3.5-10 × 0.5-1.4 cm, tapering at base, margins conspicuously toothed, apex acute, glabrous, shiny upper leaf; secondary veins prominent below. Inflorescence an homogamous head, solitary, ligulate. Phyllaries multiseriate, glabrous, wooly on the outer surface; receptacle flat. Ligulate flowers, up to 3 cm long, oblong, yellow, denticulate at the apex; limb of the external flowers longer than the one of the internal ones; pappus of feathery bristles, cream color; style with two branches, recurved. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 222, :name => "virgata", :genus => { :id => 127, :name => "Lamouroxia", :family => { :id => 4, :name => "orobanchaceae", :old_id => "30" } }, :scientific => "Lamouroxia virgata", :author => "Lamourouxia virgata Kunth", :tropicos => "29200817", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes, leñosas en la base, 0.6–1.2 m de alto. Tallos erectos o apoyados en la vegetación circundante. Ramas numerosas, ascendentes, alargadas, con pelos suaves, cortos y en líneas decurrentes hacia la base de la hoja. Hojas opuestas y decusadas, lanceoladas, 1.5–4 × 3-8 mm, glabras, verdes con tintes cafés, sésiles o con pecíolos cortos, el ápice agudo, los márgenes dentados, con dientes ascendentes, algunas veces crenados y revolutos. Inflorescencias en racimos, cubiertos con pelos suaves muy cortos, a menudo brácteas en forma de hoja; pedicelos de 3–10 mm de largo. Cáliz 10–16 mm largo, glabro a puberulento, los lóbulos de 5–12 mm de largo, ampliamente lanceolados, agudos o apiculados, verdes con tintes rojizos. Corola bilabiada, densamente puberulenta por fuera, magenta o violeta, el interior del labio superior de la corola de color rosa pálido, 27–42 mm de largo, el perianto y el labio inferior 8–15 mm de largo, el tubo y la garganta comprimidos lateralmente. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador.", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, woody at the base, 0.6-1.2 m high. Stems erect or leaning on the surrounding vegetation. Branches numerous, ascending, elongated, with smooth, short and decurrent hair lines to the base of the leaf. Leaves opposite and decussate, lanceolate, 1.5-4 × 3-8 mm, glabrous, green with brown tints, sessile or with short petioles, apex acute, margins toothed, with ascending teeth, sometimes crenate and revolute. Inflorescences in racemes, covered with soft, very short hairs, often with leafy bracts; pedicels 3-10 mm long. Calyx 10-16 mm long, glabrous to puberulent, lobes 5-12 mm long, broadly lanceolate, acute or apiculate, green with reddish tints. Corolla bilabiate, densely puberulent on the outside, magenta or violet, the inside of the upper lip of the corolla pale pink, 27-42 mm long, perianth and lower lip 8-15 mm long, tube and throat laterally compressed. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 223, :name => "rupestris", :genus => { :id => 128, :name => "Macleania", :family => { :id => 13, :name => "ericaceae", :old_id => "91" } }, :scientific => "Macleania rupestris", :author => "Macleania rupestris (Kunth) A. C. Sm.", :tropicos => "12300895", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos epífitos o terrestres, 0.6–2 m de alto; tallos glabros a moderadamente pubescentes, las amitas glabras a densamente pilosas, los vellos cortos. Hojas alternas, 4–8 × 2–5 cm, elípticas, ovadas a coriáceas, oblongas, la base redondeada a cuneada, raramente cordata, los márgenes enteros, el ápice obtuso o redondeado. Inflorescencia racimosa, con 10–20 flores. Racimos a menudo dirigidos hacia atrás; corola cilíndrica a largamente urceolada, 10–15 mm de largo, carnosa, rosado claro a rosado oscuro; estambres amarillos; estilo rosado oscuro. Cáliz, 5–7 mm de largo, ciatiforme con 5 dientes diminutos, verde claro; pedicelos engrosados. Frutos bayas esféricas, 12–15 mm de diámetro, glabras, carnosas, blanco-verde. ", :distribution_es => " Costa Rica a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Epiphytic or terrestrial shrubs, 0.6 to 2 m high; stems glabrous to moderately pubescent, branchlets glabrous to densely hairy, short hairs. Leaves alternate, 4-8 × 2-5 cm, elliptic to ovate leathery, oblong, base rounded to cuneate, rarely cordate, margins entire, obtuse or rounded apex. Inflorescence racemose, with 10-20 flowers. Racemes often downwardly; corolla cylindrical to long-urceolate, 10-15 mm long, fleshy, light pink to dark pink; stamens yellow; style dark pink. Calyx 5-7 mm long, cyathiform with 5 minute teeth, light green; pedicels swollen. Fruits spherical berries, 12-15 mm in diameter, glabrous, fleshy, white-green. ", :distribution_en => " Costa Rica to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 224, :name => "bracteolata", :genus => { :id => 45, :name => "Miconia", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "202" }, :scientific => "Miconia bracteolata", :author => "Miconia bracteolata (Bonpl.) DC.", :tropicos => "20300972", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles de 3–15 m de alto. Ramas jóvenes, pecíolos, envés de las hojas e inflorescencias cubiertos de un denso indumento de tricomas pinoideos, ocre-amarillentos a ferrugíneos. Hojas simples, opuestas, 4–6 × 1.5–3 cm, oblongo-elípticas, subcoriáceas, la base ligeramente obtusa, los márgenes enteros, el ápice agudo; el haz escasamente puberulento, lustroso; el envés densamente puberulento, con tricomas color ocre-amarillento a café claro. Inflorescencias en cimas terminales, de 8–10 cm de largo, con abundantes flores. Flores pentámeras, subsésiles, 5–6 mm de largo; hipanto terete, 2–3 mm de largo, cubierto de una densa capa de tricomas pinoideos; cáliz de 0.5–1 mm de largo; pétalos blanco-crema; estambres dimórficos, blanquecinos; estigma capitado. Fruto una baya verdosa, esparcida a densamente puberulenta; semillas numerosas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia, Ecuador y Perú.", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees 3-15 m tall. Young branches, petioles, undersides of leaves and inflorescences covered with a dense indumentum of pinoide yellowish to ferruginous trichomes. Leaves simple, opposite, 4-6 × 1.5-3 cm, oblong-elliptic, subcoriaceous, base slightly obtuse, margins entire, apex acute, leaf surface slightly puberulent and shiny above, densely puberulent, with yellowish to light brown trichomes below. Inflorescences in terminal cymes, 8-10 cm long, with abundant flowers. Flowers 5-merous, subsessile, 5-6 mm long; hypanthium terete, 2-3 mm long, covered with a dense layer of pinoide trichomes; calyx 0.5-1 mm long; petals creamy-white; stamens dimorphic, whitish; stigma capitated. Fruit a greenish berry, scattered to densely puberulent; seeds numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 225, :name => "corymbiformis", :genus => { :id => 45, :name => "Miconia", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "202" }, :scientific => "Miconia corymbiformis", :author => "Miconia corymbiformis Cogn.", :tropicos => "20302372", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Árboles de 4–15 m de alto, glabro. Ramas robustas, marcadamente cuadrangulares. Corteza fisurada, café-rojiza; madera dura. Hojas simples, opuestas, 6–17 × 5–9 cm, oblongo-elípticas, coriáceas, la base obtusa a redondeada, los márgenes enteros, el ápice agudo a ligeramente acuminado, el haz lustroso, glabro, el envés escasamente furfuráceo sobre los nervios; pecíolos rojizos, 2.5–6 cm de largo. Flores pentámeras, 8–12 mm de largo; un par de bractéolas caducas en la floración; hipanto terete, verde-amarillento, con tintes color rojo vino, glabro, 5–7 mm de largo; cáliz rojizo, los lóbulos redondeados, con un diente externo agudo, proyectado apicalmente; pétalos color crema a amarillo pálido, de 4–5 mm; estambres color crema, anteras blancas; estigma capitado. Infrutescencia en panícula de aspecto corimbiforme, robusta, de 12–20 cm de largo.  Fruto una baya verde-grisácea; semillas numerosas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador.", :description_en => "Trees 4-15 m tall, glabrous. Branches sturdy, markedly quadrangular. Bark fissured, red-brown; wood hard. Leaves simple, opposite, 6-17 × 5-9 cm, oblong-elliptic, leathery, base obtuse to rounded, margins entire, apex acute to slightly acuminate, leaf blade lustrous and glabrous above, slightly furfuraceous below on the nerves; petioles reddish, 2.5-6 cm long. Flowers 5-merous, 8-12 mm long; bracteoles caducous at flowering; hypanthium terete, yellowish-green, with red wine tints, glabrous, 5-7 mm long; calyx reddish, lobes rounded with a sharp external tooth apically projected; petals cream to pale yellow, 4-5 mm; stamens cream colored, anthers white; stigma capitate. Infructescence in corymbiform panicle, robust, 12-20 cm long. Fruit a green-gray berry; seeds numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 17, :name => "esmeraldas" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 226, :name => "crocea", :genus => { :id => 45, :name => "Miconia", :family => { :id => 7, :name => "melastomataceae", :old_id => "48" }, :old_id => "202" }, :scientific => "Miconia crocea", :author => "Miconia crocea (Desr.) Naudin", :tropicos => "20302374", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles de 1.5–10 m de alto, glabro. Tallos teretes, duros y flexibles. Corteza café grisácea. Ramas fragantes. Inflorescencia en panícula multiflora, de 7–11.5 cm de largo. Hojas simples, opuestas, 4.5–10.8 × 2–3.8 cm, ovado-elípticas a elíptico-lanceoladas, subcoriáceas, la base obtusa, los márgenes setuloso-aserrados, el ápice agudo a ligeramente acuminado; el haz, lustrosos, glabro, el envés densamente hirsuto en las axilas de los nervios primarios; pecíolos rojizos, 1–2.5 cm de largo. Flores 6-7-meras, 6–8 mm de largo; hipanto terete, verde claro, 3–4 mm de largo; cáliz tubular, verde-rojizo, los lóbulos con dientes externos agudos, proyectados apicalmente; pétalos blancos, 2–3 mm de largo; estambres amarillos; estigma capitado. Infrutescencia con numerosos frutos. Fruto una baya morado-grisácea, jugosa; ápice del cáliz cuando seco, se repliega formando un reborde blanquecino; semillas numerosas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador.", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees, 1.5-10 m tall, glabrous. Stems terete, hard but flexible. Bark grayish brown. Branches fragrant. Inflorescence in a multiflowered panicle 7-11.5 cm long. Leaves simple, opposite, 4.5-10.8 × 2-3.8 cm, ovate-elliptic to elliptic-lanceolate, subcoriaceous, base obtuse, margins setulose-serrate, apex acute to slightly acuminate, leaf surface lustrous and  glabrous above, densely hirsute in the axils of the primary nerves below; petioles reddish, 1-2.5 cm long. Flowers 6-7-merous, 6-8 mm long; hypanthium terete, light green, 3-4 mm long; calyx tubular, green-red, lobes with acute external teeth, apically projected. Petals white, 2-3 mm long; stamens yellow; capitated stigma. Infrutescence with many fruits. Fruit a purple-gray berry, juicy; calyx apex when dry folding to form a whitish edge; seeds numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 227, :name => "phyllanthos", :genus => { :id => 48, :name => "Nototriche", :family => { :id => 30, :name => "malvaceae", :old_id => "220" }, :old_id => "221" }, :scientific => "Nototriche phyllanthos", :author => "Nototriche phyllanthos (Cav.) A.W. Hill", :tropicos => "50260807", :color1 => { :id => 9, :name => "blue", :old_id => "127" }, :color2 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 1, :name => "cushion", :old_id => "4" }, :description_es => "Hierbas acaulescentes, formando almohadillas pequeñas a ras del suelo. Los tricomas estrellados, blanco-gris. Ramificadas bajo el suelo. La raíz leñosa, profunda. Hojas alternas, amontonadas en la punta de los tallos, profundamente palmati-lobuladas, ca. 10 × 15 mm, con 3–5 lóbulos y cada uno dividido en varios segmentos angostos de ca. 2 mm de ancho, el haz densamente gris-pubescente, el envés verde brillante; pecíolo ensanchado, envainador, las estípulas laterales, agrandadas. Flores solitarias entre las hojas, erectas, muy vistosas; cáliz ca. 10 mm de largo, profundamente lobulado, los lóbulos triangulares, densamente estrellado-pubescentes; corola hasta 25 mm, con 5 pétalos libres, traslapados en la base, azul-violeta intenso, con el centro blanco y verde-amarillento basalmente. Estambres fusionados formando una columna glabra, amarilla en la base, blanca distalmente, ligeramente más corta que la corola, las anteras amarillas amontonadas en el ápice de la columna; estigmas surgiendo entre las anteras, rosados. Fruto de mericarpos hirsutos, rostrados. Categoría UICN de LC (Preocupación Menor). ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Nototriche phyllanthos Acaulescent herbs, forming small single cushions at ground level, branched underground. Trichomes stellate, white-gray, roots woody and deep. Leaves alternate, crowded at tips of stems, deeply palmati-lobed, ca. 10 × 15 mm, with 3-5 lobes and each one divided into several narrow segments ca. 2 mm wide, the leaf surface densely gray-pubescent above, bright green below; petiole swollen and sheathed, lateral stipule andenlarged. Flowers solitary among the leaves, erect, conspicuous. Calyx ca. 10 mm long, deeply lobed, lobes triangular, densely stellate-pubescent; corolla up to 25 mm with 5 free petals, overlapping at the base, intense violet-blue, with white and yellowish-green center at baseline. Stamens fused forming a glabrous column, yellow at the base, distally white, slightly shorter than the corolla; anthers yellow crowded at apex of the column; stigmas emerging from the anthers, pink. Fruit of mericarps, bristly, rostrate. ", :distribution_en => " Endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 228, :name => "ecuadorensis", :genus => { :id => 129, :name => "Oreopanax", :family => { :id => 58, :name => "araliaceae" } }, :scientific => "Oreopanax ecuadorensis", :author => "Oreopanax ecuadorensis Seem.", :tropicos => "50106139", :color1 => { :id => 1, :name => "white", :old_id => "3" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Árboles hasta 10 m de altura, copa ancha, densa.  Corteza parda, fuertemente agrietada. Ramitas con cicatrices agrupadas dejadas por la caída de estípulas. Ramas, pecíolos, envés de las hojas e inflorescencias cubiertas por un denso tomento lanoso color ocre-crema. Hojas alternas, helicoidales, ligera o marcadamente 3–5 lobuladas o enteras, muy variables en tamaño, 10–30 × 5–20 cm, coriáceas, glabras y brillantes por el haz, lanuginosas por el envés; la base redondeada, truncada; los márgenes con dientes dispersos, el ápice acuminado, obtuso o redondeado; palmatinervias, las nervaduras conspicuas en el envés. Inflorescencia una panícula terminal de cabezas, ca. 30 cm de largo, las cabezas ca. 2 cm de diámetro, amontonadas. Flores numerosas, comprimidas en cada cabeza; cáliz reducido a un anillo; pétalos ovado-lanceolados, ca. 3 mm de largo, blanco-cremas; estambres 5. Fruto una drupa, globosa, ca. 1 cm de diámetro, negra al madurar. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia, Ecuador y Perú.", :description_en => "Trees up to 10 m tall, with wide dense crown. Bark brown, heavily fissurated. Twigs with scars left by the caducous stipules. Branches, petioles, undersides of leaves and inflorescences covered by dense woolly yellowish-cream tomentum. Leave alternate, helicoid, poorly or strongly 3-5 lobed or entire, very variable in size, 10-30 × 5-20 cm, leathery, glabrous, leaf surface glabrous and shiny above, lanuginose below; base rounded, truncated; margins with scattered teeth; apex acuminate, obtuse or rounded, palmately veined, conspicuously so below. Inflorescence a terminal panicle of heads, ca. 30 cm long, the heads ca. 2 cm in diameter, crowded. Many flowers, compressed on each head; calix reduced to a ring; ovate-lanceolate, petals ca. 3 mm long, white-cream; stamens 5. Fruit a drupe, globose, ca. 1 cm in diameter, black when mature. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 229, :name => "pauta", :genus => { :id => 62, :name => "Polylepis", :family => { :id => 21, :name => "rosaceae", :old_id => "147" }, :old_id => "276" }, :scientific => "Polylepis pauta", :author => "Polylepis pauta Hieron.", :tropicos => "27800833", :color1 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Árboles hasta 8 m de altura. Corteza multilaminada, las láminas cartáceas, marrón-rojizas, se desprenden con el crecimiento. Las partes jóvenes con tomento blanquecino. Yemas pilosas. Hojas imparipinnadas, agrupadas al extremo de cortas ramitas, 6–10 cm de largo. Folíolos 5–9, oblongos, espatulados o menos frecuente obovados, 2–3 × 0.6–1.1 cm, la base oblicua, los márgenes serrados, el ápice emarginado, glabros por el haz, pubescentes por el envés, tricomas adnados. Inflorescencia un racimo péndulo, hasta 12 cm de largo, el raquis blanco-tomentoso, las brácteas lanceoladas, ca. 1 cm de largo, pilosas. Flores con 4 sépalos verdes, ca. 5 mm de largo; pétalos ausentes; estambres numerosos con anteras púrpuras. Fruto incluido en el hipanto, 2–6 mm de largo, con varios aguijones. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú.", :description_en => "Trees up to 8 m tall. Bark multilaminated, papery, red-brown. Young parts with whitish tomentum. Hairy buds. Leaves imparipinnate, clustered at end of short twigs, 6-10 cm long. Leaflets 5-9, oblong, spatulate or less frequent, obovate, 2-3 × 0.6-1.1 cm, base oblique, margins serrated, apex emarginate, leaf surface glabrous above, pubescent below, trichomes adnate. Inflorescence a hanging raceme, up to 12 cm long, rachis white-tomentose, bracts lanceolate, ca. 1cm long, hairy. Flowers with 4 green sepals, ca. 5 mm in length; petals absent; stamens numerous with purple anthers. Fruit included in the hypanthium, 2-6 mm long, prickly. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }] }
{ :id => 230, :name => "andicola", :genus => { :id => 67, :name => "Ribes", :family => { :id => 39, :name => "grossulariaceae", :old_id => "299" }, :old_id => "300" }, :scientific => "Ribes andicola", :author => "Ribes andicola Jancz.", :tropicos => "29100279", :color1 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 2.5 m de altura, muy ramificados, más o menos escandentes. Ramitas con numerosas cicatrices derivadas de estípulas caducas. Hojas agrupadas al final de cortas ramitas, ovadas, más o menos trilobadas, 1–4 cm de largo, los márgenes doblemente serrados, la base redondeada o subcordata, el ápice agudo; nervadura 5-nervia; pecíolo alado en su parte media basal, 1–2.5 cm de largo, estípulas presentes. Inflorescencia axilar, en racimo péndulo, 4–7 cm de largo; cada flor acompañada de una bractéola lanceolada de 3–5 mm de largo. Flores funcionalmente unisexuales, 3–4.5 mm de largo, rojo oscuras; cáliz 2–3 mm de largo; pétalos 5, 1–2 mm de largo. Fruto una baya, redondeada, 4–6 cm de diámetro, roja o anaranjada; semillas numerosas. ", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Ecuador.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 2.5 m tall, densely branched, more or less scandent. Twigs with numerous scars derived from deciduous stipules. Leaves clustered at the end of short twigs, ovate, more or less lobed, 1-4 cm long, margins twice serrate, base rounded or subcordate, apex acute, 5-nerved; petiole winged in its middle basal part, 1-2.5 cm long, stipules present. Inflorescence axillary in pendulum cluster, 4-7 cm long; each flower with a lanceolate bracteole, 3-5 mm long. Flowers functionally unisexual, 3-4.5 mm long, dark red; calyx 2-3 mm long; petals 5, 1-2 mm long. Fruit a berry, rounded, 4-6 cm in diameter, red or orange; seeds numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 231, :name => "hirtum", :genus => { :id => 67, :name => "Ribes", :family => { :id => 39, :name => "grossulariaceae", :old_id => "299" }, :old_id => "300" }, :scientific => "Ribes hirtum", :author => "Ribes hirtum Willd. Ex Roem. & Schult.", :tropicos => "29100296", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 2.5 m de altura, muy ramificados. Ramitas con numerosas cicatrices derivadas de estípulas caducas. Yemas hirsutas. Hojas agrupadas al final de cortas ramitas, ovadas, más o menos trilobadas, 1–5 cm de largo, el haz glabro, el envés pubescente, los márgenes doblemente serrados, la base redondeada o cordata, el ápice agudo; la nervadura 5-nervia; pecíolo alado, 1–2.5 cm de largo con el margen ciliado; estípulas presentes. Inflorescencia axilar, un racimo péndulo, 4–8 cm de largo; cada flor acompañada de una bractéola lanceolada de 4–6 mm de largo. Flores funcionalmente unisexuales, 7–11 mm de largo; cáliz 2–3 mm de largo pubescente; pétalos 5, 1–2 mm de largo, cáliz y pétalos rosados; ovario hirsuto, verde o rosado. Fruto una baya casi redondeada, 6–10 mm de diámetro, roja al madurar; semillas numerosas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia y Ecuador.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 2.5 m tall, densely branched. Twigs with numerous scars from deciduous stipules. Buds hirsute. Leaves clustered at the end of short twigs, ovate, more or less lobed, 1-5 cm long, leaf surface glabrous above, pubescent below , 5-nerved, margins twice serrated, base rounded or cordate, apex acute; petiole winged, 1-2.5 cm long with ciliate margins; stipules present. Inflorescence a hanging axillary raceme, 4-8 cm long; flower each subtended by a lanceolate bracteole 4-6 mm long. Flowers functionally unisexual, 7-11 mm long; calyx 2-3 mm long, pubescent; petals 5, 1-2 mm long, calyx and pink; ovary hirsute, green or pink. Fruit an almost round berry, 6-10 mm in diameter, red when mature; seeds numerous. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia and Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 232, :name => "pichinchensis", :genus => { :id => 130, :name => "Salvia", :family => { :id => 12, :name => "lamiaceae", :old_id => "82" } }, :scientific => "Salvia pichinchensis", :author => "Salvia pichinchensis Benth.", :tropicos => "17605072", :color1 => { :id => 9, :name => "blue", :old_id => "127" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 1.5 m de alto. Tallo cuadrangular de ca. 4 mm de diámetro, con tintes azulados, tricomas blancos. Hojas simples, opuestas, elípticas, 3–10 × 1–6 cm, la base subcordado-oblicua, los márgenes serrados, el ápice agudo, el haz ampolloso con tintes amarillo-verdosos, el envés con abundantes tricomas; nervadura conspicua, pinnada, reticulada; estípulas infrapeciolares. Inflorescencia en verticilastros bracteados, ca. de 21 cm de largo. Flores ca. 16 mm de largo; cáliz tubular, bilabiado, verde con los lóbulos triangulares, mucronatos, con los bordes superiores púrpura; corola tubular, bilabiada, azul-claro, con tintes blanco, labio superior erecto; estambres 2, ascendiendo paralelamente bajo el labio superior junto con el estilo largo, bífido cerca del ápice. ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 1.5 m tall. Stem quadrangular, ca. 4 mm width, with bluish tints, trichomes white. Leaves simple, opposite, elliptic, 3-10 × 1-6 cm, base subcordate-oblique, margins serrated, apex acute, leaf surface bullate with yellow-green tints above, with abundant trichomes below; venation conspicuous, pinnate, reticulated; stipules infrapetiolar. Inflorescence in a bracteate verticillasters, ca. 21 cm long. Flowers ca. 16 mm long; calyx tubular, bilabiate, green with triangular lobes, mucronate with purple edges; corolla tubular, bilabiate, light-blue, with white tints, upper lip erect; stamens 2, ascending parallel under the upper lip along with the long style, forked near the apex. ", :distribution_en => " endemic to Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }, { :id => 11, :name => "zamora-chinchipe" }] }
{ :id => 233, :name => "quitensis", :genus => { :id => 131, :name => "Saracha", :family => { :id => 59, :name => "solanaceae" } }, :scientific => "Saracha quitensis", :author => "Saracha quitensis (Hook.) Miers", :tropicos => "29606366", :color1 => { :id => 6, :name => "purple", :old_id => "47" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos hasta 5 m de altura. Ramitas a menudo terminadas en espinas rígidas, o estas sobre el tronco, las ramitas más jóvenes con escamas o protuberancias de 0.5–1 mm de largo que dan un aspecto rugoso. Hojas simples, alternas, helicoidales, 1–5 ×1–3 cm, coriáceas y algo crasas, glabras, la base obtusa, los márgenes enteros, el ápice obtuso o redondeado, el haz glabro y brillante, el envés con puntuaciones o rayitas cortas; nervaduras conspicuas en ambas superficies. Inflorescencia en fascículos terminales o sobre las ramitas, con 2–5 flores; cáliz anchamente tubular, ca. 4 mm de largo, terminado en 5 lóbulos agudos, verde; corola tubular, 1–2.3 cm de largo, terminado en 5 lóbulos expandidos, violeta; estambres 5, las anteras azul-verde. Fruto una baya redondeada, ca. 1 cm de diámetro, sobre el cáliz persistente, verde tornando morada; semillas numerosas. ", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Perú. ", :description_en => "Shrubs up to 5 m tall. Twigs often ending in rigid spines, or these ones on the bark. Young twigs with scales or projections 0.5-1 mm long giving a rough appearance. Leaves simple, alternate, helicoidal, 1-5 × 1-3 cm, leathery and somewhat thick, glabrous, base obtuse, margins entire, apex obtuse or rounded, leaf surface glabrous and bright above, with punctuations or short lines below. Conspicuous ribs on both surfaces. Inflorescence in terminal fascicles or on twigs; flowers 2-5; calyx broadly tubular, ca. 4 mm long, with 5 acute, green lobes; corolla tubular, 1-2.3 cm long, with 5 expanded lobes, violet; stamens 5, anthers blue-green. Fruit a rounded berry, ca. 1 cm in diameter, the persistent calyx, green turning purple; numerous seeds. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 234, :name => "longebracteatus", :genus => { :id => 132, :name => "Tristerix", :family => { :id => 54, :name => "loranthaceae" } }, :scientific => "Tristerix longebracteatus", :author => "Tristerix longebracteatus (Desr.) Barlow & Wiens", :tropicos => "19100516", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 8, :name => "red", :old_id => "71" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Arbustos parásitos sobre ramas de otras plantas. Ramas hasta 1.5 m de largo. Inflorescencia un racimo terminal. Hojas simples, opuestas, lanceoladas, 5–8 × 3–5 cm, crasas, verde, con tintes rojizos o violáceos, la base obtusa o redondeada, los márgenes enteros, el ápice agudo, glabras; nervaduras inconspicuas. Flores vistosas, acompañadas cada una de una bráctea oblonga, 2–3 cm de largo; cáliz ciatiforme, 3–5 mm de largo, verde; corola tubular, 4–6 cm de largo amarillo-rojiza, con 4–6 lóbulos espatulados y recurvados; estambres 5–6, adnados a la corola, amarillos; las anteras rojizo-anaranjadas. Fruto una baya, ca. 1 cm de diámetro, redondeada, verde tornando morada; semillas diminutas. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia a Perú.", :description_en => "Parasitic shrub, on branches of other plants. Branches up to 1.5 m long. Leaves simple, opposite, lanceolate, 5-8 × 3-5 cm, succulent, green with reddish or violet tints, base obtuse or rounded, margins entire, apex acute, glabrous; venation inconspicuous. Inflorescence in a terminal raceme. Flowers showy, each with an oblong bract, 2-3 cm long; calyx cyatiform, 3-5 mm long, green; corolla tubular, 4-6 cm long, reddish-yellow, with 4-6 lobes, spatulate and recurved; stamens 5-6 adnate to the corolla, yellow; anthers reddish-orange. Fruit a berry, ca. 1 cm in diameter, round, green turning purple seeds; minute. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia to Peru.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 14, :name => "pastaza" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 235, :name => "stipularis", :genus => { :id => 133, :name => "Vallea", :family => { :id => 60, :name => "elaeocarpaceae" } }, :scientific => "Vallea stipularis", :author => "Vallea stipularis L. f.", :tropicos => "11700090", :color1 => { :id => 3, :name => "pink", :old_id => "29" }, :color2 => nil, :life_form1 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Árboles hasta 7 m de altura. Corteza superficialmente agrietada. Hojas simples, alternas, ovadas, 3–9 × 2–6 cm, membranáceas, glabras excepto por los mechones de tricomas en las axilas basales por el envés, la base truncada o subcordada, los márgenes enteros, el ápice agudo; nervadura pentanervia en la base y luego pinnada; pecíolo ligeramente engrosado y curvado en el ápice, 2–4 cm; estípulas foliáceas. Inflorescencia axilar, una cima laxa con pocas flores, ca. 8 cm de largo. Flores vistosas; cáliz con 5 sépalos oblongo-lanceolados, 4–5 mm de largo; pétalos 4–5, trilobulados, 0.8–1.1 cm de largo, rosados; estambres numerosos, negros. Fruto una cápsula tuberculada, irregularmente dehiscente por 3–5 valvas, ca. 1.2 cm de diámetro. ", :distribution_es => " Venezuela a Bolivia.", :description_en => "Trees up to 7 m high. Bark fissured. Leaves simple, alternate, ovate, 3-9 × 2-6 cm, membranous, glabrous except for tufts of trichomes in basal axils on the surface below, base truncate or subcordate, margins entire, apex acute; 5-nerved at the base and then pinnate; petiole slightly swollen and curved at the apex, 2-4 cm; stipules leafy. Inflorescence sxillary, a loose cyme with few flowers, ca. 8 cm long. Flowers showy; calyx with 5 sepals, oblong-lanceolate, 4-5 mm long; petals 4-5-lobed, 0.8-1.1 cm long, bright pink; stamens numerous, black. Fruit a tuberculate capsule, irregularly dehiscent by 3-5 valves, ca. 1.2 cm in diameter. ", :distribution_en => " Venezuela to Bolivia.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 2, :name => "bolívar" }, { :id => 3, :name => "cañar" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 15, :name => "el oro" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 6, :name => "loja" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 16, :name => "sucumbíos" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 236, :name => "pichinchensis", :genus => { :id => 121, :name => "Buddleja", :family => { :id => 55, :name => "scrophulariaceae" } }, :scientific => "Buddleja pichinchensis", :author => "Buddleja pichinchensis Kunth", :tropicos => "19000333", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 5, :name => "orange", :old_id => "37" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 3, :name => "shrub", :old_id => "10" }, :life_form2 => { :id => 8, :name => "tree", :old_id => "275" }, :description_es => "Arbustos o árboles hasta 6 m de altura. Ramas opuesto-decusadas. Tallos, hojas y flores recubiertos de un denso tomento lanoso gris-blanquecino. Hojas simples, opuestas, lanceoladas, 4–7 × 0.5–2.5 cm, coriáceas, la base obtusa o aguda, los márgenes crenulados, el ápice acuminado, el haz ampolloso, el envés lanuginoso, grisáceo, con tricomas estrellados; nervadura elevada en el haz. Inflorescencia una panícula cimosa, terminal, ca. 8 cm de largo, formando 2–3 niveles de ramificaciones, y terminado en varias cabezuelas compactas; cada cabezuela con 15–24 flores. Corola 3–5 mm de largo, amarilla a anaranjada, con los lóbulos recurvados; cáliz 5–7 mm de largo, densamente lanoso. Fruto capsular, ovoide, 6–10 mm de largo, bivalvado, con verticilos florales persistentes. ", :distribution_es => " Colombia, Ecuador y Bolivia. ", :description_en => "Perennial herbs, stems decumbent or stoloniferous, up to 18 cm tall, simple or with few branches. Flowering stems up to 13 cm high. Leaves opposite, whorled, numerous, crowded, 8-30 × 4-9 mm, proximal ones and in vegetative stems are closer to each other, ascending, narrow, spatulated, elliptic to obovate, obtuse to acute, distal ones elliptical or oblanceolate to spatulate-obovate, acute or acuminate. Flowers nodding in ascending pedicels up to 20 mm. Inflorescence is umbeloid top of 3-9, solitary or together. Calyx short-tubular, 4.5-8.5 mm, lobes are oblong-lanceolate, erect, up to 2 mm wide, acute to apiculate. Corolla up to 12 mm, yellowish green to yellow, lobes ovate up to 4 mm wide, with teeth near the apex, subacute to acute, with slender spurs, recurved and pendant, up to 3.5 × 1.5 mm. ", :distribution_en => " Ecuador.", :provincias => [{ :id => 1, :name => "azuay" }, { :id => 4, :name => "carchi" }, { :id => 5, :name => "chimborazo" }, { :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 13, :name => "imbabura" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }
{ :id => 237, :name => "pulchella ", :genus => { :id => 33, :name => "Halenia", :family => { :id => 19, :name => "gentianaceae", :old_id => "128" }, :old_id => "156" }, :scientific => "Halenia pulchella ", :author => "Halenia pulchella Gilg", :tropicos => "13800315", :color1 => { :id => 4, :name => "yellow", :old_id => "36" }, :color2 => { :id => 2, :name => "green", :old_id => "15" }, :life_form1 => { :id => 2, :name => "herb", :old_id => "5" }, :life_form2 => nil, :description_es => "Hierbas perennes; los tallos decumbentes o estoloníferos, hasta 18 cm de alto, simples o con pocas ramas. Tallos florales hasta 13 cm de alto. Flores nutantes, en pedicelos ascendentes de hasta 20 mm. Inflorescencia en una cima umbeloide de 3-9, solitarias o en conjunto. Hojas opuestas, verticiladas, numerosas, amontonadas, 8-30 × 4-9 mm, en las partes bajas y en los tallos vegetativos son más juntas, ascendentes, angostas, espatuladas, elípticas a obovadas, obtusas a agudas, en las partes más altas elípticas u oblanceoladas a espatuladas-obovadas, agudas o acuminadas. Cáliz cortamente tubular, 4.5-8.5 mm, los lóbulos oblongo-lanceolados, erectos, hasta 2 mm de ancho, agudos a apiculados; corola hasta 12 mm, de un verde amarillento a amarillo, los lóbulos ovados, hasta 4 mm de ancho, con dientes cerca del ápice, subagudos a agudos, con espolones delgados, recurvados y péndulos, hasta 3.5 × 1.5 mm. ", :distribution_es => " Ecuador.", :description_en => "Shrubs or trees, up to 6 m tall. Branches opposite-decussate. Stems, leaves and flowers covered with a gray-white dense woolly tomentum. Leaves simple, opposite, lanceolate, 4-7 × 0.5-2.5 cm, leathery, base obtuse or acute, margins crenulated, apex acuminate, bullous above, lanate below, grayish, with stellate trichomes, venation raised above. Inflorescence a cymose panicle, terminal, ca. 8 cm long, with  2-3 branching levels, and ending in several compact heads, each flower head with 15 to 24 flowers. Corolla 3-5 mm long, yellow to orange, with recurved lobes; calyx 5-7 mm long, densely woolly. Fruit capsular, ovoid, 6-10 mm long, bivalved, with persistent floral whorls. ", :distribution_en => " Colombia, Ecuador and Bolivia. ", :provincias => [{ :id => 12, :name => "cotopaxi" }, { :id => 10, :name => "morona-santiago" }, { :id => 7, :name => "napo" }, { :id => 8, :name => "pichincha" }, { :id => 9, :name => "tungurahua" }] }